74enum class ImplicitItModeTy { Always, Never, ARMOnly, ThumbOnly };
75
76static cl::opt<ImplicitItModeTy> ImplicitItMode(
77 "arm-implicit-it", cl::init(ImplicitItModeTy::ARMOnly),
78 cl::desc("Allow conditional instructions outdside of an IT block"),
79 cl::values(clEnumValN(ImplicitItModeTy::Always, "always",
80 "Accept in both ISAs, emit implicit ITs in Thumb"),
81 clEnumValN(ImplicitItModeTy::Never, "never",
82 "Warn in ARM, reject in Thumb"),
83 clEnumValN(ImplicitItModeTy::ARMOnly, "arm",
84 "Accept in ARM, reject in Thumb"),
85 clEnumValN(ImplicitItModeTy::ThumbOnly, "thumb",
86 "Warn in ARM, emit implicit ITs in Thumb")));
87
88static cl::opt<bool> AddBuildAttributes("arm-add-build-attributes",
89 cl::init(false));
90
91enum VectorLaneTy { NoLanes, AllLanes, IndexedLane };
92
93static inline unsigned extractITMaskBit(unsigned Mask, unsigned Position) {
94 // Position==0 means we're not in an IT block at all. Position==1
95 // means we want the first state bit, which is always 0 (Then).
96 // Position==2 means we want the second state bit, stored at bit 3
97 // of Mask, and so on downwards. So (5 - Position) will shift the
98 // right bit down to bit 0, including the always-0 bit at bit 4 for
99 // the mandatory initial Then.
100 return (Mask >> (5 - Position) & 1);
101}
102
103class UnwindContext {
104 using Locs = SmallVector<SMLoc, 4>;
105
106 MCAsmParser &Parser;
107 Locs FnStartLocs;
108 Locs CantUnwindLocs;
109 Locs PersonalityLocs;
110 Locs PersonalityIndexLocs;
111 Locs HandlerDataLocs;
112 int FPReg;
113
114public:
115 UnwindContext(MCAsmParser &P) : Parser(P), FPReg(ARM::SP) {}
116
117 bool hasFnStart() const { return !FnStartLocs.empty(); }
118 bool cantUnwind() const { return !CantUnwindLocs.empty(); }
119 bool hasHandlerData() const { return !HandlerDataLocs.empty(); }
120
121 bool hasPersonality() const {
122 return !(PersonalityLocs.empty() && PersonalityIndexLocs.empty());
123 }
124
125 void recordFnStart(SMLoc L) { FnStartLocs.push_back(L); }
126 void recordCantUnwind(SMLoc L) { CantUnwindLocs.push_back(L); }
127 void recordPersonality(SMLoc L) { PersonalityLocs.push_back(L); }
128 void recordHandlerData(SMLoc L) { HandlerDataLocs.push_back(L); }
129 void recordPersonalityIndex(SMLoc L) { PersonalityIndexLocs.push_back(L); }
130
131 void saveFPReg(int Reg) { FPReg = Reg; }
132 int getFPReg() const { return FPReg; }
133
134 void emitFnStartLocNotes() const {
135 for (Locs::const_iterator FI = FnStartLocs.begin(), FE = FnStartLocs.end();
136 FI != FE; ++FI)
137 Parser.Note(*FI, ".fnstart was specified here");
138 }
139
140 void emitCantUnwindLocNotes() const {
141 for (Locs::const_iterator UI = CantUnwindLocs.begin(),
142 UE = CantUnwindLocs.end(); UI != UE; ++UI)
143 Parser.Note(*UI, ".cantunwind was specified here");
144 }
145
146 void emitHandlerDataLocNotes() const {
147 for (Locs::const_iterator HI = HandlerDataLocs.begin(),
148 HE = HandlerDataLocs.end(); HI != HE; ++HI)
149 Parser.Note(*HI, ".handlerdata was specified here");
150 }
151
152 void emitPersonalityLocNotes() const {
153 for (Locs::const_iterator PI = PersonalityLocs.begin(),
154 PE = PersonalityLocs.end(),
155 PII = PersonalityIndexLocs.begin(),
156 PIE = PersonalityIndexLocs.end();
157 PI != PE || PII != PIE;) {
158 if (PI != PE && (PII == PIE || PI->getPointer() < PII->getPointer()))
159 Parser.Note(*PI++, ".personality was specified here");
160 else if (PII != PIE && (PI == PE || PII->getPointer() < PI->getPointer()))
161 Parser.Note(*PII++, ".personalityindex was specified here");
162 else
163 llvm_unreachable(".personality and .personalityindex cannot be "
164 "at the same location");
165 }
166 }
167
168 void reset() {
169 FnStartLocs = Locs();
170 CantUnwindLocs = Locs();
171 PersonalityLocs = Locs();
172 HandlerDataLocs = Locs();
173 PersonalityIndexLocs = Locs();
174 FPReg = ARM::SP;
175 }
176};

179class ARMAsmParser : public MCTargetAsmParser {
180 const MCRegisterInfo *MRI;
181 UnwindContext UC;
182
183 ARMTargetStreamer &getTargetStreamer() {
184 assert(getParser().getStreamer().getTargetStreamer() &&
185 "do not have a target streamer");
186 MCTargetStreamer &TS = *getParser().getStreamer().getTargetStreamer();
187 return static_cast<ARMTargetStreamer &>(TS);
188 }
189
190 // Map of register aliases registers via the .req directive.
191 StringMap<unsigned> RegisterReqs;
192
193 bool NextSymbolIsThumb;
194
195 bool useImplicitITThumb() const {
196 return ImplicitItMode == ImplicitItModeTy::Always ||
197 ImplicitItMode == ImplicitItModeTy::ThumbOnly;
198 }
199
200 bool useImplicitITARM() const {
201 return ImplicitItMode == ImplicitItModeTy::Always ||
202 ImplicitItMode == ImplicitItModeTy::ARMOnly;
203 }
204
205 struct {
206 ARMCC::CondCodes Cond; // Condition for IT block.
207 unsigned Mask:4; // Condition mask for instructions.
208 // Starting at first 1 (from lsb).
209 // '1' condition as indicated in IT.
210 // '0' inverse of condition (else).
211 // Count of instructions in IT block is
212 // 4 - trailingzeroes(mask)
213 // Note that this does not have the same encoding
214 // as in the IT instruction, which also depends
215 // on the low bit of the condition code.
216
217 unsigned CurPosition; // Current position in parsing of IT
218 // block. In range [0,4], with 0 being the IT
219 // instruction itself. Initialized according to
220 // count of instructions in block. ~0U if no
221 // active IT block.
222
223 bool IsExplicit; // true - The IT instruction was present in the
224 // input, we should not modify it.
225 // false - The IT instruction was added
226 // implicitly, we can extend it if that
227 // would be legal.
228 } ITState;
229
230 SmallVector<MCInst, 4> PendingConditionalInsts;
231
232 void flushPendingInstructions(MCStreamer &Out) override {
233 if (!inImplicitITBlock()) {
234 assert(PendingConditionalInsts.size() == 0);
235 return;
236 }
237
238 // Emit the IT instruction
239 MCInst ITInst;
240 ITInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2IT);
241 ITInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ITState.Cond));
242 ITInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ITState.Mask));
243 Out.EmitInstruction(ITInst, getSTI());
244
245 // Emit the conditonal instructions
246 assert(PendingConditionalInsts.size() <= 4);
247 for (const MCInst &Inst : PendingConditionalInsts) {
248 Out.EmitInstruction(Inst, getSTI());
249 }
250 PendingConditionalInsts.clear();
251
252 // Clear the IT state
253 ITState.Mask = 0;
254 ITState.CurPosition = ~0U;
255 }
256
257 bool inITBlock() { return ITState.CurPosition != ~0U; }
258 bool inExplicitITBlock() { return inITBlock() && ITState.IsExplicit; }
259 bool inImplicitITBlock() { return inITBlock() && !ITState.IsExplicit; }
260
261 bool lastInITBlock() {
262 return ITState.CurPosition == 4 - countTrailingZeros(ITState.Mask);
263 }
264
265 void forwardITPosition() {
266 if (!inITBlock()) return;
267 // Move to the next instruction in the IT block, if there is one. If not,
268 // mark the block as done, except for implicit IT blocks, which we leave
269 // open until we find an instruction that can't be added to it.
270 unsigned TZ = countTrailingZeros(ITState.Mask);
271 if (++ITState.CurPosition == 5 - TZ && ITState.IsExplicit)
272 ITState.CurPosition = ~0U; // Done with the IT block after this.
273 }
274
275 // Rewind the state of the current IT block, removing the last slot from it.
276 void rewindImplicitITPosition() {
277 assert(inImplicitITBlock());
278 assert(ITState.CurPosition > 1);
279 ITState.CurPosition--;
280 unsigned TZ = countTrailingZeros(ITState.Mask);
281 unsigned NewMask = 0;
282 NewMask |= ITState.Mask & (0xC << TZ);
283 NewMask |= 0x2 << TZ;
284 ITState.Mask = NewMask;
285 }
286
287 // Rewind the state of the current IT block, removing the last slot from it.
288 // If we were at the first slot, this closes the IT block.
289 void discardImplicitITBlock() {
290 assert(inImplicitITBlock());
291 assert(ITState.CurPosition == 1);
292 ITState.CurPosition = ~0U;
293 }
294
295 // Return the low-subreg of a given Q register.
296 unsigned getDRegFromQReg(unsigned QReg) const {
297 return MRI->getSubReg(QReg, ARM::dsub_0);
298 }
299
300 // Get the condition code corresponding to the current IT block slot.
301 ARMCC::CondCodes currentITCond() {
302 unsigned MaskBit = extractITMaskBit(ITState.Mask, ITState.CurPosition);
303 return MaskBit ? ARMCC::getOppositeCondition(ITState.Cond) : ITState.Cond;
304 }
305
306 // Invert the condition of the current IT block slot without changing any
307 // other slots in the same block.
308 void invertCurrentITCondition() {
309 if (ITState.CurPosition == 1) {
310 ITState.Cond = ARMCC::getOppositeCondition(ITState.Cond);
311 } else {
312 ITState.Mask ^= 1 << (5 - ITState.CurPosition);
313 }
314 }
315
316 // Returns true if the current IT block is full (all 4 slots used).
317 bool isITBlockFull() {
318 return inITBlock() && (ITState.Mask & 1);
319 }
320
321 // Extend the current implicit IT block to have one more slot with the given
322 // condition code.
323 void extendImplicitITBlock(ARMCC::CondCodes Cond) {
324 assert(inImplicitITBlock());
325 assert(!isITBlockFull());
326 assert(Cond == ITState.Cond ||
327 Cond == ARMCC::getOppositeCondition(ITState.Cond));
328 unsigned TZ = countTrailingZeros(ITState.Mask);
329 unsigned NewMask = 0;
330 // Keep any existing condition bits.
331 NewMask |= ITState.Mask & (0xE << TZ);
332 // Insert the new condition bit.
333 NewMask |= (Cond != ITState.Cond) << TZ;
334 // Move the trailing 1 down one bit.
335 NewMask |= 1 << (TZ - 1);
336 ITState.Mask = NewMask;
337 }
338
339 // Create a new implicit IT block with a dummy condition code.
340 void startImplicitITBlock() {
341 assert(!inITBlock());
342 ITState.Cond = ARMCC::AL;
343 ITState.Mask = 8;
344 ITState.CurPosition = 1;
345 ITState.IsExplicit = false;
346 }
347
348 // Create a new explicit IT block with the given condition and mask.
349 // The mask should be in the format used in ARMOperand and
350 // MCOperand, with a 1 implying 'e', regardless of the low bit of
351 // the condition.
352 void startExplicitITBlock(ARMCC::CondCodes Cond, unsigned Mask) {
353 assert(!inITBlock());
354 ITState.Cond = Cond;
355 ITState.Mask = Mask;
356 ITState.CurPosition = 0;
357 ITState.IsExplicit = true;
358 }

566 enum ARMMatchResultTy {
567 Match_RequiresITBlock = FIRST_TARGET_MATCH_RESULT_TY,
568 Match_RequiresNotITBlock,
569 Match_RequiresV6,
570 Match_RequiresThumb2,

577
578 ARMAsmParser(const MCSubtargetInfo &STI, MCAsmParser &Parser,
579 const MCInstrInfo &MII, const MCTargetOptions &Options)
580 : MCTargetAsmParser(Options, STI, MII), UC(Parser) {
581 MCAsmParserExtension::Initialize(Parser);
582
583 // Cache the MCRegisterInfo.
584 MRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
585
586 // Initialize the set of available features.
587 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits()));
588
589 // Add build attributes based on the selected target.
590 if (AddBuildAttributes)
591 getTargetStreamer().emitTargetAttributes(STI);
592
593 // Not in an ITBlock to start with.
594 ITState.CurPosition = ~0U;
595
596 NextSymbolIsThumb = false;
597 }
598
599 // Implementation of the MCTargetAsmParser interface:
600 bool ParseRegister(unsigned &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, SMLoc &EndLoc) override;
601 bool ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, StringRef Name,
602 SMLoc NameLoc, OperandVector &Operands) override;
603 bool ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) override;
604
605 unsigned validateTargetOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &Op,
606 unsigned Kind) override;
607 unsigned checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) override;
608
609 bool MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode,
610 OperandVector &Operands, MCStreamer &Out,
611 uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
612 bool MatchingInlineAsm) override;
613 unsigned MatchInstruction(OperandVector &Operands, MCInst &Inst,
614 SmallVectorImpl<NearMissInfo> &NearMisses,
615 bool MatchingInlineAsm, bool &EmitInITBlock,
616 MCStreamer &Out);

627 SMLoc IDLoc, OperandVector &Operands);

629 OperandVector &Operands);
630
631 void doBeforeLabelEmit(MCSymbol *Symbol) override;
632
633 void onLabelParsed(MCSymbol *Symbol) override;
634};

636/// ARMOperand - Instances of this class represent a parsed ARM machine
637/// operand.
638class ARMOperand : public MCParsedAsmOperand {
639 enum KindTy {
640 k_CondCode,
641 k_CCOut,
642 k_ITCondMask,
643 k_CoprocNum,
644 k_CoprocReg,
645 k_CoprocOption,
646 k_Immediate,
647 k_MemBarrierOpt,
648 k_InstSyncBarrierOpt,
649 k_TraceSyncBarrierOpt,
650 k_Memory,
651 k_PostIndexRegister,
652 k_MSRMask,
653 k_BankedReg,
654 k_ProcIFlags,
655 k_VectorIndex,
656 k_Register,
657 k_RegisterList,
658 k_RegisterListWithAPSR,
659 k_DPRRegisterList,
660 k_SPRRegisterList,
661 k_FPSRegisterListWithVPR,
662 k_FPDRegisterListWithVPR,
663 k_VectorList,
664 k_VectorListAllLanes,
665 k_VectorListIndexed,
666 k_ShiftedRegister,
667 k_ShiftedImmediate,
668 k_ShifterImmediate,
669 k_RotateImmediate,
670 k_ModifiedImmediate,
671 k_ConstantPoolImmediate,
672 k_BitfieldDescriptor,
673 k_Token,
674 } Kind;
675
676 SMLoc StartLoc, EndLoc, AlignmentLoc;
677 SmallVector<unsigned, 8> Registers;

744 /// Combined record for all forms of ARM address expressions.
745 struct MemoryOp {
746 unsigned BaseRegNum;
747 // Offset is in OffsetReg or OffsetImm. If both are zero, no offset
748 // was specified.
749 const MCConstantExpr *OffsetImm; // Offset immediate value
750 unsigned OffsetRegNum; // Offset register num, when OffsetImm == NULL
751 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftType; // Shift type for OffsetReg
752 unsigned ShiftImm; // shift for OffsetReg.
753 unsigned Alignment; // 0 = no alignment specified
754 // n = alignment in bytes (2, 4, 8, 16, or 32)
755 unsigned isNegative : 1; // Negated OffsetReg? (~'U' bit)
756 };
757
758 struct PostIdxRegOp {
759 unsigned RegNum;
760 bool isAdd;
761 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy;
762 unsigned ShiftImm;
763 };

766 bool isASR;
767 unsigned Imm;
768 };
769
770 struct RegShiftedRegOp {
771 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy;
772 unsigned SrcReg;
773 unsigned ShiftReg;
774 unsigned ShiftImm;
775 };
776
777 struct RegShiftedImmOp {
778 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy;
779 unsigned SrcReg;
780 unsigned ShiftImm;
781 };

783 struct RotImmOp {
784 unsigned Imm;
785 };

788 unsigned Bits;
789 unsigned Rot;

793 unsigned LSB;
794 unsigned Width;
795 };

817 struct RegShiftedImmOp RegShiftedImm;
818 struct RotImmOp RotImm;

833 /// operand.

927 bool isARMBranchTarget() const {
928 if (!isImm()) return false;
929
930 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm()))
931 return CE->getValue() % 4 == 0;
932 return true;
933 }
934
935
936 bool isThumbBranchTarget() const {
937 if (!isImm()) return false;
938
939 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm()))
940 return CE->getValue() % 2 == 0;
941 return true;
942 }
943
944 // checks whether this operand is an unsigned offset which fits is a field
945 // of specified width and scaled by a specific number of bits
946 template<unsigned width, unsigned scale>
947 bool isUnsignedOffset() const {
948 if (!isImm()) return false;
949 if (isa<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Imm.Val)) return true;
950 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Imm.Val)) {
951 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
952 int64_t Align = 1LL << scale;
953 int64_t Max = Align * ((1LL << width) - 1);
954 return ((Val % Align) == 0) && (Val >= 0) && (Val <= Max);
955 }
956 return false;
957 }
958
959 // checks whether this operand is an signed offset which fits is a field
960 // of specified width and scaled by a specific number of bits
961 template<unsigned width, unsigned scale>
962 bool isSignedOffset() const {
963 if (!isImm()) return false;
964 if (isa<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Imm.Val)) return true;
965 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Imm.Val)) {
966 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
967 int64_t Align = 1LL << scale;
968 int64_t Max = Align * ((1LL << (width-1)) - 1);
969 int64_t Min = -Align * (1LL << (width-1));
970 return ((Val % Align) == 0) && (Val >= Min) && (Val <= Max);
971 }
972 return false;
973 }
974
975 // checks whether this operand is a memory operand computed as an offset
976 // applied to PC. the offset may have 8 bits of magnitude and is represented
977 // with two bits of shift. textually it may be either [pc, #imm], #imm or
978 // relocable expression...
979 bool isThumbMemPC() const {
980 int64_t Val = 0;
981 if (isImm()) {
982 if (isa<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Imm.Val)) return true;
983 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Imm.Val);
984 if (!CE) return false;
985 Val = CE->getValue();
986 }
987 else if (isMem()) {
988 if(!Memory.OffsetImm || Memory.OffsetRegNum) return false;
989 if(Memory.BaseRegNum != ARM::PC) return false;
990 Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
991 }
992 else return false;
993 return ((Val % 4) == 0) && (Val >= 0) && (Val <= 1020);
994 }
995
996 bool isFPImm() const {
997 if (!isImm()) return false;
998 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
999 if (!CE) return false;
1000 int Val = ARM_AM::getFP32Imm(APInt(32, CE->getValue()));
1001 return Val != -1;
1002 }
1003
1004 template<int64_t N, int64_t M>
1005 bool isImmediate() const {
1006 if (!isImm()) return false;
1007 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1008 if (!CE) return false;
1009 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1010 return Value >= N && Value <= M;
1011 }
1012
1013 template<int64_t N, int64_t M>
1014 bool isImmediateS4() const {
1015 if (!isImm()) return false;
1016 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1017 if (!CE) return false;
1018 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1019 return ((Value & 3) == 0) && Value >= N && Value <= M;
1020 }
1021
1022 bool isFBits16() const {
1023 return isImmediate<0, 17>();
1024 }
1025 bool isFBits32() const {
1026 return isImmediate<1, 33>();
1027 }
1028 bool isImm8s4() const {
1029 return isImmediateS4<-1020, 1020>();
1030 }
1031 bool isImm7s4() const {
1032 return isImmediateS4<-508, 508>();
1033 }
1034 bool isImm0_1020s4() const {
1035 return isImmediateS4<0, 1020>();
1036 }
1037 bool isImm0_508s4() const {
1038 return isImmediateS4<0, 508>();
1039 }
1040 bool isImm0_508s4Neg() const {
1041 if (!isImm()) return false;
1042 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1043 if (!CE) return false;
1044 int64_t Value = -CE->getValue();
1045 // explicitly exclude zero. we want that to use the normal 0_508 version.
1046 return ((Value & 3) == 0) && Value > 0 && Value <= 508;
1047 }
1048
1049 bool isImm0_4095Neg() const {
1050 if (!isImm()) return false;
1051 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1052 if (!CE) return false;
1053 // isImm0_4095Neg is used with 32-bit immediates only.
1054 // 32-bit immediates are zero extended to 64-bit when parsed,
1055 // thus simple -CE->getValue() results in a big negative number,
1056 // not a small positive number as intended
1057 if ((CE->getValue() >> 32) > 0) return false;
1058 uint32_t Value = -static_cast<uint32_t>(CE->getValue());
1059 return Value > 0 && Value < 4096;
1060 }
1061
1062 bool isImm0_7() const {
1063 return isImmediate<0, 7>();
1064 }
1065
1066 bool isImm1_16() const {
1067 return isImmediate<1, 16>();
1068 }
1069
1070 bool isImm1_32() const {
1071 return isImmediate<1, 32>();
1072 }
1073
1074 bool isImm8_255() const {
1075 return isImmediate<8, 255>();
1076 }
1077
1078 bool isImm256_65535Expr() const {
1079 if (!isImm()) return false;
1080 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1081 // If it's not a constant expression, it'll generate a fixup and be
1082 // handled later.
1083 if (!CE) return true;
1084 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1085 return Value >= 256 && Value < 65536;
1086 }
1087
1088 bool isImm0_65535Expr() const {
1089 if (!isImm()) return false;
1090 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1091 // If it's not a constant expression, it'll generate a fixup and be
1092 // handled later.
1093 if (!CE) return true;
1094 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1095 return Value >= 0 && Value < 65536;
1096 }
1097
1098 bool isImm24bit() const {
1099 return isImmediate<0, 0xffffff + 1>();
1100 }
1101
1102 bool isImmThumbSR() const {
1103 return isImmediate<1, 33>();
1104 }
1105
1106 bool isPKHLSLImm() const {
1107 return isImmediate<0, 32>();
1108 }
1109
1110 bool isPKHASRImm() const {
1111 return isImmediate<0, 33>();
1112 }
1113
1114 bool isAdrLabel() const {
1115 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
1116 // reference needing a fixup.
1117 if (isImm() && !isa<MCConstantExpr>(getImm()))
1118 return true;
1119
1120 // If it is a constant, it must fit into a modified immediate encoding.
1121 if (!isImm()) return false;
1122 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1123 if (!CE) return false;
1124 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1125 return (ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(Value) != -1 ||
1126 ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(-Value) != -1);
1127 }
1128
1129 bool isT2SOImm() const {
1130 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as an expression
1131 // needing a fixup.
1132 if (isImm() && !isa<MCConstantExpr>(getImm())) {
1133 // We want to avoid matching :upper16: and :lower16: as we want these
1134 // expressions to match in isImm0_65535Expr()
1135 const ARMMCExpr *ARM16Expr = dyn_cast<ARMMCExpr>(getImm());
1136 return (!ARM16Expr || (ARM16Expr->getKind() != ARMMCExpr::VK_ARM_HI16 &&
1137 ARM16Expr->getKind() != ARMMCExpr::VK_ARM_LO16));
1138 }
1139 if (!isImm()) return false;
1140 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1141 if (!CE) return false;
1142 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1143 return ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Value) != -1;
1144 }
1145
1146 bool isT2SOImmNot() const {
1147 if (!isImm()) return false;
1148 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1149 if (!CE) return false;
1150 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1151 return ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Value) == -1 &&
1152 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(~Value) != -1;
1153 }
1154
1155 bool isT2SOImmNeg() const {
1156 if (!isImm()) return false;
1157 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1158 if (!CE) return false;
1159 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1160 // Only use this when not representable as a plain so_imm.
1161 return ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Value) == -1 &&
1162 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(-Value) != -1;
1163 }
1164
1165 bool isSetEndImm() const {
1166 if (!isImm()) return false;
1167 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1168 if (!CE) return false;
1169 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1170 return Value == 1 || Value == 0;
1171 }

1173 bool isReg() const override { return Kind == k_Register; }
1174 bool isRegList() const { return Kind == k_RegisterList; }
1175 bool isRegListWithAPSR() const {
1176 return Kind == k_RegisterListWithAPSR || Kind == k_RegisterList;
1177 }
1178 bool isDPRRegList() const { return Kind == k_DPRRegisterList; }
1179 bool isSPRRegList() const { return Kind == k_SPRRegisterList; }
1180 bool isFPSRegListWithVPR() const { return Kind == k_FPSRegisterListWithVPR; }
1181 bool isFPDRegListWithVPR() const { return Kind == k_FPDRegisterListWithVPR; }
1182 bool isToken() const override { return Kind == k_Token; }
1183 bool isMemBarrierOpt() const { return Kind == k_MemBarrierOpt; }
1184 bool isInstSyncBarrierOpt() const { return Kind == k_InstSyncBarrierOpt; }
1185 bool isTraceSyncBarrierOpt() const { return Kind == k_TraceSyncBarrierOpt; }
1186 bool isMem() const override {
1187 if (Kind != k_Memory)
1188 return false;
1189 if (Memory.BaseRegNum &&
1190 !ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(Memory.BaseRegNum))
1191 return false;
1192 if (Memory.OffsetRegNum &&
1193 !ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(Memory.OffsetRegNum))
1194 return false;
1195 return true;
1196 }
1197 bool isShifterImm() const { return Kind == k_ShifterImmediate; }
1198 bool isRegShiftedReg() const {
1199 return Kind == k_ShiftedRegister &&
1200 ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(
1201 RegShiftedReg.SrcReg) &&
1202 ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(
1203 RegShiftedReg.ShiftReg);
1204 }
1205 bool isRegShiftedImm() const {
1206 return Kind == k_ShiftedImmediate &&
1207 ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(
1208 RegShiftedImm.SrcReg);
1209 }
1210 bool isRotImm() const { return Kind == k_RotateImmediate; }
1211 bool isModImm() const { return Kind == k_ModifiedImmediate; }
1212
1213 bool isModImmNot() const {
1214 if (!isImm()) return false;
1215 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1216 if (!CE) return false;
1217 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1218 return ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(~Value) != -1;
1219 }
1220
1221 bool isModImmNeg() const {
1222 if (!isImm()) return false;
1223 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1224 if (!CE) return false;
1225 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1226 return ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(Value) == -1 &&
1227 ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(-Value) != -1;
1228 }
1229
1230 bool isThumbModImmNeg1_7() const {
1231 if (!isImm()) return false;
1232 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1233 if (!CE) return false;
1234 int32_t Value = -(int32_t)CE->getValue();
1235 return 0 < Value && Value < 8;
1236 }
1237
1238 bool isThumbModImmNeg8_255() const {
1239 if (!isImm()) return false;
1240 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1241 if (!CE) return false;
1242 int32_t Value = -(int32_t)CE->getValue();
1243 return 7 < Value && Value < 256;
1244 }
1245
1246 bool isConstantPoolImm() const { return Kind == k_ConstantPoolImmediate; }
1247 bool isBitfield() const { return Kind == k_BitfieldDescriptor; }
1248 bool isPostIdxRegShifted() const {
1249 return Kind == k_PostIndexRegister &&
1250 ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(PostIdxReg.RegNum);
1251 }
1252 bool isPostIdxReg() const {
1253 return isPostIdxRegShifted() && PostIdxReg.ShiftTy == ARM_AM::no_shift;
1254 }
1255 bool isMemNoOffset(bool alignOK = false, unsigned Alignment = 0) const {
1256 if (!isMem())
1257 return false;
1258 // No offset of any kind.
1259 return Memory.OffsetRegNum == 0 && Memory.OffsetImm == nullptr &&
1260 (alignOK || Memory.Alignment == Alignment);
1261 }
1262 bool isMemNoOffsetT2(bool alignOK = false, unsigned Alignment = 0) const {
1263 if (!isMem())
1264 return false;
1265
1266 if (!ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRnopcRegClassID].contains(
1267 Memory.BaseRegNum))
1268 return false;
1269
1270 // No offset of any kind.
1271 return Memory.OffsetRegNum == 0 && Memory.OffsetImm == nullptr &&
1272 (alignOK || Memory.Alignment == Alignment);
1273 }
1274 bool isMemNoOffsetT2NoSp(bool alignOK = false, unsigned Alignment = 0) const {
1275 if (!isMem())
1276 return false;
1277
1278 if (!ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::rGPRRegClassID].contains(
1279 Memory.BaseRegNum))
1280 return false;
1281
1282 // No offset of any kind.
1283 return Memory.OffsetRegNum == 0 && Memory.OffsetImm == nullptr &&
1284 (alignOK || Memory.Alignment == Alignment);
1285 }
1286 bool isMemPCRelImm12() const {
1287 if (!isMem() || Memory.OffsetRegNum != 0 || Memory.Alignment != 0)
1288 return false;
1289 // Base register must be PC.
1290 if (Memory.BaseRegNum != ARM::PC)
1291 return false;
1292 // Immediate offset in range [-4095, 4095].
1293 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;
1294 int64_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
1295 return (Val > -4096 && Val < 4096) ||
1296 (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
1297 }
1298
1299 bool isAlignedMemory() const {
1300 return isMemNoOffset(true);
1301 }
1302
1303 bool isAlignedMemoryNone() const {
1304 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1305 }
1306
1307 bool isDupAlignedMemoryNone() const {
1308 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1309 }
1310
1311 bool isAlignedMemory16() const {
1312 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 2)) // alignment in bytes for 16-bits is 2.
1313 return true;
1314 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1315 }
1316
1317 bool isDupAlignedMemory16() const {
1318 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 2)) // alignment in bytes for 16-bits is 2.
1319 return true;
1320 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1321 }
1322
1323 bool isAlignedMemory32() const {
1324 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 4)) // alignment in bytes for 32-bits is 4.
1325 return true;
1326 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1327 }
1328
1329 bool isDupAlignedMemory32() const {
1330 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 4)) // alignment in bytes for 32-bits is 4.
1331 return true;
1332 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1333 }
1334
1335 bool isAlignedMemory64() const {
1336 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 8)) // alignment in bytes for 64-bits is 8.
1337 return true;
1338 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1339 }
1340
1341 bool isDupAlignedMemory64() const {
1342 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 8)) // alignment in bytes for 64-bits is 8.
1343 return true;
1344 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1345 }
1346
1347 bool isAlignedMemory64or128() const {
1348 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 8)) // alignment in bytes for 64-bits is 8.
1349 return true;
1350 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 16)) // alignment in bytes for 128-bits is 16.
1351 return true;
1352 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1353 }
1354
1355 bool isDupAlignedMemory64or128() const {
1356 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 8)) // alignment in bytes for 64-bits is 8.
1357 return true;
1358 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 16)) // alignment in bytes for 128-bits is 16.
1359 return true;
1360 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1361 }
1362
1363 bool isAlignedMemory64or128or256() const {
1364 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 8)) // alignment in bytes for 64-bits is 8.
1365 return true;
1366 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 16)) // alignment in bytes for 128-bits is 16.
1367 return true;
1368 if (isMemNoOffset(false, 32)) // alignment in bytes for 256-bits is 32.
1369 return true;
1370 return isMemNoOffset(false, 0);
1371 }
1372
1373 bool isAddrMode2() const {
1374 if (!isMem() || Memory.Alignment != 0) return false;
1375 // Check for register offset.
1376 if (Memory.OffsetRegNum) return true;
1377 // Immediate offset in range [-4095, 4095].
1378 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;
1379 int64_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
1380 return Val > -4096 && Val < 4096;
1381 }
1382
1383 bool isAM2OffsetImm() const {
1384 if (!isImm()) return false;
1385 // Immediate offset in range [-4095, 4095].
1386 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1387 if (!CE) return false;
1388 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
1389 return (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) ||
1390 (Val > -4096 && Val < 4096);
1391 }
1392
1393 bool isAddrMode3() const {
1394 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
1395 // reference needing a fixup. If it is a constant, it's something else
1396 // and we reject it.
1397 if (isImm() && !isa<MCConstantExpr>(getImm()))
1398 return true;
1399 if (!isMem() || Memory.Alignment != 0) return false;
1400 // No shifts are legal for AM3.
1401 if (Memory.ShiftType != ARM_AM::no_shift) return false;
1402 // Check for register offset.
1403 if (Memory.OffsetRegNum) return true;
1404 // Immediate offset in range [-255, 255].
1405 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;
1406 int64_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
1407 // The #-0 offset is encoded as std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min(), and we
1408 // have to check for this too.
1409 return (Val > -256 && Val < 256) ||
1410 Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
1411 }
1412
1413 bool isAM3Offset() const {
1414 if (isPostIdxReg())
1415 return true;
1416 if (!isImm())
1417 return false;
1418 // Immediate offset in range [-255, 255].
1419 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1420 if (!CE) return false;
1421 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
1422 // Special case, #-0 is std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min().
1423 return (Val > -256 && Val < 256) ||
1424 Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
1425 }
1426
1427 bool isAddrMode5() const {
1428 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
1429 // reference needing a fixup. If it is a constant, it's something else
1430 // and we reject it.
1431 if (isImm() && !isa<MCConstantExpr>(getImm()))
1432 return true;
1433 if (!isMem() || Memory.Alignment != 0) return false;
1434 // Check for register offset.
1435 if (Memory.OffsetRegNum) return false;
1436 // Immediate offset in range [-1020, 1020] and a multiple of 4.
1437 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;
1438 int64_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
1439 return (Val >= -1020 && Val <= 1020 && ((Val & 3) == 0)) ||
1440 Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
1441 }
1442
1443 bool isAddrMode5FP16() const {
1444 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
1445 // reference needing a fixup. If it is a constant, it's something else
1446 // and we reject it.
1447 if (isImm() && !isa<MCConstantExpr>(getImm()))
1448 return true;
1449 if (!isMem() || Memory.Alignment != 0) return false;
1450 // Check for register offset.
1451 if (Memory.OffsetRegNum) return false;
1452 // Immediate offset in range [-510, 510] and a multiple of 2.
1453 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;
1454 int64_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
1455 return (Val >= -510 && Val <= 510 && ((Val & 1) == 0)) ||
1456 Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
1457 }

1461 Memory.ShiftType != ARM_AM::no_shift || Memory.Alignment != 0)
1462 return false;
1463 return true;

1469 Memory.Alignment != 0 )
1470 return false;
1471 return true;
1472 }

1476 return false;
1477 return true;
1478 }
1479
1480 bool isT2MemRegOffset() const {
1481 if (!isMem() || !Memory.OffsetRegNum || Memory.isNegative ||
1482 Memory.Alignment != 0 || Memory.BaseRegNum == ARM::PC)
1483 return false;
1484 // Only lsl #{0, 1, 2, 3} allowed.
1485 if (Memory.ShiftType == ARM_AM::no_shift)
1486 return true;
1487 if (Memory.ShiftType != ARM_AM::lsl || Memory.ShiftImm > 3)
1488 return false;
1489 return true;
1490 }

1492 bool isMemThumbRR() const {
1493 // Thumb reg+reg addressing is simple. Just two registers, a base and
1494 // an offset. No shifts, negations or any other complicating factors.
1495 if (!isMem() || !Memory.OffsetRegNum || Memory.isNegative ||
1496 Memory.ShiftType != ARM_AM::no_shift || Memory.Alignment != 0)
1497 return false;
1498 return isARMLowRegister(Memory.BaseRegNum) &&
1499 (!Memory.OffsetRegNum || isARMLowRegister(Memory.OffsetRegNum));
1500 }

1502 bool isMemThumbRIs4() const {
1503 if (!isMem() || Memory.OffsetRegNum != 0 ||
1504 !isARMLowRegister(Memory.BaseRegNum) || Memory.Alignment != 0)
1505 return false;
1506 // Immediate offset, multiple of 4 in range [0, 124].
1507 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;
1508 int64_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm->getValue();
1509 return Val >= 0 && Val <= 124 && (Val % 4) == 0;
1510 }

1514 !isARMLowRegister(Memory.BaseRegNum) || Memory.Alignment != 0)
1515 return false;
1516 // Immediate offset, multiple of 4 in range [0, 62].
1517 if (!Memory.OffsetImm) return true;

1520 }

1877 bool isNEONi8splat() const {
1878 if (!isImm()) return false;
1879 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1880 // Must be a constant.
1881 if (!CE) return false;
1882 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1883 // i8 value splatted across 8 bytes. The immediate is just the 8 byte
1884 // value.
1885 return Value >= 0 && Value < 256;
1886 }
1887
1888 bool isNEONi16splat() const {
1889 if (isNEONByteReplicate(2))
1890 return false; // Leave that for bytes replication and forbid by default.
1891 if (!isImm())
1892 return false;
1893 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1894 // Must be a constant.
1895 if (!CE) return false;
1896 unsigned Value = CE->getValue();
1897 return ARM_AM::isNEONi16splat(Value);
1898 }
1899
1900 bool isNEONi16splatNot() const {
1901 if (!isImm())
1902 return false;
1903 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1904 // Must be a constant.
1905 if (!CE) return false;
1906 unsigned Value = CE->getValue();
1907 return ARM_AM::isNEONi16splat(~Value & 0xffff);
1908 }
1909
1910 bool isNEONi32splat() const {
1911 if (isNEONByteReplicate(4))
1912 return false; // Leave that for bytes replication and forbid by default.
1913 if (!isImm())
1914 return false;
1915 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1916 // Must be a constant.
1917 if (!CE) return false;
1918 unsigned Value = CE->getValue();
1919 return ARM_AM::isNEONi32splat(Value);
1920 }
1921
1922 bool isNEONi32splatNot() const {
1923 if (!isImm())
1924 return false;
1925 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1926 // Must be a constant.
1927 if (!CE) return false;
1928 unsigned Value = CE->getValue();
1929 return ARM_AM::isNEONi32splat(~Value);
1930 }
1931
1932 static bool isValidNEONi32vmovImm(int64_t Value) {
1933 // i32 value with set bits only in one byte X000, 0X00, 00X0, or 000X,
1934 // for VMOV/VMVN only, 00Xf or 0Xff are also accepted.
1935 return ((Value & 0xffffffffffffff00) == 0) ||
1936 ((Value & 0xffffffffffff00ff) == 0) ||
1937 ((Value & 0xffffffffff00ffff) == 0) ||
1938 ((Value & 0xffffffff00ffffff) == 0) ||
1939 ((Value & 0xffffffffffff00ff) == 0xff) ||
1940 ((Value & 0xffffffffff00ffff) == 0xffff);
1941 }
1942
1943 bool isNEONReplicate(unsigned Width, unsigned NumElems, bool Inv) const {
1944 assert((Width == 8 || Width == 16 || Width == 32) &&
1945 "Invalid element width");
1946 assert(NumElems * Width <= 64 && "Invalid result width");
1947
1948 if (!isImm())
1949 return false;
1950 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
1951 // Must be a constant.
1952 if (!CE)
1953 return false;
1954 int64_t Value = CE->getValue();
1955 if (!Value)
1956 return false; // Don't bother with zero.
1957 if (Inv)
1958 Value = ~Value;
1959
1960 uint64_t Mask = (1ull << Width) - 1;
1961 uint64_t Elem = Value & Mask;
1962 if (Width == 16 && (Elem & 0x00ff) != 0 && (Elem & 0xff00) != 0)
1963 return false;
1964 if (Width == 32 && !isValidNEONi32vmovImm(Elem))
1965 return false;
1966
1967 for (unsigned i = 1; i < NumElems; ++i) {
1968 Value >>= Width;
1969 if ((Value & Mask) != Elem)
1970 return false;
1971 }
1972 return true;
1973 }
1974
1975 bool isNEONByteReplicate(unsigned NumBytes) const {
1976 return isNEONReplicate(8, NumBytes, false);
1977 }
1978
1979 static void checkNeonReplicateArgs(unsigned FromW, unsigned ToW) {
1980 assert((FromW == 8 || FromW == 16 || FromW == 32) &&
1981 "Invalid source width");
1982 assert((ToW == 16 || ToW == 32 || ToW == 64) &&
1983 "Invalid destination width");
1984 assert(FromW < ToW && "ToW is not less than FromW");
1985 }
1986
1987 template<unsigned FromW, unsigned ToW>
1988 bool isNEONmovReplicate() const {
1989 checkNeonReplicateArgs(FromW, ToW);
1990 if (ToW == 64 && isNEONi64splat())
1991 return false;
1992 return isNEONReplicate(FromW, ToW / FromW, false);
1993 }
1994
1995 template<unsigned FromW, unsigned ToW>
1996 bool isNEONinvReplicate() const {
1997 checkNeonReplicateArgs(FromW, ToW);
1998 return isNEONReplicate(FromW, ToW / FromW, true);
1999 }
2000
2001 bool isNEONi32vmov() const {
2002 if (isNEONByteReplicate(4))
2003 return false; // Let it to be classified as byte-replicate case.
2004 if (!isImm())
2005 return false;
2006 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2007 // Must be a constant.
2008 if (!CE)
2009 return false;
2010 return isValidNEONi32vmovImm(CE->getValue());
2011 }
2012
2013 bool isNEONi32vmovNeg() const {
2014 if (!isImm()) return false;
2015 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2016 // Must be a constant.
2017 if (!CE) return false;
2018 return isValidNEONi32vmovImm(~CE->getValue());
2019 }
2020
2021 bool isNEONi64splat() const {
2022 if (!isImm()) return false;
2023 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2024 // Must be a constant.
2025 if (!CE) return false;
2026 uint64_t Value = CE->getValue();
2027 // i64 value with each byte being either 0 or 0xff.
2028 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 8; ++i, Value >>= 8)
2029 if ((Value & 0xff) != 0 && (Value & 0xff) != 0xff) return false;
2030 return true;
2031 }
2032
2033 template<int64_t Angle, int64_t Remainder>
2034 bool isComplexRotation() const {
2035 if (!isImm()) return false;
2036
2037 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2038 if (!CE) return false;
2039 uint64_t Value = CE->getValue();
2040
2041 return (Value % Angle == Remainder && Value <= 270);
2042 }
2043
2044 bool isMVELongShift() const {
2045 if (!isImm()) return false;
2046 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2047 // Must be a constant.
2048 if (!CE) return false;
2049 uint64_t Value = CE->getValue();
2050 return Value >= 1 && Value <= 32;
2051 }
2052
2053 bool isITCondCodeNoAL() const {
2054 if (!isITCondCode()) return false;
2055 auto CC = (ARMCC::CondCodes) getCondCode();
2056 return CC != ARMCC::AL;
2057 }
2058
2059 void addExpr(MCInst &Inst, const MCExpr *Expr) const {
2060 // Add as immediates when possible. Null MCExpr = 0.
2061 if (!Expr)
2062 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
2063 else if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr))
2064 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(CE->getValue()));
2065 else
2066 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr));
2067 }

2228
2229 void addBitfieldOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2230 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2231 // Munge the lsb/width into a bitfield mask.
2232 unsigned lsb = Bitfield.LSB;
2233 unsigned width = Bitfield.Width;
2234 // Make a 32-bit mask w/ the referenced bits clear and all other bits set.
2235 uint32_t Mask = ~(((uint32_t)0xffffffff >> lsb) << (32 - width) >>
2236 (32 - (lsb + width)));
2237 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Mask));
2238 }

2490
2491 void addAddrMode2Operands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2492 assert(N == 3 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2493 int32_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm ? Memory.OffsetImm->getValue() : 0;
2494 if (!Memory.OffsetRegNum) {
2495 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Val < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add;
2496 // Special case for #-0
2497 if (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Val = 0;
2498 if (Val < 0) Val = -Val;
2499 Val = ARM_AM::getAM2Opc(AddSub, Val, ARM_AM::no_shift);
2500 } else {
2501 // For register offset, we encode the shift type and negation flag
2502 // here.
2503 Val = ARM_AM::getAM2Opc(Memory.isNegative ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add,
2504 Memory.ShiftImm, Memory.ShiftType);
2505 }
2506 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Memory.BaseRegNum));
2507 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Memory.OffsetRegNum));
2508 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2509 }
2510
2511 void addAM2OffsetImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2512 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2513 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2514 assert(CE && "non-constant AM2OffsetImm operand!");
2515 int32_t Val = CE->getValue();
2516 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Val < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add;
2517 // Special case for #-0
2518 if (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Val = 0;
2519 if (Val < 0) Val = -Val;
2520 Val = ARM_AM::getAM2Opc(AddSub, Val, ARM_AM::no_shift);
2521 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0));
2522 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2523 }
2524
2525 void addAddrMode3Operands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2526 assert(N == 3 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2527 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
2528 // reference needing a fixup. If it is a constant, it's something else
2529 // and we reject it.
2530 if (isImm()) {
2531 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getImm()));
2532 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0));
2533 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
2534 return;
2535 }
2536
2537 int32_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm ? Memory.OffsetImm->getValue() : 0;
2538 if (!Memory.OffsetRegNum) {
2539 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Val < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add;
2540 // Special case for #-0
2541 if (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Val = 0;
2542 if (Val < 0) Val = -Val;
2543 Val = ARM_AM::getAM3Opc(AddSub, Val);
2544 } else {
2545 // For register offset, we encode the shift type and negation flag
2546 // here.
2547 Val = ARM_AM::getAM3Opc(Memory.isNegative ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add, 0);
2548 }
2549 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Memory.BaseRegNum));
2550 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Memory.OffsetRegNum));
2551 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2552 }
2553
2554 void addAM3OffsetOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2555 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2556 if (Kind == k_PostIndexRegister) {
2557 int32_t Val =
2558 ARM_AM::getAM3Opc(PostIdxReg.isAdd ? ARM_AM::add : ARM_AM::sub, 0);
2559 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(PostIdxReg.RegNum));
2560 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2561 return;
2562 }
2563
2564 // Constant offset.
2565 const MCConstantExpr *CE = static_cast<const MCConstantExpr*>(getImm());
2566 int32_t Val = CE->getValue();
2567 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Val < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add;
2568 // Special case for #-0
2569 if (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Val = 0;
2570 if (Val < 0) Val = -Val;
2571 Val = ARM_AM::getAM3Opc(AddSub, Val);
2572 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0));
2573 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2574 }
2575
2576 void addAddrMode5Operands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2577 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2578 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
2579 // reference needing a fixup. If it is a constant, it's something else
2580 // and we reject it.
2581 if (isImm()) {
2582 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getImm()));
2583 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
2584 return;
2585 }
2586
2587 // The lower two bits are always zero and as such are not encoded.
2588 int32_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm ? Memory.OffsetImm->getValue() / 4 : 0;
2589 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Val < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add;
2590 // Special case for #-0
2591 if (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Val = 0;
2592 if (Val < 0) Val = -Val;
2593 Val = ARM_AM::getAM5Opc(AddSub, Val);
2594 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Memory.BaseRegNum));
2595 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2596 }
2597
2598 void addAddrMode5FP16Operands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2599 assert(N == 2 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2600 // If we have an immediate that's not a constant, treat it as a label
2601 // reference needing a fixup. If it is a constant, it's something else
2602 // and we reject it.
2603 if (isImm()) {
2604 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(getImm()));
2605 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
2606 return;
2607 }
2608
2609 // The lower bit is always zero and as such is not encoded.
2610 int32_t Val = Memory.OffsetImm ? Memory.OffsetImm->getValue() / 2 : 0;
2611 ARM_AM::AddrOpc AddSub = Val < 0 ? ARM_AM::sub : ARM_AM::add;
2612 // Special case for #-0
2613 if (Val == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Val = 0;
2614 if (Val < 0) Val = -Val;
2615 Val = ARM_AM::getAM5FP16Opc(AddSub, Val);
2616 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Memory.BaseRegNum));
2617 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2618 }

2775
2776 void addPostIdxImm8Operands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2777 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2778 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2779 assert(CE && "non-constant post-idx-imm8 operand!");
2780 int Imm = CE->getValue();
2781 bool isAdd = Imm >= 0;
2782 if (Imm == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Imm = 0;
2783 Imm = (Imm < 0 ? -Imm : Imm) | (int)isAdd << 8;
2784 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
2785 }
2786
2787 void addPostIdxImm8s4Operands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2788 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2789 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2790 assert(CE && "non-constant post-idx-imm8s4 operand!");
2791 int Imm = CE->getValue();
2792 bool isAdd = Imm >= 0;
2793 if (Imm == std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min()) Imm = 0;
2794 // Immediate is scaled by 4.
2795 Imm = ((Imm < 0 ? -Imm : Imm) / 4) | (int)isAdd << 8;
2796 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
2797 }

2807 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(PostIdxReg.RegNum));
2808 // The sign, shift type, and shift amount are encoded in a single operand
2809 // using the AM2 encoding helpers.
2810 ARM_AM::AddrOpc opc = PostIdxReg.isAdd ? ARM_AM::add : ARM_AM::sub;
2811 unsigned Imm = ARM_AM::getAM2Opc(opc, PostIdxReg.ShiftImm,
2812 PostIdxReg.ShiftTy);
2813 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm));
2814 }

2905
2906 void addNEONi8ReplicateOperands(MCInst &Inst, bool Inv) const {
2907 // The immediate encodes the type of constant as well as the value.
2908 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2909 assert((Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVv8i8 ||
2910 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVv16i8) &&
2911 "All instructions that wants to replicate non-zero byte "
2912 "always must be replaced with VMOVv8i8 or VMOVv16i8.");
2913 unsigned Value = CE->getValue();
2914 if (Inv)
2915 Value = ~Value;
2916 unsigned B = Value & 0xff;
2917 B |= 0xe00; // cmode = 0b1110
2918 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(B));
2919 }
2920
2921 void addNEONinvi8ReplicateOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2922 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2923 addNEONi8ReplicateOperands(Inst, true);
2924 }
2925
2926 static unsigned encodeNeonVMOVImmediate(unsigned Value) {
2927 if (Value >= 256 && Value <= 0xffff)
2928 Value = (Value >> 8) | ((Value & 0xff) ? 0xc00 : 0x200);
2929 else if (Value > 0xffff && Value <= 0xffffff)
2930 Value = (Value >> 16) | ((Value & 0xff) ? 0xd00 : 0x400);
2931 else if (Value > 0xffffff)
2932 Value = (Value >> 24) | 0x600;
2933 return Value;
2934 }
2935
2936 void addNEONi32vmovOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2937 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2938 // The immediate encodes the type of constant as well as the value.
2939 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2940 unsigned Value = encodeNeonVMOVImmediate(CE->getValue());
2941 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Value));
2942 }
2943
2944 void addNEONvmovi8ReplicateOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2945 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2946 addNEONi8ReplicateOperands(Inst, false);
2947 }
2948
2949 void addNEONvmovi16ReplicateOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2950 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2951 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2952 assert((Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVv4i16 ||
2953 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVv8i16 ||
2954 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMVNv4i16 ||
2955 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMVNv8i16) &&
2956 "All instructions that want to replicate non-zero half-word "
2957 "always must be replaced with V{MOV,MVN}v{4,8}i16.");
2958 uint64_t Value = CE->getValue();
2959 unsigned Elem = Value & 0xffff;
2960 if (Elem >= 256)
2961 Elem = (Elem >> 8) | 0x200;
2962 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Elem));
2963 }
2964
2965 void addNEONi32vmovNegOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2966 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2967 // The immediate encodes the type of constant as well as the value.
2968 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2969 unsigned Value = encodeNeonVMOVImmediate(~CE->getValue());
2970 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Value));
2971 }
2972
2973 void addNEONvmovi32ReplicateOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2974 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2975 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2976 assert((Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVv2i32 ||
2977 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMOVv4i32 ||
2978 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMVNv2i32 ||
2979 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::VMVNv4i32) &&
2980 "All instructions that want to replicate non-zero word "
2981 "always must be replaced with V{MOV,MVN}v{2,4}i32.");
2982 uint64_t Value = CE->getValue();
2983 unsigned Elem = encodeNeonVMOVImmediate(Value & 0xffffffff);
2984 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Elem));
2985 }
2986
2987 void addNEONi64splatOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2988 assert(N == 1 && "Invalid number of operands!");
2989 // The immediate encodes the type of constant as well as the value.
2990 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(getImm());
2991 uint64_t Value = CE->getValue();
2992 unsigned Imm = 0;
2993 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 8; ++i, Value >>= 8) {
2994 Imm |= (Value & 1) << i;
2995 }
2996 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm | 0x1e00));
2997 }

3062
3063 static std::unique_ptr<ARMOperand> CreateToken(StringRef Str, SMLoc S) {
3064 auto Op = make_unique<ARMOperand>(k_Token);

3154
3155 static std::unique_ptr<ARMOperand>
3156 CreateRegList(SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>> &Regs,
3157 SMLoc StartLoc, SMLoc EndLoc) {
3158 assert(Regs.size() > 0 && "RegList contains no registers?");
3159 KindTy Kind = k_RegisterList;
3160
3161 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPRRegClassID].contains(
3162 Regs.front().second)) {
3163 if (Regs.back().second == ARM::VPR)
3164 Kind = k_FPDRegisterListWithVPR;
3165 else
3166 Kind = k_DPRRegisterList;
3167 } else if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::SPRRegClassID].contains(
3168 Regs.front().second)) {
3169 if (Regs.back().second == ARM::VPR)
3170 Kind = k_FPSRegisterListWithVPR;
3171 else
3172 Kind = k_SPRRegisterList;
3173 }
3174
3175 // Sort based on the register encoding values.
3176 array_pod_sort(Regs.begin(), Regs.end());
3177
3178 if (Kind == k_RegisterList && Regs.back().second == ARM::APSR)
3179 Kind = k_RegisterListWithAPSR;
3180
3181 auto Op = make_unique<ARMOperand>(Kind);
3182 for (SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>>::const_iterator
3183 I = Regs.begin(), E = Regs.end(); I != E; ++I)
3184 Op->Registers.push_back(I->second);
3185
3186 Op->StartLoc = StartLoc;
3187 Op->EndLoc = EndLoc;
3188 return Op;
3189 }
