3333
3334void ARMOperand::print(raw_ostream &OS) const {
3335 auto RegName = [](unsigned Reg) {
3336 if (Reg)
3337 return ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg);
3338 else
3339 return "noreg";
3340 };
3341
3342 switch (Kind) {
3343 case k_CondCode:
3344 OS << "<ARMCC::" << ARMCondCodeToString(getCondCode()) << ">";
3345 break;
3346 case k_CCOut:
3347 OS << "<ccout " << RegName(getReg()) << ">";
3348 break;
3349 case k_ITCondMask: {
3350 static const char *const MaskStr[] = {
3351 "(invalid)", "(tttt)", "(ttt)", "(ttte)",
3352 "(tt)", "(ttet)", "(tte)", "(ttee)",
3353 "(t)", "(tett)", "(tet)", "(tete)",
3354 "(te)", "(teet)", "(tee)", "(teee)",
3355 };
3356 assert((ITMask.Mask & 0xf) == ITMask.Mask);
3357 OS << "<it-mask " << MaskStr[ITMask.Mask] << ">";
3358 break;
3359 }
3360 case k_CoprocNum:
3361 OS << "<coprocessor number: " << getCoproc() << ">";
3362 break;
3363 case k_CoprocReg:
3364 OS << "<coprocessor register: " << getCoproc() << ">";
3365 break;
3366 case k_CoprocOption:
3367 OS << "<coprocessor option: " << CoprocOption.Val << ">";
3368 break;
3369 case k_MSRMask:
3370 OS << "<mask: " << getMSRMask() << ">";
3371 break;
3372 case k_BankedReg:
3373 OS << "<banked reg: " << getBankedReg() << ">";
3374 break;
3375 case k_Immediate:
3376 OS << *getImm();
3377 break;
3378 case k_MemBarrierOpt:
3379 OS << "<ARM_MB::" << MemBOptToString(getMemBarrierOpt(), false) << ">";
3380 break;
3381 case k_InstSyncBarrierOpt:
3382 OS << "<ARM_ISB::" << InstSyncBOptToString(getInstSyncBarrierOpt()) << ">";
3383 break;
3384 case k_TraceSyncBarrierOpt:
3385 OS << "<ARM_TSB::" << TraceSyncBOptToString(getTraceSyncBarrierOpt()) << ">";
3386 break;
3387 case k_Memory:
3388 OS << "<memory";
3389 if (Memory.BaseRegNum)
3390 OS << " base:" << RegName(Memory.BaseRegNum);
3391 if (Memory.OffsetImm)
3392 OS << " offset-imm:" << *Memory.OffsetImm;
3393 if (Memory.OffsetRegNum)
3394 OS << " offset-reg:" << (Memory.isNegative ? "-" : "")
3395 << RegName(Memory.OffsetRegNum);
3396 if (Memory.ShiftType != ARM_AM::no_shift) {
3397 OS << " shift-type:" << ARM_AM::getShiftOpcStr(Memory.ShiftType);
3398 OS << " shift-imm:" << Memory.ShiftImm;
3399 }
3400 if (Memory.Alignment)
3401 OS << " alignment:" << Memory.Alignment;
3402 OS << ">";
3403 break;
3404 case k_PostIndexRegister:
3405 OS << "post-idx register " << (PostIdxReg.isAdd ? "" : "-")
3406 << RegName(PostIdxReg.RegNum);
3407 if (PostIdxReg.ShiftTy != ARM_AM::no_shift)
3408 OS << ARM_AM::getShiftOpcStr(PostIdxReg.ShiftTy) << " "
3409 << PostIdxReg.ShiftImm;
3410 OS << ">";
3411 break;
3412 case k_ProcIFlags: {
3413 OS << "<ARM_PROC::";
3414 unsigned IFlags = getProcIFlags();
3415 for (int i=2; i >= 0; --i)
3416 if (IFlags & (1 << i))
3417 OS << ARM_PROC::IFlagsToString(1 << i);
3418 OS << ">";
3419 break;
3420 }
3421 case k_Register:
3422 OS << "<register " << RegName(getReg()) << ">";
3423 break;
3424 case k_ShifterImmediate:
3425 OS << "<shift " << (ShifterImm.isASR ? "asr" : "lsl")
3426 << " #" << ShifterImm.Imm << ">";
3427 break;
3428 case k_ShiftedRegister:
3429 OS << "<so_reg_reg " << RegName(RegShiftedReg.SrcReg) << " "
3430 << ARM_AM::getShiftOpcStr(RegShiftedReg.ShiftTy) << " "
3431 << RegName(RegShiftedReg.ShiftReg) << ">";
3432 break;
3433 case k_ShiftedImmediate:
3434 OS << "<so_reg_imm " << RegName(RegShiftedImm.SrcReg) << " "
3435 << ARM_AM::getShiftOpcStr(RegShiftedImm.ShiftTy) << " #"
3436 << RegShiftedImm.ShiftImm << ">";
3437 break;
3438 case k_RotateImmediate:
3439 OS << "<ror " << " #" << (RotImm.Imm * 8) << ">";
3440 break;
3441 case k_ModifiedImmediate:
3442 OS << "<mod_imm #" << ModImm.Bits << ", #"
3443 << ModImm.Rot << ")>";
3444 break;
3445 case k_ConstantPoolImmediate:
3446 OS << "<constant_pool_imm #" << *getConstantPoolImm();
3447 break;
3448 case k_BitfieldDescriptor:
3449 OS << "<bitfield " << "lsb: " << Bitfield.LSB
3450 << ", width: " << Bitfield.Width << ">";
3451 break;
3452 case k_RegisterList:
3453 case k_RegisterListWithAPSR:
3454 case k_DPRRegisterList:
3455 case k_SPRRegisterList:
3456 case k_FPSRegisterListWithVPR:
3457 case k_FPDRegisterListWithVPR: {
3458 OS << "<register_list ";
3459
3460 const SmallVectorImpl<unsigned> &RegList = getRegList();
3461 for (SmallVectorImpl<unsigned>::const_iterator
3462 I = RegList.begin(), E = RegList.end(); I != E; ) {
3463 OS << RegName(*I);
3464 if (++I < E) OS << ", ";
3465 }
3466
3467 OS << ">";
3468 break;
3469 }
3470 case k_VectorList:
3471 OS << "<vector_list " << VectorList.Count << " * "
3472 << RegName(VectorList.RegNum) << ">";
3473 break;
3474 case k_VectorListAllLanes:
3475 OS << "<vector_list(all lanes) " << VectorList.Count << " * "
3476 << RegName(VectorList.RegNum) << ">";
3477 break;
3478 case k_VectorListIndexed:
3479 OS << "<vector_list(lane " << VectorList.LaneIndex << ") "
3480 << VectorList.Count << " * " << RegName(VectorList.RegNum) << ">";
3481 break;
3482 case k_Token:
3483 OS << "'" << getToken() << "'";
3484 break;
3485 case k_VectorIndex:
3486 OS << "<vectorindex " << getVectorIndex() << ">";
3487 break;
3488 }
3489}
3490
3491/// @name Auto-generated Match Functions
3492/// {
3493
3494static unsigned MatchRegisterName(StringRef Name);
3495
3496/// }
3497
3498bool ARMAsmParser::ParseRegister(unsigned &RegNo,
3499 SMLoc &StartLoc, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
3500 const AsmToken &Tok = getParser().getTok();
3501 StartLoc = Tok.getLoc();
3502 EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc();
3503 RegNo = tryParseRegister();
3504
3505 return (RegNo == (unsigned)-1);
3506}
3507
3508/// Try to parse a register name. The token must be an Identifier when called,
3509/// and if it is a register name the token is eaten and the register number is
3510/// returned. Otherwise return -1.
3511int ARMAsmParser::tryParseRegister() {
3512 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3513 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
3514 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) return -1;
3515
3516 std::string lowerCase = Tok.getString().lower();
3517 unsigned RegNum = MatchRegisterName(lowerCase);
3518 if (!RegNum) {
3519 RegNum = StringSwitch<unsigned>(lowerCase)
3520 .Case("r13", ARM::SP)
3521 .Case("r14", ARM::LR)
3522 .Case("r15", ARM::PC)
3523 .Case("ip", ARM::R12)
3524 // Additional register name aliases for 'gas' compatibility.
3525 .Case("a1", ARM::R0)
3526 .Case("a2", ARM::R1)
3527 .Case("a3", ARM::R2)
3528 .Case("a4", ARM::R3)
3529 .Case("v1", ARM::R4)
3530 .Case("v2", ARM::R5)
3531 .Case("v3", ARM::R6)
3532 .Case("v4", ARM::R7)
3533 .Case("v5", ARM::R8)
3534 .Case("v6", ARM::R9)
3535 .Case("v7", ARM::R10)
3536 .Case("v8", ARM::R11)
3537 .Case("sb", ARM::R9)
3538 .Case("sl", ARM::R10)
3539 .Case("fp", ARM::R11)
3540 .Default(0);
3541 }
3542 if (!RegNum) {
3543 // Check for aliases registered via .req. Canonicalize to lower case.
3544 // That's more consistent since register names are case insensitive, and
3545 // it's how the original entry was passed in from MC/MCParser/AsmParser.
3546 StringMap<unsigned>::const_iterator Entry = RegisterReqs.find(lowerCase);
3547 // If no match, return failure.
3548 if (Entry == RegisterReqs.end())
3549 return -1;
3550 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
3551 return Entry->getValue();
3552 }
3553
3554 // Some FPUs only have 16 D registers, so D16-D31 are invalid
3555 if (!hasD32() && RegNum >= ARM::D16 && RegNum <= ARM::D31)
3556 return -1;
3557
3558 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
3559
3560 return RegNum;
3561}
3562
3563// Try to parse a shifter (e.g., "lsl <amt>"). On success, return 0.
3564// If a recoverable error occurs, return 1. If an irrecoverable error
3565// occurs, return -1. An irrecoverable error is one where tokens have been
3566// consumed in the process of trying to parse the shifter (i.e., when it is
3567// indeed a shifter operand, but malformed).
3568int ARMAsmParser::tryParseShiftRegister(OperandVector &Operands) {
3569 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3570 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3571 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
3572 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
3573 return -1;
3574
3575 std::string lowerCase = Tok.getString().lower();
3576 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy = StringSwitch<ARM_AM::ShiftOpc>(lowerCase)
3577 .Case("asl", ARM_AM::lsl)
3578 .Case("lsl", ARM_AM::lsl)
3579 .Case("lsr", ARM_AM::lsr)
3580 .Case("asr", ARM_AM::asr)
3581 .Case("ror", ARM_AM::ror)
3582 .Case("rrx", ARM_AM::rrx)
3583 .Default(ARM_AM::no_shift);
3584
3585 if (ShiftTy == ARM_AM::no_shift)
3586 return 1;
3587
3588 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the operator.
3589
3590 // The source register for the shift has already been added to the
3591 // operand list, so we need to pop it off and combine it into the shifted
3592 // register operand instead.
3593 std::unique_ptr<ARMOperand> PrevOp(
3594 (ARMOperand *)Operands.pop_back_val().release());
3595 if (!PrevOp->isReg())
3596 return Error(PrevOp->getStartLoc(), "shift must be of a register");
3597 int SrcReg = PrevOp->getReg();
3598
3599 SMLoc EndLoc;
3600 int64_t Imm = 0;
3601 int ShiftReg = 0;
3602 if (ShiftTy == ARM_AM::rrx) {
3603 // RRX Doesn't have an explicit shift amount. The encoder expects
3604 // the shift register to be the same as the source register. Seems odd,
3605 // but OK.
3606 ShiftReg = SrcReg;
3607 } else {
3608 // Figure out if this is shifted by a constant or a register (for non-RRX).
3609 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
3610 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
3611 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash.
3612 SMLoc ImmLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3613 const MCExpr *ShiftExpr = nullptr;
3614 if (getParser().parseExpression(ShiftExpr, EndLoc)) {
3615 Error(ImmLoc, "invalid immediate shift value");
3616 return -1;
3617 }
3618 // The expression must be evaluatable as an immediate.
3619 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ShiftExpr);
3620 if (!CE) {
3621 Error(ImmLoc, "invalid immediate shift value");
3622 return -1;
3623 }
3624 // Range check the immediate.
3625 // lsl, ror: 0 <= imm <= 31
3626 // lsr, asr: 0 <= imm <= 32
3627 Imm = CE->getValue();
3628 if (Imm < 0 ||
3629 ((ShiftTy == ARM_AM::lsl || ShiftTy == ARM_AM::ror) && Imm > 31) ||
3630 ((ShiftTy == ARM_AM::lsr || ShiftTy == ARM_AM::asr) && Imm > 32)) {
3631 Error(ImmLoc, "immediate shift value out of range");
3632 return -1;
3633 }
3634 // shift by zero is a nop. Always send it through as lsl.
3635 // ('as' compatibility)
3636 if (Imm == 0)
3637 ShiftTy = ARM_AM::lsl;
3638 } else if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
3639 SMLoc L = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3640 EndLoc = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
3641 ShiftReg = tryParseRegister();
3642 if (ShiftReg == -1) {
3643 Error(L, "expected immediate or register in shift operand");
3644 return -1;
3645 }
3646 } else {
3647 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
3648 "expected immediate or register in shift operand");
3649 return -1;
3650 }
3651 }
3652
3653 if (ShiftReg && ShiftTy != ARM_AM::rrx)
3654 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateShiftedRegister(ShiftTy, SrcReg,
3655 ShiftReg, Imm,
3656 S, EndLoc));
3657 else
3658 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateShiftedImmediate(ShiftTy, SrcReg, Imm,
3659 S, EndLoc));
3660
3661 return 0;
3662}
3663
3664/// Try to parse a register name. The token must be an Identifier when called.
3665/// If it's a register, an AsmOperand is created. Another AsmOperand is created
3666/// if there is a "writeback". 'true' if it's not a register.
3667///
3668/// TODO this is likely to change to allow different register types and or to
3669/// parse for a specific register type.
3670bool ARMAsmParser::tryParseRegisterWithWriteBack(OperandVector &Operands) {
3671 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3672 SMLoc RegStartLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3673 SMLoc RegEndLoc = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
3674 int RegNo = tryParseRegister();
3675 if (RegNo == -1)
3676 return true;
3677
3678 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateReg(RegNo, RegStartLoc, RegEndLoc));
3679
3680 const AsmToken &ExclaimTok = Parser.getTok();
3681 if (ExclaimTok.is(AsmToken::Exclaim)) {
3682 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateToken(ExclaimTok.getString(),
3683 ExclaimTok.getLoc()));
3684 Parser.Lex(); // Eat exclaim token
3685 return false;
3686 }
3687
3688 // Also check for an index operand. This is only legal for vector registers,
3689 // but that'll get caught OK in operand matching, so we don't need to
3690 // explicitly filter everything else out here.
3691 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
3692 SMLoc SIdx = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3693 Parser.Lex(); // Eat left bracket token.
3694
3695 const MCExpr *ImmVal;
3696 if (getParser().parseExpression(ImmVal))
3697 return true;
3698 const MCConstantExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ImmVal);
3699 if (!MCE)
3700 return TokError("immediate value expected for vector index");
3701
3702 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac))
3703 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "']' expected");
3704
3705 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
3706 Parser.Lex(); // Eat right bracket token.
3707
3708 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorIndex(MCE->getValue(),
3709 SIdx, E,
3710 getContext()));
3711 }
3712
3713 return false;
3714}
3715
3716/// MatchCoprocessorOperandName - Try to parse an coprocessor related
3717/// instruction with a symbolic operand name.
3718/// We accept "crN" syntax for GAS compatibility.
3719/// <operand-name> ::= <prefix><number>
3720/// If CoprocOp is 'c', then:
3721/// <prefix> ::= c | cr
3722/// If CoprocOp is 'p', then :
3723/// <prefix> ::= p
3724/// <number> ::= integer in range [0, 15]
3725static int MatchCoprocessorOperandName(StringRef Name, char CoprocOp) {
3726 // Use the same layout as the tablegen'erated register name matcher. Ugly,
3727 // but efficient.
3728 if (Name.size() < 2 || Name[0] != CoprocOp)
3729 return -1;
3730 Name = (Name[1] == 'r') ? Name.drop_front(2) : Name.drop_front();
3731
3732 switch (Name.size()) {
3733 default: return -1;
3734 case 1:
3735 switch (Name[0]) {
3736 default: return -1;
3737 case '0': return 0;
3738 case '1': return 1;
3739 case '2': return 2;
3740 case '3': return 3;
3741 case '4': return 4;
3742 case '5': return 5;
3743 case '6': return 6;
3744 case '7': return 7;
3745 case '8': return 8;
3746 case '9': return 9;
3747 }
3748 case 2:
3749 if (Name[0] != '1')
3750 return -1;
3751 switch (Name[1]) {
3752 default: return -1;
3753 // CP10 and CP11 are VFP/NEON and so vector instructions should be used.
3754 // However, old cores (v5/v6) did use them in that way.
3755 case '0': return 10;
3756 case '1': return 11;
3757 case '2': return 12;
3758 case '3': return 13;
3759 case '4': return 14;
3760 case '5': return 15;
3761 }
3762 }
3763}
3764
3765/// parseITCondCode - Try to parse a condition code for an IT instruction.
3766OperandMatchResultTy
3767ARMAsmParser::parseITCondCode(OperandVector &Operands) {
3768 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3769 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3770 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
3771 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier))
3772 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3773 unsigned CC = ARMCondCodeFromString(Tok.getString());
3774 if (CC == ~0U)
3775 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3776 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the token.
3777
3778 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateCondCode(ARMCC::CondCodes(CC), S));
3779
3780 return MatchOperand_Success;
3781}
3782
3783/// parseCoprocNumOperand - Try to parse an coprocessor number operand. The
3784/// token must be an Identifier when called, and if it is a coprocessor
3785/// number, the token is eaten and the operand is added to the operand list.
3786OperandMatchResultTy
3787ARMAsmParser::parseCoprocNumOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
3788 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3789 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3790 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
3791 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
3792 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3793
3794 int Num = MatchCoprocessorOperandName(Tok.getString().lower(), 'p');
3795 if (Num == -1)
3796 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3797 // ARMv7 and v8 don't allow cp10/cp11 due to VFP/NEON specific instructions
3798 if ((hasV7Ops() || hasV8Ops()) && (Num == 10 || Num == 11))
3799 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3800
3801 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
3802 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateCoprocNum(Num, S));
3803 return MatchOperand_Success;
3804}
3805
3806/// parseCoprocRegOperand - Try to parse an coprocessor register operand. The
3807/// token must be an Identifier when called, and if it is a coprocessor
3808/// number, the token is eaten and the operand is added to the operand list.
3809OperandMatchResultTy
3810ARMAsmParser::parseCoprocRegOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
3811 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3812 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3813 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
3814 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
3815 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3816
3817 int Reg = MatchCoprocessorOperandName(Tok.getString().lower(), 'c');
3818 if (Reg == -1)
3819 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3820
3821 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
3822 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateCoprocReg(Reg, S));
3823 return MatchOperand_Success;
3824}
3825
3826/// parseCoprocOptionOperand - Try to parse an coprocessor option operand.
3827/// coproc_option : '{' imm0_255 '}'
3828OperandMatchResultTy
3829ARMAsmParser::parseCoprocOptionOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
3830 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3831 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3832
3833 // If this isn't a '{', this isn't a coprocessor immediate operand.
3834 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::LCurly))
3835 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3836 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '{'
3837
3838 const MCExpr *Expr;
3839 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3840 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr)) {
3841 Error(Loc, "illegal expression");
3842 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3843 }
3844 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr);
3845 if (!CE || CE->getValue() < 0 || CE->getValue() > 255) {
3846 Error(Loc, "coprocessor option must be an immediate in range [0, 255]");
3847 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3848 }
3849 int Val = CE->getValue();
3850
3851 // Check for and consume the closing '}'
3852 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RCurly))
3853 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3854 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
3855 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '}'
3856
3857 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateCoprocOption(Val, S, E));
3858 return MatchOperand_Success;
3859}
3860
3861// For register list parsing, we need to map from raw GPR register numbering
3862// to the enumeration values. The enumeration values aren't sorted by
3863// register number due to our using "sp", "lr" and "pc" as canonical names.
3864static unsigned getNextRegister(unsigned Reg) {
3865 // If this is a GPR, we need to do it manually, otherwise we can rely
3866 // on the sort ordering of the enumeration since the other reg-classes
3867 // are sane.
3868 if (!ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3869 return Reg + 1;
3870 switch(Reg) {
3871 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid GPR number!");
3872 case ARM::R0: return ARM::R1; case ARM::R1: return ARM::R2;
3873 case ARM::R2: return ARM::R3; case ARM::R3: return ARM::R4;
3874 case ARM::R4: return ARM::R5; case ARM::R5: return ARM::R6;
3875 case ARM::R6: return ARM::R7; case ARM::R7: return ARM::R8;
3876 case ARM::R8: return ARM::R9; case ARM::R9: return ARM::R10;
3877 case ARM::R10: return ARM::R11; case ARM::R11: return ARM::R12;
3878 case ARM::R12: return ARM::SP; case ARM::SP: return ARM::LR;
3879 case ARM::LR: return ARM::PC; case ARM::PC: return ARM::R0;
3880 }
3881}
3882
3883/// Parse a register list.
3884bool ARMAsmParser::parseRegisterList(OperandVector &Operands,
3885 bool EnforceOrder) {
3886 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
3887 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::LCurly))
3888 return TokError("Token is not a Left Curly Brace");
3889 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3890 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '{' token.
3891 SMLoc RegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3892
3893 // Check the first register in the list to see what register class
3894 // this is a list of.
3895 int Reg = tryParseRegister();
3896 if (Reg == -1)
3897 return Error(RegLoc, "register expected");
3898
3899 // The reglist instructions have at most 16 registers, so reserve
3900 // space for that many.
3901 int EReg = 0;
3902 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>, 16> Registers;
3903
3904 // Allow Q regs and just interpret them as the two D sub-registers.
3905 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
3906 Reg = getDRegFromQReg(Reg);
3907 EReg = MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg);
3908 Registers.push_back(std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>(EReg, Reg));
3909 ++Reg;
3910 }
3911 const MCRegisterClass *RC;
3912 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3913 RC = &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID];
3914 else if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPRRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3915 RC = &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPRRegClassID];
3916 else if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::SPRRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3917 RC = &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::SPRRegClassID];
3918 else if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3919 RC = &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID];
3920 else
3921 return Error(RegLoc, "invalid register in register list");
3922
3923 // Store the register.
3924 EReg = MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg);
3925 Registers.push_back(std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>(EReg, Reg));
3926
3927 // This starts immediately after the first register token in the list,
3928 // so we can see either a comma or a minus (range separator) as a legal
3929 // next token.
3930 while (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma) ||
3931 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
3932 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
3933 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the minus.
3934 SMLoc AfterMinusLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3935 int EndReg = tryParseRegister();
3936 if (EndReg == -1)
3937 return Error(AfterMinusLoc, "register expected");
3938 // Allow Q regs and just interpret them as the two D sub-registers.
3939 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(EndReg))
3940 EndReg = getDRegFromQReg(EndReg) + 1;
3941 // If the register is the same as the start reg, there's nothing
3942 // more to do.
3943 if (Reg == EndReg)
3944 continue;
3945 // The register must be in the same register class as the first.
3946 if (!RC->contains(EndReg))
3947 return Error(AfterMinusLoc, "invalid register in register list");
3948 // Ranges must go from low to high.
3949 if (MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg) > MRI->getEncodingValue(EndReg))
3950 return Error(AfterMinusLoc, "bad range in register list");
3951
3952 // Add all the registers in the range to the register list.
3953 while (Reg != EndReg) {
3954 Reg = getNextRegister(Reg);
3955 EReg = MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg);
3956 Registers.push_back(std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>(EReg, Reg));
3957 }
3958 continue;
3959 }
3960 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
3961 RegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
3962 int OldReg = Reg;
3963 const AsmToken RegTok = Parser.getTok();
3964 Reg = tryParseRegister();
3965 if (Reg == -1)
3966 return Error(RegLoc, "register expected");
3967 // Allow Q regs and just interpret them as the two D sub-registers.
3968 bool isQReg = false;
3969 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
3970 Reg = getDRegFromQReg(Reg);
3971 isQReg = true;
3972 }
3973 if (!RC->contains(Reg) &&
3974 RC->getID() == ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].getID() &&
3975 ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
3976 // switch the register classes, as GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID is a partial
3977 // subset of GPRRegClassId except it contains APSR as well.
3978 RC = &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID];
3979 }
3980 if (Reg == ARM::VPR && (RC == &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::SPRRegClassID] ||
3981 RC == &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPRRegClassID])) {
3982 RC = &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::FPWithVPRRegClassID];
3983 EReg = MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg);
3984 Registers.push_back(std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>(EReg, Reg));
3985 continue;
3986 }
3987 // The register must be in the same register class as the first.
3988 if (!RC->contains(Reg))
3989 return Error(RegLoc, "invalid register in register list");
3990 // In most cases, the list must be monotonically increasing. An
3991 // exception is CLRM, which is order-independent anyway, so
3992 // there's no potential for confusion if you write clrm {r2,r1}
3993 // instead of clrm {r1,r2}.
3994 if (EnforceOrder &&
3995 MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg) < MRI->getEncodingValue(OldReg)) {
3996 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3997 Warning(RegLoc, "register list not in ascending order");
3998 else if (!ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID].contains(Reg))
3999 return Error(RegLoc, "register list not in ascending order");
4000 }
4001 if (MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg) == MRI->getEncodingValue(OldReg)) {
4002 Warning(RegLoc, "duplicated register (" + RegTok.getString() +
4003 ") in register list");
4004 continue;
4005 }
4006 // VFP register lists must also be contiguous.
4007 if (RC != &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRRegClassID] &&
4008 RC != &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::GPRwithAPSRnospRegClassID] &&
4009 Reg != OldReg + 1)
4010 return Error(RegLoc, "non-contiguous register range");
4011 EReg = MRI->getEncodingValue(Reg);
4012 Registers.push_back(std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>(EReg, Reg));
4013 if (isQReg) {
4014 EReg = MRI->getEncodingValue(++Reg);
4015 Registers.push_back(std::pair<unsigned, unsigned>(EReg, Reg));
4016 }
4017 }
4018
4019 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RCurly))
4020 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'}' expected");
4021 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
4022 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '}' token.
4023
4024 // Push the register list operand.
4025 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateRegList(Registers, S, E));
4026
4027 // The ARM system instruction variants for LDM/STM have a '^' token here.
4028 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Caret)) {
4029 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateToken("^",Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
4030 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '^' token.
4031 }
4032
4033 return false;
4034}
4035
4036// Helper function to parse the lane index for vector lists.
4037OperandMatchResultTy ARMAsmParser::
4038parseVectorLane(VectorLaneTy &LaneKind, unsigned &Index, SMLoc &EndLoc) {
4039 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4040 Index = 0; // Always return a defined index value.
4041 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
4042 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '['.
4043 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::RBrac)) {
4044 // "Dn[]" is the 'all lanes' syntax.
4045 LaneKind = AllLanes;
4046 EndLoc = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
4047 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ']'.
4048 return MatchOperand_Success;
4049 }
4050
4051 // There's an optional '#' token here. Normally there wouldn't be, but
4052 // inline assemble puts one in, and it's friendly to accept that.
4053 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash))
4054 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '#' or '$'.
4055
4056 const MCExpr *LaneIndex;
4057 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4058 if (getParser().parseExpression(LaneIndex)) {
4059 Error(Loc, "illegal expression");
4060 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4061 }
4062 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(LaneIndex);
4063 if (!CE) {
4064 Error(Loc, "lane index must be empty or an integer");
4065 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4066 }
4067 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac)) {
4068 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "']' expected");
4069 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4070 }
4071 EndLoc = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
4072 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ']'.
4073 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
4074
4075 // FIXME: Make this range check context sensitive for .8, .16, .32.
4076 if (Val < 0 || Val > 7) {
4077 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "lane index out of range");
4078 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4079 }
4080 Index = Val;
4081 LaneKind = IndexedLane;
4082 return MatchOperand_Success;
4083 }
4084 LaneKind = NoLanes;
4085 return MatchOperand_Success;
4086}
4087
4088// parse a vector register list
4089OperandMatchResultTy
4090ARMAsmParser::parseVectorList(OperandVector &Operands) {
4091 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4092 VectorLaneTy LaneKind;
4093 unsigned LaneIndex;
4094 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4095 // As an extension (to match gas), support a plain D register or Q register
4096 // (without encosing curly braces) as a single or double entry list,
4097 // respectively.
4098 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4099 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
4100 int Reg = tryParseRegister();
4101 if (Reg == -1)
4102 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4103 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPRRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
4104 OperandMatchResultTy Res = parseVectorLane(LaneKind, LaneIndex, E);
4105 if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
4106 return Res;
4107 switch (LaneKind) {
4108 case NoLanes:
4109 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorList(Reg, 1, false, S, E));
4110 break;
4111 case AllLanes:
4112 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorListAllLanes(Reg, 1, false,
4113 S, E));
4114 break;
4115 case IndexedLane:
4116 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorListIndexed(Reg, 1,
4117 LaneIndex,
4118 false, S, E));
4119 break;
4120 }
4121 return MatchOperand_Success;
4122 }
4123 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
4124 Reg = getDRegFromQReg(Reg);
4125 OperandMatchResultTy Res = parseVectorLane(LaneKind, LaneIndex, E);
4126 if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
4127 return Res;
4128 switch (LaneKind) {
4129 case NoLanes:
4130 Reg = MRI->getMatchingSuperReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_0,
4131 &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPairRegClassID]);
4132 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorList(Reg, 2, false, S, E));
4133 break;
4134 case AllLanes:
4135 Reg = MRI->getMatchingSuperReg(Reg, ARM::dsub_0,
4136 &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPairRegClassID]);
4137 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorListAllLanes(Reg, 2, false,
4138 S, E));
4139 break;
4140 case IndexedLane:
4141 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorListIndexed(Reg, 2,
4142 LaneIndex,
4143 false, S, E));
4144 break;
4145 }
4146 return MatchOperand_Success;
4147 }
4148 Error(S, "vector register expected");
4149 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4150 }
4151
4152 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::LCurly))
4153 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4154
4155 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '{' token.
4156 SMLoc RegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4157
4158 int Reg = tryParseRegister();
4159 if (Reg == -1) {
4160 Error(RegLoc, "register expected");
4161 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4162 }
4163 unsigned Count = 1;
4164 int Spacing = 0;
4165 unsigned FirstReg = Reg;
4166 // The list is of D registers, but we also allow Q regs and just interpret
4167 // them as the two D sub-registers.
4168 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
4169 FirstReg = Reg = getDRegFromQReg(Reg);
4170 Spacing = 1; // double-spacing requires explicit D registers, otherwise
4171 // it's ambiguous with four-register single spaced.
4172 ++Reg;
4173 ++Count;
4174 }
4175
4176 SMLoc E;
4177 if (parseVectorLane(LaneKind, LaneIndex, E) != MatchOperand_Success)
4178 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4179
4180 while (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma) ||
4181 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
4182 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
4183 if (!Spacing)
4184 Spacing = 1; // Register range implies a single spaced list.
4185 else if (Spacing == 2) {
4186 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(),
4187 "sequential registers in double spaced list");
4188 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4189 }
4190 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the minus.
4191 SMLoc AfterMinusLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4192 int EndReg = tryParseRegister();
4193 if (EndReg == -1) {
4194 Error(AfterMinusLoc, "register expected");
4195 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4196 }
4197 // Allow Q regs and just interpret them as the two D sub-registers.
4198 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(EndReg))
4199 EndReg = getDRegFromQReg(EndReg) + 1;
4200 // If the register is the same as the start reg, there's nothing
4201 // more to do.
4202 if (Reg == EndReg)
4203 continue;
4204 // The register must be in the same register class as the first.
4205 if (!ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPRRegClassID].contains(EndReg)) {
4206 Error(AfterMinusLoc, "invalid register in register list");
4207 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4208 }
4209 // Ranges must go from low to high.
4210 if (Reg > EndReg) {
4211 Error(AfterMinusLoc, "bad range in register list");
4212 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4213 }
4214 // Parse the lane specifier if present.
4215 VectorLaneTy NextLaneKind;
4216 unsigned NextLaneIndex;
4217 if (parseVectorLane(NextLaneKind, NextLaneIndex, E) !=
4218 MatchOperand_Success)
4219 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4220 if (NextLaneKind != LaneKind || LaneIndex != NextLaneIndex) {
4221 Error(AfterMinusLoc, "mismatched lane index in register list");
4222 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4223 }
4224
4225 // Add all the registers in the range to the register list.
4226 Count += EndReg - Reg;
4227 Reg = EndReg;
4228 continue;
4229 }
4230 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
4231 RegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4232 int OldReg = Reg;
4233 Reg = tryParseRegister();
4234 if (Reg == -1) {
4235 Error(RegLoc, "register expected");
4236 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4237 }
4238 // vector register lists must be contiguous.
4239 // It's OK to use the enumeration values directly here rather, as the
4240 // VFP register classes have the enum sorted properly.
4241 //
4242 // The list is of D registers, but we also allow Q regs and just interpret
4243 // them as the two D sub-registers.
4244 if (ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::QPRRegClassID].contains(Reg)) {
4245 if (!Spacing)
4246 Spacing = 1; // Register range implies a single spaced list.
4247 else if (Spacing == 2) {
4248 Error(RegLoc,
4249 "invalid register in double-spaced list (must be 'D' register')");
4250 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4251 }
4252 Reg = getDRegFromQReg(Reg);
4253 if (Reg != OldReg + 1) {
4254 Error(RegLoc, "non-contiguous register range");
4255 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4256 }
4257 ++Reg;
4258 Count += 2;
4259 // Parse the lane specifier if present.
4260 VectorLaneTy NextLaneKind;
4261 unsigned NextLaneIndex;
4262 SMLoc LaneLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4263 if (parseVectorLane(NextLaneKind, NextLaneIndex, E) !=
4264 MatchOperand_Success)
4265 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4266 if (NextLaneKind != LaneKind || LaneIndex != NextLaneIndex) {
4267 Error(LaneLoc, "mismatched lane index in register list");
4268 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4269 }
4270 continue;
4271 }
4272 // Normal D register.
4273 // Figure out the register spacing (single or double) of the list if
4274 // we don't know it already.
4275 if (!Spacing)
4276 Spacing = 1 + (Reg == OldReg + 2);
4277
4278 // Just check that it's contiguous and keep going.
4279 if (Reg != OldReg + Spacing) {
4280 Error(RegLoc, "non-contiguous register range");
4281 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4282 }
4283 ++Count;
4284 // Parse the lane specifier if present.
4285 VectorLaneTy NextLaneKind;
4286 unsigned NextLaneIndex;
4287 SMLoc EndLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4288 if (parseVectorLane(NextLaneKind, NextLaneIndex, E) != MatchOperand_Success)
4289 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4290 if (NextLaneKind != LaneKind || LaneIndex != NextLaneIndex) {
4291 Error(EndLoc, "mismatched lane index in register list");
4292 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4293 }
4294 }
4295
4296 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RCurly)) {
4297 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'}' expected");
4298 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4299 }
4300 E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
4301 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '}' token.
4302
4303 switch (LaneKind) {
4304 case NoLanes:
4305 // Two-register operands have been converted to the
4306 // composite register classes.
4307 if (Count == 2) {
4308 const MCRegisterClass *RC = (Spacing == 1) ?
4309 &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPairRegClassID] :
4310 &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPairSpcRegClassID];
4311 FirstReg = MRI->getMatchingSuperReg(FirstReg, ARM::dsub_0, RC);
4312 }
4313 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorList(FirstReg, Count,
4314 (Spacing == 2), S, E));
4315 break;
4316 case AllLanes:
4317 // Two-register operands have been converted to the
4318 // composite register classes.
4319 if (Count == 2) {
4320 const MCRegisterClass *RC = (Spacing == 1) ?
4321 &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPairRegClassID] :
4322 &ARMMCRegisterClasses[ARM::DPairSpcRegClassID];
4323 FirstReg = MRI->getMatchingSuperReg(FirstReg, ARM::dsub_0, RC);
4324 }
4325 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorListAllLanes(FirstReg, Count,
4326 (Spacing == 2),
4327 S, E));
4328 break;
4329 case IndexedLane:
4330 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateVectorListIndexed(FirstReg, Count,
4331 LaneIndex,
4332 (Spacing == 2),
4333 S, E));
4334 break;
4335 }
4336 return MatchOperand_Success;
4337}
4338
4339/// parseMemBarrierOptOperand - Try to parse DSB/DMB data barrier options.
4340OperandMatchResultTy
4341ARMAsmParser::parseMemBarrierOptOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
4342 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4343 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4344 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4345 unsigned Opt;
4346
4347 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4348 StringRef OptStr = Tok.getString();
4349
4350 Opt = StringSwitch<unsigned>(OptStr.slice(0, OptStr.size()).lower())
4351 .Case("sy", ARM_MB::SY)
4352 .Case("st", ARM_MB::ST)
4353 .Case("ld", ARM_MB::LD)
4354 .Case("sh", ARM_MB::ISH)
4355 .Case("ish", ARM_MB::ISH)
4356 .Case("shst", ARM_MB::ISHST)
4357 .Case("ishst", ARM_MB::ISHST)
4358 .Case("ishld", ARM_MB::ISHLD)
4359 .Case("nsh", ARM_MB::NSH)
4360 .Case("un", ARM_MB::NSH)
4361 .Case("nshst", ARM_MB::NSHST)
4362 .Case("nshld", ARM_MB::NSHLD)
4363 .Case("unst", ARM_MB::NSHST)
4364 .Case("osh", ARM_MB::OSH)
4365 .Case("oshst", ARM_MB::OSHST)
4366 .Case("oshld", ARM_MB::OSHLD)
4367 .Default(~0U);
4368
4369 // ishld, oshld, nshld and ld are only available from ARMv8.
4370 if (!hasV8Ops() && (Opt == ARM_MB::ISHLD || Opt == ARM_MB::OSHLD ||
4371 Opt == ARM_MB::NSHLD || Opt == ARM_MB::LD))
4372 Opt = ~0U;
4373
4374 if (Opt == ~0U)
4375 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4376
4377 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4378 } else if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
4379 Tok.is(AsmToken::Dollar) ||
4380 Tok.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
4381 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Integer))
4382 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '#' or '$'.
4383 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4384
4385 const MCExpr *MemBarrierID;
4386 if (getParser().parseExpression(MemBarrierID)) {
4387 Error(Loc, "illegal expression");
4388 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4389 }
4390
4391 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(MemBarrierID);
4392 if (!CE) {
4393 Error(Loc, "constant expression expected");
4394 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4395 }
4396
4397 int Val = CE->getValue();
4398 if (Val & ~0xf) {
4399 Error(Loc, "immediate value out of range");
4400 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4401 }
4402
4403 Opt = ARM_MB::RESERVED_0 + Val;
4404 } else
4405 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4406
4407 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMemBarrierOpt((ARM_MB::MemBOpt)Opt, S));
4408 return MatchOperand_Success;
4409}

4411OperandMatchResultTy
4412ARMAsmParser::parseTraceSyncBarrierOptOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
4413 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4414 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4415 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4416
4417 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
4418 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4419
4420 if (!Tok.getString().equals_lower("csync"))
4421 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4422
4423 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4424
4425 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateTraceSyncBarrierOpt(ARM_TSB::CSYNC, S));
4426 return MatchOperand_Success;

4429/// parseInstSyncBarrierOptOperand - Try to parse ISB inst sync barrier options.
4430OperandMatchResultTy
4431ARMAsmParser::parseInstSyncBarrierOptOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
4432 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4433 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4434 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4435 unsigned Opt;
4436
4437 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4438 StringRef OptStr = Tok.getString();
4439
4440 if (OptStr.equals_lower("sy"))
4441 Opt = ARM_ISB::SY;
4442 else
4443 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4444
4445 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4446 } else if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
4447 Tok.is(AsmToken::Dollar) ||
4448 Tok.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
4449 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Integer))
4450 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '#' or '$'.
4451 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4452
4453 const MCExpr *ISBarrierID;
4454 if (getParser().parseExpression(ISBarrierID)) {
4455 Error(Loc, "illegal expression");
4456 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4457 }
4458
4459 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ISBarrierID);
4460 if (!CE) {
4461 Error(Loc, "constant expression expected");
4462 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4463 }
4464
4465 int Val = CE->getValue();
4466 if (Val & ~0xf) {
4467 Error(Loc, "immediate value out of range");
4468 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4469 }
4470
4471 Opt = ARM_ISB::RESERVED_0 + Val;
4472 } else
4473 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4474
4475 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateInstSyncBarrierOpt(
4476 (ARM_ISB::InstSyncBOpt)Opt, S));
4477 return MatchOperand_Success;
4478}

4480
4481/// parseProcIFlagsOperand - Try to parse iflags from CPS instruction.
4482OperandMatchResultTy
4483ARMAsmParser::parseProcIFlagsOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
4484 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4485 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4486 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4487 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier))
4488 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4489 StringRef IFlagsStr = Tok.getString();
4490
4491 // An iflags string of "none" is interpreted to mean that none of the AIF
4492 // bits are set. Not a terribly useful instruction, but a valid encoding.
4493 unsigned IFlags = 0;
4494 if (IFlagsStr != "none") {
4495 for (int i = 0, e = IFlagsStr.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4496 unsigned Flag = StringSwitch<unsigned>(IFlagsStr.substr(i, 1).lower())
4497 .Case("a", ARM_PROC::A)
4498 .Case("i", ARM_PROC::I)
4499 .Case("f", ARM_PROC::F)
4500 .Default(~0U);
4501
4502 // If some specific iflag is already set, it means that some letter is
4503 // present more than once, this is not acceptable.
4504 if (Flag == ~0U || (IFlags & Flag))
4505 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4506
4507 IFlags |= Flag;
4508 }
4509 }
4510
4511 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4512 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateProcIFlags((ARM_PROC::IFlags)IFlags, S));
4513 return MatchOperand_Success;
4514}
4515
4516/// parseMSRMaskOperand - Try to parse mask flags from MSR instruction.
4517OperandMatchResultTy
4518ARMAsmParser::parseMSRMaskOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
4519 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4520 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4521 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4522
4523 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
4524 int64_t Val = Tok.getIntVal();
4525 if (Val > 255 || Val < 0) {
4526 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4527 }
4528 unsigned SYSmvalue = Val & 0xFF;
4529 Parser.Lex();
4530 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMSRMask(SYSmvalue, S));
4531 return MatchOperand_Success;
4532 }
4533
4534 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier))
4535 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4536 StringRef Mask = Tok.getString();
4537
4538 if (isMClass()) {
4539 auto TheReg = ARMSysReg::lookupMClassSysRegByName(Mask.lower());
4540 if (!TheReg || !TheReg->hasRequiredFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits()))
4541 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4542
4543 unsigned SYSmvalue = TheReg->Encoding & 0xFFF;
4544
4545 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4546 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMSRMask(SYSmvalue, S));
4547 return MatchOperand_Success;
4548 }
4549
4550 // Split spec_reg from flag, example: CPSR_sxf => "CPSR" and "sxf"
4551 size_t Start = 0, Next = Mask.find('_');
4552 StringRef Flags = "";
4553 std::string SpecReg = Mask.slice(Start, Next).lower();
4554 if (Next != StringRef::npos)
4555 Flags = Mask.slice(Next+1, Mask.size());
4556
4557 // FlagsVal contains the complete mask:
4558 // 3-0: Mask
4559 // 4: Special Reg (cpsr, apsr => 0; spsr => 1)
4560 unsigned FlagsVal = 0;
4561
4562 if (SpecReg == "apsr") {
4563 FlagsVal = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Flags)
4564 .Case("nzcvq", 0x8) // same as CPSR_f
4565 .Case("g", 0x4) // same as CPSR_s
4566 .Case("nzcvqg", 0xc) // same as CPSR_fs
4567 .Default(~0U);
4568
4569 if (FlagsVal == ~0U) {
4570 if (!Flags.empty())
4571 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4572 else
4573 FlagsVal = 8; // No flag
4574 }
4575 } else if (SpecReg == "cpsr" || SpecReg == "spsr") {
4576 // cpsr_all is an alias for cpsr_fc, as is plain cpsr.
4577 if (Flags == "all" || Flags == "")
4578 Flags = "fc";
4579 for (int i = 0, e = Flags.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4580 unsigned Flag = StringSwitch<unsigned>(Flags.substr(i, 1))
4581 .Case("c", 1)
4582 .Case("x", 2)
4583 .Case("s", 4)
4584 .Case("f", 8)
4585 .Default(~0U);
4586
4587 // If some specific flag is already set, it means that some letter is
4588 // present more than once, this is not acceptable.
4589 if (Flag == ~0U || (FlagsVal & Flag))
4590 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4591 FlagsVal |= Flag;
4592 }
4593 } else // No match for special register.
4594 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4595
4596 // Special register without flags is NOT equivalent to "fc" flags.
4597 // NOTE: This is a divergence from gas' behavior. Uncommenting the following
4598 // two lines would enable gas compatibility at the expense of breaking
4599 // round-tripping.
4600 //
4601 // if (!FlagsVal)
4602 // FlagsVal = 0x9;
4603
4604 // Bit 4: Special Reg (cpsr, apsr => 0; spsr => 1)
4605 if (SpecReg == "spsr")
4606 FlagsVal |= 16;
4607
4608 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4609 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMSRMask(FlagsVal, S));
4610 return MatchOperand_Success;
4611}
4612
4613/// parseBankedRegOperand - Try to parse a banked register (e.g. "lr_irq") for
4614/// use in the MRS/MSR instructions added to support virtualization.
4615OperandMatchResultTy
4616ARMAsmParser::parseBankedRegOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
4617 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4618 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4619 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4620 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Identifier))
4621 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4622 StringRef RegName = Tok.getString();
4623
4624 auto TheReg = ARMBankedReg::lookupBankedRegByName(RegName.lower());
4625 if (!TheReg)
4626 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4627 unsigned Encoding = TheReg->Encoding;
4628
4629 Parser.Lex(); // Eat identifier token.
4630 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateBankedReg(Encoding, S));
4631 return MatchOperand_Success;
4632}
4633
4634OperandMatchResultTy
4635ARMAsmParser::parsePKHImm(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Op, int Low,
4636 int High) {
4637 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4638 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4639 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4640 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), Op + " operand expected.");
4641 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4642 }
4643 StringRef ShiftName = Tok.getString();
4644 std::string LowerOp = Op.lower();
4645 std::string UpperOp = Op.upper();
4646 if (ShiftName != LowerOp && ShiftName != UpperOp) {
4647 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), Op + " operand expected.");
4648 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4649 }
4650 Parser.Lex(); // Eat shift type token.
4651
4652 // There must be a '#' and a shift amount.
4653 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
4654 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
4655 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
4656 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4657 }
4658 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
4659
4660 const MCExpr *ShiftAmount;
4661 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4662 SMLoc EndLoc;
4663 if (getParser().parseExpression(ShiftAmount, EndLoc)) {
4664 Error(Loc, "illegal expression");
4665 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4666 }
4667 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ShiftAmount);
4668 if (!CE) {
4669 Error(Loc, "constant expression expected");
4670 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4671 }
4672 int Val = CE->getValue();
4673 if (Val < Low || Val > High) {
4674 Error(Loc, "immediate value out of range");
4675 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4676 }
4677
4678 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateImm(CE, Loc, EndLoc));
4679
4680 return MatchOperand_Success;
4681}
4682
4683OperandMatchResultTy
4684ARMAsmParser::parseSetEndImm(OperandVector &Operands) {
4685 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4686 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4687 SMLoc S = Tok.getLoc();
4688 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4689 Error(S, "'be' or 'le' operand expected");
4690 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4691 }
4692 int Val = StringSwitch<int>(Tok.getString().lower())
4693 .Case("be", 1)
4694 .Case("le", 0)
4695 .Default(-1);
4696 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the token.
4697
4698 if (Val == -1) {
4699 Error(S, "'be' or 'le' operand expected");
4700 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4701 }
4702 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateImm(MCConstantExpr::create(Val,
4703 getContext()),
4704 S, Tok.getEndLoc()));
4705 return MatchOperand_Success;
4706}
4707
4708/// parseShifterImm - Parse the shifter immediate operand for SSAT/USAT
4709/// instructions. Legal values are:
4710/// lsl #n 'n' in [0,31]
4711/// asr #n 'n' in [1,32]
4712/// n == 32 encoded as n == 0.
4713OperandMatchResultTy
4714ARMAsmParser::parseShifterImm(OperandVector &Operands) {
4715 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4716 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4717 SMLoc S = Tok.getLoc();
4718 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4719 Error(S, "shift operator 'asr' or 'lsl' expected");
4720 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4721 }
4722 StringRef ShiftName = Tok.getString();
4723 bool isASR;
4724 if (ShiftName == "lsl" || ShiftName == "LSL")
4725 isASR = false;
4726 else if (ShiftName == "asr" || ShiftName == "ASR")
4727 isASR = true;
4728 else {
4729 Error(S, "shift operator 'asr' or 'lsl' expected");
4730 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4731 }
4732 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the operator.
4733
4734 // A '#' and a shift amount.
4735 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
4736 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
4737 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
4738 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4739 }
4740 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
4741 SMLoc ExLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4742
4743 const MCExpr *ShiftAmount;
4744 SMLoc EndLoc;
4745 if (getParser().parseExpression(ShiftAmount, EndLoc)) {
4746 Error(ExLoc, "malformed shift expression");
4747 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4748 }
4749 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ShiftAmount);
4750 if (!CE) {
4751 Error(ExLoc, "shift amount must be an immediate");
4752 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4753 }
4754
4755 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
4756 if (isASR) {
4757 // Shift amount must be in [1,32]
4758 if (Val < 1 || Val > 32) {
4759 Error(ExLoc, "'asr' shift amount must be in range [1,32]");
4760 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4761 }
4762 // asr #32 encoded as asr #0, but is not allowed in Thumb2 mode.
4763 if (isThumb() && Val == 32) {
4764 Error(ExLoc, "'asr #32' shift amount not allowed in Thumb mode");
4765 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4766 }
4767 if (Val == 32) Val = 0;
4768 } else {
4769 // Shift amount must be in [1,32]
4770 if (Val < 0 || Val > 31) {
4771 Error(ExLoc, "'lsr' shift amount must be in range [0,31]");
4772 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4773 }
4774 }
4775
4776 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateShifterImm(isASR, Val, S, EndLoc));
4777
4778 return MatchOperand_Success;
4779}
4780
4781/// parseRotImm - Parse the shifter immediate operand for SXTB/UXTB family
4782/// of instructions. Legal values are:
4783/// ror #n 'n' in {0, 8, 16, 24}
4784OperandMatchResultTy
4785ARMAsmParser::parseRotImm(OperandVector &Operands) {
4786 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4787 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
4788 SMLoc S = Tok.getLoc();
4789 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
4790 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4791 StringRef ShiftName = Tok.getString();
4792 if (ShiftName != "ror" && ShiftName != "ROR")
4793 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4794 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the operator.
4795
4796 // A '#' and a rotate amount.
4797 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
4798 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
4799 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
4800 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4801 }
4802 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
4803 SMLoc ExLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4804
4805 const MCExpr *ShiftAmount;
4806 SMLoc EndLoc;
4807 if (getParser().parseExpression(ShiftAmount, EndLoc)) {
4808 Error(ExLoc, "malformed rotate expression");
4809 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4810 }
4811 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ShiftAmount);
4812 if (!CE) {
4813 Error(ExLoc, "rotate amount must be an immediate");
4814 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4815 }
4816
4817 int64_t Val = CE->getValue();
4818 // Shift amount must be in {0, 8, 16, 24} (0 is undocumented extension)
4819 // normally, zero is represented in asm by omitting the rotate operand
4820 // entirely.
4821 if (Val != 8 && Val != 16 && Val != 24 && Val != 0) {
4822 Error(ExLoc, "'ror' rotate amount must be 8, 16, or 24");
4823 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4824 }
4825
4826 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateRotImm(Val, S, EndLoc));
4827
4828 return MatchOperand_Success;
4829}
4830
4831OperandMatchResultTy
4832ARMAsmParser::parseModImm(OperandVector &Operands) {
4833 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4834 MCAsmLexer &Lexer = getLexer();
4835 int64_t Imm1, Imm2;
4836
4837 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4838
4839 // 1) A mod_imm operand can appear in the place of a register name:
4840 // add r0, #mod_imm
4841 // add r0, r0, #mod_imm
4842 // to correctly handle the latter, we bail out as soon as we see an
4843 // identifier.
4844 //
4845 // 2) Similarly, we do not want to parse into complex operands:
4846 // mov r0, #mod_imm
4847 // mov r0, :lower16:(_foo)
4848 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier) ||
4849 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Colon))
4850 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4851
4852 // Hash (dollar) is optional as per the ARMARM
4853 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
4854 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
4855 // Avoid parsing into complex operands (#:)
4856 if (Lexer.peekTok().is(AsmToken::Colon))
4857 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
4858
4859 // Eat the hash (dollar)
4860 Parser.Lex();
4861 }
4862
4863 SMLoc Sx1, Ex1;
4864 Sx1 = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4865 const MCExpr *Imm1Exp;
4866 if (getParser().parseExpression(Imm1Exp, Ex1)) {
4867 Error(Sx1, "malformed expression");
4868 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4869 }
4870
4871 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Imm1Exp);
4872
4873 if (CE) {
4874 // Immediate must fit within 32-bits
4875 Imm1 = CE->getValue();
4876 int Enc = ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(Imm1);
4877 if (Enc != -1 && Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
4878 // We have a match!
4879 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateModImm((Enc & 0xFF),
4880 (Enc & 0xF00) >> 7,
4881 Sx1, Ex1));
4882 return MatchOperand_Success;
4883 }
4884
4885 // We have parsed an immediate which is not for us, fallback to a plain
4886 // immediate. This can happen for instruction aliases. For an example,
4887 // ARMInstrInfo.td defines the alias [mov <-> mvn] which can transform
4888 // a mov (mvn) with a mod_imm_neg/mod_imm_not operand into the opposite
4889 // instruction with a mod_imm operand. The alias is defined such that the
4890 // parser method is shared, that's why we have to do this here.
4891 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
4892 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateImm(Imm1Exp, Sx1, Ex1));
4893 return MatchOperand_Success;
4894 }
4895 } else {
4896 // Operands like #(l1 - l2) can only be evaluated at a later stage (via an
4897 // MCFixup). Fallback to a plain immediate.
4898 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateImm(Imm1Exp, Sx1, Ex1));
4899 return MatchOperand_Success;
4900 }
4901
4902 // From this point onward, we expect the input to be a (#bits, #rot) pair
4903 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
4904 Error(Sx1, "expected modified immediate operand: #[0, 255], #even[0-30]");
4905 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4906 }
4907
4908 if (Imm1 & ~0xFF) {
4909 Error(Sx1, "immediate operand must a number in the range [0, 255]");
4910 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4911 }
4912
4913 // Eat the comma
4914 Parser.Lex();
4915
4916 // Repeat for #rot
4917 SMLoc Sx2, Ex2;
4918 Sx2 = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4919
4920 // Eat the optional hash (dollar)
4921 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
4922 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar))
4923 Parser.Lex();
4924
4925 const MCExpr *Imm2Exp;
4926 if (getParser().parseExpression(Imm2Exp, Ex2)) {
4927 Error(Sx2, "malformed expression");
4928 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4929 }
4930
4931 CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Imm2Exp);
4932
4933 if (CE) {
4934 Imm2 = CE->getValue();
4935 if (!(Imm2 & ~0x1E)) {
4936 // We have a match!
4937 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateModImm(Imm1, Imm2, S, Ex2));
4938 return MatchOperand_Success;
4939 }
4940 Error(Sx2, "immediate operand must an even number in the range [0, 30]");
4941 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4942 } else {
4943 Error(Sx2, "constant expression expected");
4944 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4945 }
4946}
4947
4948OperandMatchResultTy
4949ARMAsmParser::parseBitfield(OperandVector &Operands) {
4950 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
4951 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4952 // The bitfield descriptor is really two operands, the LSB and the width.
4953 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
4954 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
4955 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
4956 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4957 }
4958 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
4959
4960 const MCExpr *LSBExpr;
4961 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4962 if (getParser().parseExpression(LSBExpr)) {
4963 Error(E, "malformed immediate expression");
4964 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4965 }
4966 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(LSBExpr);
4967 if (!CE) {
4968 Error(E, "'lsb' operand must be an immediate");
4969 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4970 }
4971
4972 int64_t LSB = CE->getValue();
4973 // The LSB must be in the range [0,31]
4974 if (LSB < 0 || LSB > 31) {
4975 Error(E, "'lsb' operand must be in the range [0,31]");
4976 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4977 }
4978 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
4979
4980 // Expect another immediate operand.
4981 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Comma)) {
4982 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "too few operands");
4983 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4984 }
4985 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
4986 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
4987 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
4988 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
4989 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4990 }
4991 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
4992
4993 const MCExpr *WidthExpr;
4994 SMLoc EndLoc;
4995 if (getParser().parseExpression(WidthExpr, EndLoc)) {
4996 Error(E, "malformed immediate expression");
4997 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
4998 }
4999 CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(WidthExpr);
5000 if (!CE) {
5001 Error(E, "'width' operand must be an immediate");
5002 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5003 }
5004
5005 int64_t Width = CE->getValue();
5006 // The LSB must be in the range [1,32-lsb]
5007 if (Width < 1 || Width > 32 - LSB) {
5008 Error(E, "'width' operand must be in the range [1,32-lsb]");
5009 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5010 }
5011
5012 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateBitfield(LSB, Width, S, EndLoc));
5013
5014 return MatchOperand_Success;
5015}
5016
5017OperandMatchResultTy
5018ARMAsmParser::parsePostIdxReg(OperandVector &Operands) {
5019 // Check for a post-index addressing register operand. Specifically:
5020 // postidx_reg := '+' register {, shift}
5021 // | '-' register {, shift}
5022 // | register {, shift}
5023
5024 // This method must return MatchOperand_NoMatch without consuming any tokens
5025 // in the case where there is no match, as other alternatives take other
5026 // parse methods.
5027 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5028 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok();
5029 SMLoc S = Tok.getLoc();
5030 bool haveEaten = false;
5031 bool isAdd = true;
5032 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Plus)) {
5033 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '+' token.
5034 haveEaten = true;
5035 } else if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
5036 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '-' token.
5037 isAdd = false;
5038 haveEaten = true;
5039 }
5040
5041 SMLoc E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
5042 int Reg = tryParseRegister();
5043 if (Reg == -1) {
5044 if (!haveEaten)
5045 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5046 Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "register expected");
5047 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5048 }
5049
5050 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy = ARM_AM::no_shift;
5051 unsigned ShiftImm = 0;
5052 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
5053 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ','.
5054 if (parseMemRegOffsetShift(ShiftTy, ShiftImm))
5055 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5056
5057 // FIXME: Only approximates end...may include intervening whitespace.
5058 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5059 }
5060
5061 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreatePostIdxReg(Reg, isAdd, ShiftTy,
5062 ShiftImm, S, E));
5063
5064 return MatchOperand_Success;
5065}
5066
5067OperandMatchResultTy
5068ARMAsmParser::parseAM3Offset(OperandVector &Operands) {
5069 // Check for a post-index addressing register operand. Specifically:
5070 // am3offset := '+' register
5071 // | '-' register
5072 // | register
5073 // | # imm
5074 // | # + imm
5075 // | # - imm
5076
5077 // This method must return MatchOperand_NoMatch without consuming any tokens
5078 // in the case where there is no match, as other alternatives take other
5079 // parse methods.
5080 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5081 AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok();
5082 SMLoc S = Tok.getLoc();
5083
5084 // Do immediates first, as we always parse those if we have a '#'.
5085 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
5086 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar)) {
5087 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '#' or '$'.
5088 // Explicitly look for a '-', as we need to encode negative zero
5089 // differently.
5090 bool isNegative = Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus);
5091 const MCExpr *Offset;
5092 SMLoc E;
5093 if (getParser().parseExpression(Offset, E))
5094 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5095 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Offset);
5096 if (!CE) {
5097 Error(S, "constant expression expected");
5098 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5099 }
5100 // Negative zero is encoded as the flag value
5101 // std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min().
5102 int32_t Val = CE->getValue();
5103 if (isNegative && Val == 0)
5104 Val = std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min();
5105
5106 Operands.push_back(
5107 ARMOperand::CreateImm(MCConstantExpr::create(Val, getContext()), S, E));
5108
5109 return MatchOperand_Success;
5110 }
5111
5112 bool haveEaten = false;
5113 bool isAdd = true;
5114 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Plus)) {
5115 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '+' token.
5116 haveEaten = true;
5117 } else if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
5118 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '-' token.
5119 isAdd = false;
5120 haveEaten = true;
5121 }
5122
5123 Tok = Parser.getTok();
5124 int Reg = tryParseRegister();
5125 if (Reg == -1) {
5126 if (!haveEaten)
5127 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5128 Error(Tok.getLoc(), "register expected");
5129 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5130 }
5131
5132 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreatePostIdxReg(Reg, isAdd, ARM_AM::no_shift,
5133 0, S, Tok.getEndLoc()));
5134
5135 return MatchOperand_Success;
5136}
5137
5138/// Convert parsed operands to MCInst. Needed here because this instruction
5139/// only has two register operands, but multiplication is commutative so
5140/// assemblers should accept both "mul rD, rN, rD" and "mul rD, rD, rN".
5141void ARMAsmParser::cvtThumbMultiply(MCInst &Inst,
5142 const OperandVector &Operands) {
5143 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[3]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
5144 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[1]).addCCOutOperands(Inst, 1);
5145 // If we have a three-operand form, make sure to set Rn to be the operand
5146 // that isn't the same as Rd.
5147 unsigned RegOp = 4;
5148 if (Operands.size() == 6 &&
5149 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[4]).getReg() ==
5150 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[3]).getReg())
5151 RegOp = 5;
5152 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[RegOp]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
5153 Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
5154 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[2]).addCondCodeOperands(Inst, 2);
5155}
5156
5157void ARMAsmParser::cvtThumbBranches(MCInst &Inst,
5158 const OperandVector &Operands) {
5159 int CondOp = -1, ImmOp = -1;
5160 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
5161 case ARM::tB:
5162 case ARM::tBcc: CondOp = 1; ImmOp = 2; break;
5163
5164 case ARM::t2B:
5165 case ARM::t2Bcc: CondOp = 1; ImmOp = 3; break;
5166
5167 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instruction in cvtThumbBranches");
5168 }
5169 // first decide whether or not the branch should be conditional
5170 // by looking at it's location relative to an IT block
5171 if(inITBlock()) {
5172 // inside an IT block we cannot have any conditional branches. any
5173 // such instructions needs to be converted to unconditional form
5174 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
5175 case ARM::tBcc: Inst.setOpcode(ARM::tB); break;
5176 case ARM::t2Bcc: Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2B); break;
5177 }
5178 } else {
5179 // outside IT blocks we can only have unconditional branches with AL
5180 // condition code or conditional branches with non-AL condition code
5181 unsigned Cond = static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[CondOp]).getCondCode();
5182 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
5183 case ARM::tB:
5184 case ARM::tBcc:
5185 Inst.setOpcode(Cond == ARMCC::AL ? ARM::tB : ARM::tBcc);
5186 break;
5187 case ARM::t2B:
5188 case ARM::t2Bcc:
5189 Inst.setOpcode(Cond == ARMCC::AL ? ARM::t2B : ARM::t2Bcc);
5190 break;
5191 }
5192 }
5193
5194 // now decide on encoding size based on branch target range
5195 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
5196 // classify tB as either t2B or t1B based on range of immediate operand
5197 case ARM::tB: {
5198 ARMOperand &op = static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[ImmOp]);
5199 if (!op.isSignedOffset<11, 1>() && isThumb() && hasV8MBaseline())
5200 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2B);
5201 break;
5202 }
5203 // classify tBcc as either t2Bcc or t1Bcc based on range of immediate operand
5204 case ARM::tBcc: {
5205 ARMOperand &op = static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[ImmOp]);
5206 if (!op.isSignedOffset<8, 1>() && isThumb() && hasV8MBaseline())
5207 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2Bcc);
5208 break;
5209 }
5210 }
5211 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[ImmOp]).addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
5212 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[CondOp]).addCondCodeOperands(Inst, 2);
5213}
5214
5215/// Parse an ARM memory expression, return false if successful else return true
5216/// or an error. The first token must be a '[' when called.
5217bool ARMAsmParser::parseMemory(OperandVector &Operands) {
5218 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5219 SMLoc S, E;
5220 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::LBrac))
5221 return TokError("Token is not a Left Bracket");
5222 S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5223 Parser.Lex(); // Eat left bracket token.
5224
5225 const AsmToken &BaseRegTok = Parser.getTok();
5226 int BaseRegNum = tryParseRegister();
5227 if (BaseRegNum == -1)
5228 return Error(BaseRegTok.getLoc(), "register expected");
5229
5230 // The next token must either be a comma, a colon or a closing bracket.
5231 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
5232 if (!Tok.is(AsmToken::Colon) && !Tok.is(AsmToken::Comma) &&
5233 !Tok.is(AsmToken::RBrac))
5234 return Error(Tok.getLoc(), "malformed memory operand");
5235
5236 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::RBrac)) {
5237 E = Tok.getEndLoc();
5238 Parser.Lex(); // Eat right bracket token.
5239
5240 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMem(BaseRegNum, nullptr, 0,
5241 ARM_AM::no_shift, 0, 0, false,
5242 S, E));
5243
5244 // If there's a pre-indexing writeback marker, '!', just add it as a token
5245 // operand. It's rather odd, but syntactically valid.
5246 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Exclaim)) {
5247 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateToken("!",Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
5248 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '!'.
5249 }
5250
5251 return false;
5252 }
5253
5254 assert((Tok.is(AsmToken::Colon) || Tok.is(AsmToken::Comma)) &&
5255 "Lost colon or comma in memory operand?!");
5256 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
5257 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma.
5258 }
5259
5260 // If we have a ':', it's an alignment specifier.
5261 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Colon)) {
5262 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ':'.
5263 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5264 SMLoc AlignmentLoc = Tok.getLoc();
5265
5266 const MCExpr *Expr;
5267 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr))
5268 return true;
5269
5270 // The expression has to be a constant. Memory references with relocations
5271 // don't come through here, as they use the <label> forms of the relevant
5272 // instructions.
5273 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr);
5274 if (!CE)
5275 return Error (E, "constant expression expected");
5276
5277 unsigned Align = 0;
5278 switch (CE->getValue()) {
5279 default:
5280 return Error(E,
5281 "alignment specifier must be 16, 32, 64, 128, or 256 bits");
5282 case 16: Align = 2; break;
5283 case 32: Align = 4; break;
5284 case 64: Align = 8; break;
5285 case 128: Align = 16; break;
5286 case 256: Align = 32; break;
5287 }
5288
5289 // Now we should have the closing ']'
5290 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac))
5291 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "']' expected");
5292 E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
5293 Parser.Lex(); // Eat right bracket token.
5294
5295 // Don't worry about range checking the value here. That's handled by
5296 // the is*() predicates.
5297 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMem(BaseRegNum, nullptr, 0,
5298 ARM_AM::no_shift, 0, Align,
5299 false, S, E, AlignmentLoc));
5300
5301 // If there's a pre-indexing writeback marker, '!', just add it as a token
5302 // operand.
5303 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Exclaim)) {
5304 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateToken("!",Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
5305 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '!'.
5306 }
5307
5308 return false;
5309 }
5310
5311 // If we have a '#', it's an immediate offset, else assume it's a register
5312 // offset. Be friendly and also accept a plain integer (without a leading
5313 // hash) for gas compatibility.
5314 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Hash) ||
5315 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Dollar) ||
5316 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Integer)) {
5317 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Integer))
5318 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '#' or '$'.
5319 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5320
5321 bool isNegative = getParser().getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus);
5322 const MCExpr *Offset;
5323 if (getParser().parseExpression(Offset))
5324 return true;
5325
5326 // The expression has to be a constant. Memory references with relocations
5327 // don't come through here, as they use the <label> forms of the relevant
5328 // instructions.
5329 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Offset);
5330 if (!CE)
5331 return Error (E, "constant expression expected");
5332
5333 // If the constant was #-0, represent it as
5334 // std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min().
5335 int32_t Val = CE->getValue();
5336 if (isNegative && Val == 0)
5337 CE = MCConstantExpr::create(std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min(),
5338 getContext());
5339
5340 // Now we should have the closing ']'
5341 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac))
5342 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "']' expected");
5343 E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
5344 Parser.Lex(); // Eat right bracket token.
5345
5346 // Don't worry about range checking the value here. That's handled by
5347 // the is*() predicates.
5348 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMem(BaseRegNum, CE, 0,
5349 ARM_AM::no_shift, 0, 0,
5350 false, S, E));
5351
5352 // If there's a pre-indexing writeback marker, '!', just add it as a token
5353 // operand.
5354 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Exclaim)) {
5355 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateToken("!",Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
5356 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '!'.
5357 }
5358
5359 return false;
5360 }
5361
5362 // The register offset is optionally preceded by a '+' or '-'
5363 bool isNegative = false;
5364 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
5365 isNegative = true;
5366 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '-'.
5367 } else if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Plus)) {
5368 // Nothing to do.
5369 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '+'.
5370 }
5371
5372 E = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5373 int OffsetRegNum = tryParseRegister();
5374 if (OffsetRegNum == -1)
5375 return Error(E, "register expected");
5376
5377 // If there's a shift operator, handle it.
5378 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftType = ARM_AM::no_shift;
5379 unsigned ShiftImm = 0;
5380 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
5381 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the ','.
5382 if (parseMemRegOffsetShift(ShiftType, ShiftImm))
5383 return true;
5384 }
5385
5386 // Now we should have the closing ']'
5387 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::RBrac))
5388 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "']' expected");
5389 E = Parser.getTok().getEndLoc();
5390 Parser.Lex(); // Eat right bracket token.
5391
5392 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateMem(BaseRegNum, nullptr, OffsetRegNum,
5393 ShiftType, ShiftImm, 0, isNegative,
5394 S, E));
5395
5396 // If there's a pre-indexing writeback marker, '!', just add it as a token
5397 // operand.
5398 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Exclaim)) {
5399 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateToken("!",Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
5400 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '!'.
5401 }
5402
5403 return false;
5404}
5405
5406/// parseMemRegOffsetShift - one of these two:
5407/// ( lsl | lsr | asr | ror ) , # shift_amount
5408/// rrx
5409/// return true if it parses a shift otherwise it returns false.
5410bool ARMAsmParser::parseMemRegOffsetShift(ARM_AM::ShiftOpc &St,
5411 unsigned &Amount) {
5412 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5413 SMLoc Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5414 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
5415 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
5416 return Error(Loc, "illegal shift operator");
5417 StringRef ShiftName = Tok.getString();
5418 if (ShiftName == "lsl" || ShiftName == "LSL" ||
5419 ShiftName == "asl" || ShiftName == "ASL")
5420 St = ARM_AM::lsl;
5421 else if (ShiftName == "lsr" || ShiftName == "LSR")
5422 St = ARM_AM::lsr;
5423 else if (ShiftName == "asr" || ShiftName == "ASR")
5424 St = ARM_AM::asr;
5425 else if (ShiftName == "ror" || ShiftName == "ROR")
5426 St = ARM_AM::ror;
5427 else if (ShiftName == "rrx" || ShiftName == "RRX")
5428 St = ARM_AM::rrx;
5429 else
5430 return Error(Loc, "illegal shift operator");
5431 Parser.Lex(); // Eat shift type token.
5432
5433 // rrx stands alone.
5434 Amount = 0;
5435 if (St != ARM_AM::rrx) {
5436 Loc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5437 // A '#' and a shift amount.
5438 const AsmToken &HashTok = Parser.getTok();
5439 if (HashTok.isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
5440 HashTok.isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
5441 return Error(HashTok.getLoc(), "'#' expected");
5442 Parser.Lex(); // Eat hash token.
5443
5444 const MCExpr *Expr;
5445 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr))
5446 return true;
5447 // Range check the immediate.
5448 // lsl, ror: 0 <= imm <= 31
5449 // lsr, asr: 0 <= imm <= 32
5450 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Expr);
5451 if (!CE)
5452 return Error(Loc, "shift amount must be an immediate");
5453 int64_t Imm = CE->getValue();
5454 if (Imm < 0 ||
5455 ((St == ARM_AM::lsl || St == ARM_AM::ror) && Imm > 31) ||
5456 ((St == ARM_AM::lsr || St == ARM_AM::asr) && Imm > 32))
5457 return Error(Loc, "immediate shift value out of range");
5458 // If <ShiftTy> #0, turn it into a no_shift.
5459 if (Imm == 0)
5460 St = ARM_AM::lsl;
5461 // For consistency, treat lsr #32 and asr #32 as having immediate value 0.
5462 if (Imm == 32)
5463 Imm = 0;
5464 Amount = Imm;
5465 }
5466
5467 return false;
5468}
5469
5470/// parseFPImm - A floating point immediate expression operand.
5471OperandMatchResultTy
5472ARMAsmParser::parseFPImm(OperandVector &Operands) {
5473 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5474 // Anything that can accept a floating point constant as an operand
5475 // needs to go through here, as the regular parseExpression is
5476 // integer only.
5477 //
5478 // This routine still creates a generic Immediate operand, containing
5479 // a bitcast of the 64-bit floating point value. The various operands
5480 // that accept floats can check whether the value is valid for them
5481 // via the standard is*() predicates.
5482
5483 SMLoc S = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
5484
5485 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
5486 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
5487 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5488
5489 // Disambiguate the VMOV forms that can accept an FP immediate.
5490 // vmov.f32 <sreg>, #imm
5491 // vmov.f64 <dreg>, #imm
5492 // vmov.f32 <dreg>, #imm @ vector f32x2
5493 // vmov.f32 <qreg>, #imm @ vector f32x4
5494 //
5495 // There are also the NEON VMOV instructions which expect an
5496 // integer constant. Make sure we don't try to parse an FPImm
5497 // for these:
5498 // vmov.i{8|16|32|64} <dreg|qreg>, #imm
5499 ARMOperand &TyOp = static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[2]);
5500 bool isVmovf = TyOp.isToken() &&
5501 (TyOp.getToken() == ".f32" || TyOp.getToken() == ".f64" ||
5502 TyOp.getToken() == ".f16");
5503 ARMOperand &Mnemonic = static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[0]);
5504 bool isFconst = Mnemonic.isToken() && (Mnemonic.getToken() == "fconstd" ||
5505 Mnemonic.getToken() == "fconsts");
5506 if (!(isVmovf || isFconst))
5507 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5508
5509 Parser.Lex(); // Eat '#' or '$'.
5510
5511 // Handle negation, as that still comes through as a separate token.
5512 bool isNegative = false;
5513 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
5514 isNegative = true;
5515 Parser.Lex();
5516 }
5517 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
5518 SMLoc Loc = Tok.getLoc();
5519 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Real) && isVmovf) {
5520 APFloat RealVal(APFloat::IEEEsingle(), Tok.getString());
5521 uint64_t IntVal = RealVal.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue();
5522 // If we had a '-' in front, toggle the sign bit.
5523 IntVal ^= (uint64_t)isNegative << 31;
5524 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the token.
5525 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateImm(
5526 MCConstantExpr::create(IntVal, getContext()),
5527 S, Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
5528 return MatchOperand_Success;
5529 }
5530 // Also handle plain integers. Instructions which allow floating point
5531 // immediates also allow a raw encoded 8-bit value.
5532 if (Tok.is(AsmToken::Integer) && isFconst) {
5533 int64_t Val = Tok.getIntVal();
5534 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the token.
5535 if (Val > 255 || Val < 0) {
5536 Error(Loc, "encoded floating point value out of range");
5537 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5538 }
5539 float RealVal = ARM_AM::getFPImmFloat(Val);
5540 Val = APFloat(RealVal).bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue();
5541
5542 Operands.push_back(ARMOperand::CreateImm(
5543 MCConstantExpr::create(Val, getContext()), S,
5544 Parser.getTok().getLoc()));
5545 return MatchOperand_Success;
5546 }
5547
5548 Error(Loc, "invalid floating point immediate");
5549 return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5550}
5551
5552/// Parse a arm instruction operand. For now this parses the operand regardless
5553/// of the mnemonic.
5554bool ARMAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Mnemonic) {
5555 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
5556 SMLoc S, E;
5557
5558 // Check if the current operand has a custom associated parser, if so, try to
5559 // custom parse the operand, or fallback to the general approach.
5560 OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic);
5561 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success)
5562 return false;
5563 // If there wasn't a custom match, try the generic matcher below. Otherwise,
5564 // there was a match, but an error occurred, in which case, just return that
5565 // the operand parsing failed.
5566 if (ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
5567 return true;
5568
5569 switch (getLexer().getKind()) {
5570 default:
