7331 case ARM::VLD3LNdWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3LNd8_UPD;
7332 case ARM::VLD3LNdWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3LNd16_UPD;
7333 case ARM::VLD3LNdWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3LNd32_UPD;
7334 case ARM::VLD3LNqWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3LNq16_UPD;
7335 case ARM::VLD3LNqWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3LNq32_UPD;
7336 case ARM::VLD3LNdAsm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3LNd8;
7337 case ARM::VLD3LNdAsm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3LNd16;
7338 case ARM::VLD3LNdAsm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3LNd32;
7339 case ARM::VLD3LNqAsm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3LNq16;
7340 case ARM::VLD3LNqAsm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3LNq32;
7341
7342 // VLD3
7343 case ARM::VLD3dWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d8_UPD;
7344 case ARM::VLD3dWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d16_UPD;
7345 case ARM::VLD3dWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d32_UPD;
7346 case ARM::VLD3qWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q8_UPD;
7347 case ARM::VLD3qWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q16_UPD;
7348 case ARM::VLD3qWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q32_UPD;
7349 case ARM::VLD3dWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d8_UPD;
7350 case ARM::VLD3dWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d16_UPD;
7351 case ARM::VLD3dWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d32_UPD;
7352 case ARM::VLD3qWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q8_UPD;
7353 case ARM::VLD3qWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q16_UPD;
7354 case ARM::VLD3qWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q32_UPD;
7355 case ARM::VLD3dAsm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d8;
7356 case ARM::VLD3dAsm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d16;
7357 case ARM::VLD3dAsm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD3d32;
7358 case ARM::VLD3qAsm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q8;
7359 case ARM::VLD3qAsm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q16;
7360 case ARM::VLD3qAsm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD3q32;
7361
7362 // VLD4LN
7363 case ARM::VLD4LNdWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd8_UPD;
7364 case ARM::VLD4LNdWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd16_UPD;
7365 case ARM::VLD4LNdWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd32_UPD;
7366 case ARM::VLD4LNqWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4LNq16_UPD;
7367 case ARM::VLD4LNqWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4LNq32_UPD;
7368 case ARM::VLD4LNdWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd8_UPD;
7369 case ARM::VLD4LNdWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd16_UPD;
7370 case ARM::VLD4LNdWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd32_UPD;
7371 case ARM::VLD4LNqWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4LNq16_UPD;
7372 case ARM::VLD4LNqWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4LNq32_UPD;
7373 case ARM::VLD4LNdAsm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd8;
7374 case ARM::VLD4LNdAsm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd16;
7375 case ARM::VLD4LNdAsm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4LNd32;
7376 case ARM::VLD4LNqAsm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4LNq16;
7377 case ARM::VLD4LNqAsm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4LNq32;
7378
7379 // VLD4DUP
7380 case ARM::VLD4DUPdWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd8_UPD;
7381 case ARM::VLD4DUPdWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd16_UPD;
7382 case ARM::VLD4DUPdWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd32_UPD;
7383 case ARM::VLD4DUPqWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPq8_UPD;
7384 case ARM::VLD4DUPqWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPq16_UPD;
7385 case ARM::VLD4DUPqWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq32_UPD;
7386 case ARM::VLD4DUPdWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd8_UPD;
7387 case ARM::VLD4DUPdWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd16_UPD;
7388 case ARM::VLD4DUPdWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd32_UPD;
7389 case ARM::VLD4DUPqWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq8_UPD;
7390 case ARM::VLD4DUPqWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq16_UPD;
7391 case ARM::VLD4DUPqWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq32_UPD;
7392 case ARM::VLD4DUPdAsm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd8;
7393 case ARM::VLD4DUPdAsm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd16;
7394 case ARM::VLD4DUPdAsm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4DUPd32;
7395 case ARM::VLD4DUPqAsm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq8;
7396 case ARM::VLD4DUPqAsm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq16;
7397 case ARM::VLD4DUPqAsm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4DUPq32;
7398
7399 // VLD4
7400 case ARM::VLD4dWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d8_UPD;
7401 case ARM::VLD4dWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d16_UPD;
7402 case ARM::VLD4dWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d32_UPD;
7403 case ARM::VLD4qWB_fixed_Asm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q8_UPD;
7404 case ARM::VLD4qWB_fixed_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q16_UPD;
7405 case ARM::VLD4qWB_fixed_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q32_UPD;
7406 case ARM::VLD4dWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d8_UPD;
7407 case ARM::VLD4dWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d16_UPD;
7408 case ARM::VLD4dWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d32_UPD;
7409 case ARM::VLD4qWB_register_Asm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q8_UPD;
7410 case ARM::VLD4qWB_register_Asm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q16_UPD;
7411 case ARM::VLD4qWB_register_Asm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q32_UPD;
7412 case ARM::VLD4dAsm_8: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d8;
7413 case ARM::VLD4dAsm_16: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d16;
7414 case ARM::VLD4dAsm_32: Spacing = 1; return ARM::VLD4d32;
7415 case ARM::VLD4qAsm_8: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q8;
7416 case ARM::VLD4qAsm_16: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q16;
7417 case ARM::VLD4qAsm_32: Spacing = 2; return ARM::VLD4q32;
7418 }
7419}
7420
7421bool ARMAsmParser::processInstruction(MCInst &Inst,
7422 const OperandVector &Operands,
7423 MCStreamer &Out) {
7424 // Check if we have the wide qualifier, because if it's present we
7425 // must avoid selecting a 16-bit thumb instruction.
7426 bool HasWideQualifier = false;
7427 for (auto &Op : Operands) {
7428 ARMOperand &ARMOp = static_cast<ARMOperand&>(*Op);
7429 if (ARMOp.isToken() && ARMOp.getToken() == ".w") {
7430 HasWideQualifier = true;
7431 break;
7432 }
7433 }
7434
7435 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
7436 // Alias for alternate form of 'ldr{,b}t Rt, [Rn], #imm' instruction.
7437 case ARM::LDRT_POST:
7438 case ARM::LDRBT_POST: {
7439 const unsigned Opcode =
7440 (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::LDRT_POST) ? ARM::LDRT_POST_IMM
7441 : ARM::LDRBT_POST_IMM;
7442 MCInst TmpInst;
7443 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode);
7444 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
7445 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
7446 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
7447 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0));
7448 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
7449 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
7450 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
7451 Inst = TmpInst;
7452 return true;
7453 }
7454 // Alias for alternate form of 'str{,b}t Rt, [Rn], #imm' instruction.
7455 case ARM::STRT_POST:
7456 case ARM::STRBT_POST: {
7457 const unsigned Opcode =
7458 (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::STRT_POST) ? ARM::STRT_POST_IMM
7459 : ARM::STRBT_POST_IMM;
7460 MCInst TmpInst;
7461 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opcode);
7462 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
7463 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
7464 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
7465 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0));
7466 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
7467 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
7468 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
7469 Inst = TmpInst;
7470 return true;
7471 }
7472 // Alias for alternate form of 'ADR Rd, #imm' instruction.
7473 case ARM::ADDri: {
7474 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() != ARM::PC ||
7475 Inst.getOperand(5).getReg() != 0 ||
7476 !(Inst.getOperand(2).isExpr() || Inst.getOperand(2).isImm()))
7477 return false;
7478 MCInst TmpInst;
7479 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::ADR);
7480 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
7481 if (Inst.getOperand(2).isImm()) {
7482 // Immediate (mod_imm) will be in its encoded form, we must unencode it
7483 // before passing it to the ADR instruction.
7484 unsigned Enc = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
7485 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(
7486 ARM_AM::rotr32(Enc & 0xFF, (Enc & 0xF00) >> 7)));
7487 } else {
7488 // Turn PC-relative expression into absolute expression.
7489 // Reading PC provides the start of the current instruction + 8 and
7490 // the transform to adr is biased by that.
7491 MCSymbol *Dot = getContext().createTempSymbol();
7492 Out.EmitLabel(Dot);
7493 const MCExpr *OpExpr = Inst.getOperand(2).getExpr();
7494 const MCExpr *InstPC = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Dot,
7495 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None,
7496 getContext());
7497 const MCExpr *Const8 = MCConstantExpr::create(8, getContext());
7498 const MCExpr *ReadPC = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(InstPC, Const8,
7499 getContext());
7500 const MCExpr *FixupAddr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(ReadPC, OpExpr,
7501 getContext());
7502 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(FixupAddr));
7503 }
7504 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
7505 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
7506 Inst = TmpInst;
7507 return true;
7508 }
7509 // Aliases for alternate PC+imm syntax of LDR instructions.
7510 case ARM::t2LDRpcrel:
7511 // Select the narrow version if the immediate will fit.
7512 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() > 0 &&
7513 Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() <= 0xff &&
7514 !HasWideQualifier)
7515 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::tLDRpci);
7516 else
7517 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDRpci);
7518 return true;
7519 case ARM::t2LDRBpcrel:
7520 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDRBpci);
7521 return true;
7522 case ARM::t2LDRHpcrel:
7523 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDRHpci);
7524 return true;
7525 case ARM::t2LDRSBpcrel:
7526 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDRSBpci);
7527 return true;
7528 case ARM::t2LDRSHpcrel:
7529 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDRSHpci);
7530 return true;
7531 case ARM::LDRConstPool:
7532 case ARM::tLDRConstPool:
7533 case ARM::t2LDRConstPool: {
7534 // Pseudo instruction ldr rt, =immediate is converted to a
7535 // MOV rt, immediate if immediate is known and representable
7536 // otherwise we create a constant pool entry that we load from.
7537 MCInst TmpInst;
7538 if (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::LDRConstPool)
7539 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::LDRi12);
7540 else if (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::tLDRConstPool)
7541 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::tLDRpci);
7542 else if (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2LDRConstPool)
7543 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDRpci);
7544 const ARMOperand &PoolOperand =
7545 (HasWideQualifier ?
7546 static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[4]) :
7547 static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[3]));
7548 const MCExpr *SubExprVal = PoolOperand.getConstantPoolImm();
7549 // If SubExprVal is a constant we may be able to use a MOV
7550 if (isa<MCConstantExpr>(SubExprVal) &&
7551 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != ARM::PC &&
7552 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != ARM::SP) {
7553 int64_t Value =
7554 (int64_t) (cast<MCConstantExpr>(SubExprVal))->getValue();
7555 bool UseMov = true;
7556 bool MovHasS = true;
7557 if (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::LDRConstPool) {
7558 // ARM Constant
7559 if (ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(Value) != -1) {
7560 Value = ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(Value);
7561 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::MOVi);
7562 }
7563 else if (ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(~Value) != -1) {
7564 Value = ARM_AM::getSOImmVal(~Value);
7565 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::MVNi);
7566 }
7567 else if (hasV6T2Ops() &&
7568 Value >=0 && Value < 65536) {
7569 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::MOVi16);
7570 MovHasS = false;
7571 }
7572 else
7573 UseMov = false;
7574 }
7575 else {
7576 // Thumb/Thumb2 Constant
7577 if (hasThumb2() &&
7578 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Value) != -1)
7579 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2MOVi);
7580 else if (hasThumb2() &&
7581 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(~Value) != -1) {
7582 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2MVNi);
7583 Value = ~Value;
7584 }
7585 else if (hasV8MBaseline() &&
7586 Value >=0 && Value < 65536) {
7587 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2MOVi16);
7588 MovHasS = false;
7589 }
7590 else
7591 UseMov = false;
7592 }
7593 if (UseMov) {
7594 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rt
7595 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Value)); // Immediate
7596 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
7597 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // CondCode
7598 if (MovHasS)
7599 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // S
7600 Inst = TmpInst;
7601 return true;
7602 }
7603 }
7604 // No opportunity to use MOV/MVN create constant pool
7605 const MCExpr *CPLoc =
7606 getTargetStreamer().addConstantPoolEntry(SubExprVal,
7607 PoolOperand.getStartLoc());
7608 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rt
7609 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(CPLoc)); // offset to constpool
7610 if (TmpInst.getOpcode() == ARM::LDRi12)
7611 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); // unused offset
7612 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
7613 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // CondCode
7614 Inst = TmpInst;
7615 return true;
7616 }
7617 // Handle NEON VST complex aliases.
7618 case ARM::VST1LNdWB_register_Asm_8:
7619 case ARM::VST1LNdWB_register_Asm_16:
7620 case ARM::VST1LNdWB_register_Asm_32: {
7621 MCInst TmpInst;
7622 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7623 // right place.
7624 unsigned Spacing;
7625 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7626 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7627 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7628 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7629 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rm
7630 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7631 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // lane
7632 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5)); // CondCode
7633 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(6));
7634 Inst = TmpInst;
7635 return true;
7636 }
7637
7638 case ARM::VST2LNdWB_register_Asm_8:
7639 case ARM::VST2LNdWB_register_Asm_16:
7640 case ARM::VST2LNdWB_register_Asm_32:
7641 case ARM::VST2LNqWB_register_Asm_16:
7642 case ARM::VST2LNqWB_register_Asm_32: {
7643 MCInst TmpInst;
7644 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7645 // right place.
7646 unsigned Spacing;
7647 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7648 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7649 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7650 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7651 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rm
7652 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7653 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7654 Spacing));
7655 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // lane
7656 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5)); // CondCode
7657 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(6));
7658 Inst = TmpInst;
7659 return true;
7660 }
7661
7662 case ARM::VST3LNdWB_register_Asm_8:
7663 case ARM::VST3LNdWB_register_Asm_16:
7664 case ARM::VST3LNdWB_register_Asm_32:
7665 case ARM::VST3LNqWB_register_Asm_16:
7666 case ARM::VST3LNqWB_register_Asm_32: {
7667 MCInst TmpInst;
7668 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7669 // right place.
7670 unsigned Spacing;
7671 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7672 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7673 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7674 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7675 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rm
7676 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7677 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7678 Spacing));
7679 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7680 Spacing * 2));
7681 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // lane
7682 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5)); // CondCode
7683 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(6));
7684 Inst = TmpInst;
7685 return true;
7686 }
7687
7688 case ARM::VST4LNdWB_register_Asm_8:
7689 case ARM::VST4LNdWB_register_Asm_16:
7690 case ARM::VST4LNdWB_register_Asm_32:
7691 case ARM::VST4LNqWB_register_Asm_16:
7692 case ARM::VST4LNqWB_register_Asm_32: {
7693 MCInst TmpInst;
7694 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7695 // right place.
7696 unsigned Spacing;
7697 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7698 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7699 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7700 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7701 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rm
7702 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7703 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7704 Spacing));
7705 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7706 Spacing * 2));
7707 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7708 Spacing * 3));
7709 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // lane
7710 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5)); // CondCode
7711 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(6));
7712 Inst = TmpInst;
7713 return true;
7714 }
7715
7716 case ARM::VST1LNdWB_fixed_Asm_8:
7717 case ARM::VST1LNdWB_fixed_Asm_16:
7718 case ARM::VST1LNdWB_fixed_Asm_32: {
7719 MCInst TmpInst;
7720 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7721 // right place.
7722 unsigned Spacing;
7723 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7724 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7725 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7726 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7727 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // Rm
7728 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7729 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // lane
7730 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // CondCode
7731 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
7732 Inst = TmpInst;
7733 return true;
7734 }
7735
7736 case ARM::VST2LNdWB_fixed_Asm_8:
7737 case ARM::VST2LNdWB_fixed_Asm_16:
7738 case ARM::VST2LNdWB_fixed_Asm_32:
7739 case ARM::VST2LNqWB_fixed_Asm_16:
7740 case ARM::VST2LNqWB_fixed_Asm_32: {
7741 MCInst TmpInst;
7742 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7743 // right place.
7744 unsigned Spacing;
7745 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7746 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7747 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7748 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7749 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // Rm
7750 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7751 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7752 Spacing));
7753 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // lane
7754 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // CondCode
7755 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
7756 Inst = TmpInst;
7757 return true;
7758 }
7759
7760 case ARM::VST3LNdWB_fixed_Asm_8:
7761 case ARM::VST3LNdWB_fixed_Asm_16:
7762 case ARM::VST3LNdWB_fixed_Asm_32:
7763 case ARM::VST3LNqWB_fixed_Asm_16:
7764 case ARM::VST3LNqWB_fixed_Asm_32: {
7765 MCInst TmpInst;
7766 // Shuffle the operands around so the lane index operand is in the
7767 // right place.
7768 unsigned Spacing;
7769 TmpInst.setOpcode(getRealVSTOpcode(Inst.getOpcode(), Spacing));
7770 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn_wb
7771 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rn
7772 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // alignment
7773 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // Rm
7774 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Vd
7775 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7776 Spacing));
7777 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() +
7778 Spacing * 2));

8682
8683 // Handle encoding choice for the shift-immediate instructions.
8684 case ARM::t2LSLri:
8685 case ARM::t2LSRri:
8686 case ARM::t2ASRri:
8687 if (isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
8688 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
8689 Inst.getOperand(5).getReg() == (inITBlock() ? 0 : ARM::CPSR) &&
8690 !HasWideQualifier) {
8691 unsigned NewOpc;
8692 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
8693 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode");
8694 case ARM::t2LSLri: NewOpc = ARM::tLSLri; break;
8695 case ARM::t2LSRri: NewOpc = ARM::tLSRri; break;
8696 case ARM::t2ASRri: NewOpc = ARM::tASRri; break;
8697 }
8698 // The Thumb1 operands aren't in the same order. Awesome, eh?
8699 MCInst TmpInst;
8700 TmpInst.setOpcode(NewOpc);
8701 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
8702 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
8703 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
8704 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
8705 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8706 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
8707 Inst = TmpInst;
8708 return true;
8709 }
8710 return false;
8711
8712 // Handle the Thumb2 mode MOV complex aliases.
8713 case ARM::t2MOVsr:
8714 case ARM::t2MOVSsr: {
8715 // Which instruction to expand to depends on the CCOut operand and
8716 // whether we're in an IT block if the register operands are low
8717 // registers.
8718 bool isNarrow = false;
8719 if (isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
8720 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
8721 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(2).getReg()) &&
8722 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() &&
8723 inITBlock() == (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVsr) &&
8724 !HasWideQualifier)
8725 isNarrow = true;
8726 MCInst TmpInst;
8727 unsigned newOpc;
8728 switch(ARM_AM::getSORegShOp(Inst.getOperand(3).getImm())) {
8729 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode!");
8730 case ARM_AM::asr: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tASRrr : ARM::t2ASRrr; break;
8731 case ARM_AM::lsr: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tLSRrr : ARM::t2LSRrr; break;
8732 case ARM_AM::lsl: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tLSLrr : ARM::t2LSLrr; break;
8733 case ARM_AM::ror: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tROR : ARM::t2RORrr; break;
8734 }
8735 TmpInst.setOpcode(newOpc);
8736 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rd
8737 if (isNarrow)
8738 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(
8739 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVSsr ? ARM::CPSR : 0));
8740 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8741 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rm
8742 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // CondCode
8743 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
8744 if (!isNarrow)
8745 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(
8746 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVSsr ? ARM::CPSR : 0));
8747 Inst = TmpInst;
8748 return true;
8749 }
8750 case ARM::t2MOVsi:
8751 case ARM::t2MOVSsi: {
8752 // Which instruction to expand to depends on the CCOut operand and
8753 // whether we're in an IT block if the register operands are low
8754 // registers.
8755 bool isNarrow = false;
8756 if (isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
8757 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
8758 inITBlock() == (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVsi) &&
8759 !HasWideQualifier)
8760 isNarrow = true;
8761 MCInst TmpInst;
8762 unsigned newOpc;
8763 unsigned Shift = ARM_AM::getSORegShOp(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm());
8764 unsigned Amount = ARM_AM::getSORegOffset(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm());
8765 bool isMov = false;
8766 // MOV rd, rm, LSL #0 is actually a MOV instruction
8767 if (Shift == ARM_AM::lsl && Amount == 0) {
8768 isMov = true;
8769 // The 16-bit encoding of MOV rd, rm, LSL #N is explicitly encoding T2 of
8770 // MOV (register) in the ARMv8-A and ARMv8-M manuals, and immediate 0 is
8771 // unpredictable in an IT block so the 32-bit encoding T3 has to be used
8772 // instead.
8773 if (inITBlock()) {
8774 isNarrow = false;
8775 }
8776 newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tMOVSr : ARM::t2MOVr;
8777 } else {
8778 switch(Shift) {
8779 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode!");
8780 case ARM_AM::asr: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tASRri : ARM::t2ASRri; break;
8781 case ARM_AM::lsr: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tLSRri : ARM::t2LSRri; break;
8782 case ARM_AM::lsl: newOpc = isNarrow ? ARM::tLSLri : ARM::t2LSLri; break;
8783 case ARM_AM::ror: newOpc = ARM::t2RORri; isNarrow = false; break;
8784 case ARM_AM::rrx: isNarrow = false; newOpc = ARM::t2RRX; break;
8785 }
8786 }
8787 if (Amount == 32) Amount = 0;
8788 TmpInst.setOpcode(newOpc);
8789 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rd
8790 if (isNarrow && !isMov)
8791 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(
8792 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVSsi ? ARM::CPSR : 0));
8793 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8794 if (newOpc != ARM::t2RRX && !isMov)
8795 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Amount));
8796 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // CondCode
8797 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
8798 if (!isNarrow)
8799 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(
8800 Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVSsi ? ARM::CPSR : 0));
8801 Inst = TmpInst;
8802 return true;
8803 }
8804 // Handle the ARM mode MOV complex aliases.
8805 case ARM::ASRr:
8806 case ARM::LSRr:
8807 case ARM::LSLr:
8808 case ARM::RORr: {
8809 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy;
8810 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
8811 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode!");
8812 case ARM::ASRr: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::asr; break;
8813 case ARM::LSRr: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::lsr; break;
8814 case ARM::LSLr: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::lsl; break;
8815 case ARM::RORr: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::ror; break;
8816 }
8817 unsigned Shifter = ARM_AM::getSORegOpc(ShiftTy, 0);
8818 MCInst TmpInst;
8819 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::MOVsr);
8820 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rd
8821 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8822 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // Rm
8823 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Shifter)); // Shift value and ty
8824 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // CondCode
8825 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
8826 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5)); // cc_out
8827 Inst = TmpInst;
8828 return true;
8829 }
8830 case ARM::ASRi:
8831 case ARM::LSRi:
8832 case ARM::LSLi:
8833 case ARM::RORi: {
8834 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc ShiftTy;
8835 switch(Inst.getOpcode()) {
8836 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode!");
8837 case ARM::ASRi: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::asr; break;
8838 case ARM::LSRi: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::lsr; break;
8839 case ARM::LSLi: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::lsl; break;
8840 case ARM::RORi: ShiftTy = ARM_AM::ror; break;
8841 }
8842 // A shift by zero is a plain MOVr, not a MOVsi.
8843 unsigned Amt = Inst.getOperand(2).getImm();
8844 unsigned Opc = Amt == 0 ? ARM::MOVr : ARM::MOVsi;
8845 // A shift by 32 should be encoded as 0 when permitted
8846 if (Amt == 32 && (ShiftTy == ARM_AM::lsr || ShiftTy == ARM_AM::asr))
8847 Amt = 0;
8848 unsigned Shifter = ARM_AM::getSORegOpc(ShiftTy, Amt);
8849 MCInst TmpInst;
8850 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opc);
8851 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rd
8852 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8853 if (Opc == ARM::MOVsi)
8854 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Shifter)); // Shift value and ty
8855 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3)); // CondCode
8856 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
8857 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5)); // cc_out
8858 Inst = TmpInst;
8859 return true;
8860 }
8861 case ARM::RRXi: {
8862 unsigned Shifter = ARM_AM::getSORegOpc(ARM_AM::rrx, 0);
8863 MCInst TmpInst;
8864 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::MOVsi);
8865 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rd
8866 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8867 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Shifter)); // Shift value and ty
8868 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
8869 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8870 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // cc_out
8871 Inst = TmpInst;
8872 return true;
8873 }
8874 case ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD: {
8875 // If this is a load of a single register, then we should use
8876 // a post-indexed LDR instruction instead, per the ARM ARM.
8877 if (Inst.getNumOperands() != 5)
8878 return false;
8879 MCInst TmpInst;
8880 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDR_POST);
8881 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rt
8882 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rn_wb
8883 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8884 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(4));
8885 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
8886 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8887 Inst = TmpInst;
8888 return true;
8889 }
8890 case ARM::t2STMDB_UPD: {
8891 // If this is a store of a single register, then we should use
8892 // a pre-indexed STR instruction instead, per the ARM ARM.
8893 if (Inst.getNumOperands() != 5)
8894 return false;
8895 MCInst TmpInst;
8896 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::t2STR_PRE);
8897 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rn_wb
8898 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rt
8899 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8900 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(-4));
8901 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
8902 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8903 Inst = TmpInst;
8904 return true;
8905 }
8906 case ARM::LDMIA_UPD:
8907 // If this is a load of a single register via a 'pop', then we should use
8908 // a post-indexed LDR instruction instead, per the ARM ARM.
8909 if (static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[0]).getToken() == "pop" &&
8910 Inst.getNumOperands() == 5) {
8911 MCInst TmpInst;
8912 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::LDR_POST_IMM);
8913 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rt
8914 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rn_wb
8915 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // Rn
8916 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // am2offset
8917 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(4));
8918 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
8919 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8920 Inst = TmpInst;
8921 return true;
8922 }
8923 break;
8924 case ARM::STMDB_UPD:
8925 // If this is a store of a single register via a 'push', then we should use
8926 // a pre-indexed STR instruction instead, per the ARM ARM.
8927 if (static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[0]).getToken() == "push" &&
8928 Inst.getNumOperands() == 5) {
8929 MCInst TmpInst;
8930 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::STR_PRE_IMM);
8931 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0)); // Rn_wb
8932 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4)); // Rt
8933 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1)); // addrmode_imm12
8934 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(-4));
8935 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2)); // CondCode
8936 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8937 Inst = TmpInst;
8938 }
8939 break;
8940 case ARM::t2ADDri12:
8941 // If the immediate fits for encoding T3 (t2ADDri) and the generic "add"
8942 // mnemonic was used (not "addw"), encoding T3 is preferred.
8943 if (static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[0]).getToken() != "add" ||
8944 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm()) == -1)
8945 break;
8946 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2ADDri);
8947 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // cc_out
8948 break;
8949 case ARM::t2SUBri12:
8950 // If the immediate fits for encoding T3 (t2SUBri) and the generic "sub"
8951 // mnemonic was used (not "subw"), encoding T3 is preferred.
8952 if (static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[0]).getToken() != "sub" ||
8953 ARM_AM::getT2SOImmVal(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm()) == -1)
8954 break;
8955 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2SUBri);
8956 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // cc_out
8957 break;
8958 case ARM::tADDi8:
8959 // If the immediate is in the range 0-7, we want tADDi3 iff Rd was
8960 // explicitly specified. From the ARM ARM: "Encoding T1 is preferred
8961 // to encoding T2 if <Rd> is specified and encoding T2 is preferred
8962 // to encoding T1 if <Rd> is omitted."
8963 if ((unsigned)Inst.getOperand(3).getImm() < 8 && Operands.size() == 6) {
8964 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::tADDi3);
8965 return true;
8966 }
8967 break;
8968 case ARM::tSUBi8:
8969 // If the immediate is in the range 0-7, we want tADDi3 iff Rd was
8970 // explicitly specified. From the ARM ARM: "Encoding T1 is preferred
8971 // to encoding T2 if <Rd> is specified and encoding T2 is preferred
8972 // to encoding T1 if <Rd> is omitted."
8973 if ((unsigned)Inst.getOperand(3).getImm() < 8 && Operands.size() == 6) {
8974 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::tSUBi3);
8975 return true;
8976 }
8977 break;
8978 case ARM::t2ADDri:
8979 case ARM::t2SUBri: {
8980 // If the destination and first source operand are the same, and
8981 // the flags are compatible with the current IT status, use encoding T2
8982 // instead of T3. For compatibility with the system 'as'. Make sure the
8983 // wide encoding wasn't explicit.
8984 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() ||
8985 !isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) ||
8986 (Inst.getOperand(2).isImm() &&
8987 (unsigned)Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() > 255) ||
8988 Inst.getOperand(5).getReg() != (inITBlock() ? 0 : ARM::CPSR) ||
8989 HasWideQualifier)
8990 break;
8991 MCInst TmpInst;
8992 TmpInst.setOpcode(Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2ADDri ?
8993 ARM::tADDi8 : ARM::tSUBi8);
8994 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
8995 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
8996 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
8997 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
8998 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
8999 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9000 Inst = TmpInst;
9001 return true;
9002 }
9003 case ARM::t2ADDrr: {
9004 // If the destination and first source operand are the same, and
9005 // there's no setting of the flags, use encoding T2 instead of T3.
9006 // Note that this is only for ADD, not SUB. This mirrors the system
9007 // 'as' behaviour. Also take advantage of ADD being commutative.
9008 // Make sure the wide encoding wasn't explicit.
9009 bool Swap = false;
9010 auto DestReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
9011 bool Transform = DestReg == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg();
9012 if (!Transform && DestReg == Inst.getOperand(2).getReg()) {
9013 Transform = true;
9014 Swap = true;
9015 }
9016 if (!Transform ||
9017 Inst.getOperand(5).getReg() != 0 ||
9018 HasWideQualifier)
9019 break;
9020 MCInst TmpInst;
9021 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::tADDhirr);
9022 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9023 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9024 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(Swap ? 1 : 2));
9025 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9026 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9027 Inst = TmpInst;
9028 return true;
9029 }
9030 case ARM::tADDrSP:
9031 // If the non-SP source operand and the destination operand are not the
9032 // same, we need to use the 32-bit encoding if it's available.
9033 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() != Inst.getOperand(2).getReg()) {
9034 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2ADDrr);
9035 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); // cc_out
9036 return true;
9037 }
9038 break;
9039 case ARM::tB:
9040 // A Thumb conditional branch outside of an IT block is a tBcc.
9041 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() != ARMCC::AL && !inITBlock()) {
9042 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::tBcc);
9043 return true;
9044 }
9045 break;
9046 case ARM::t2B:
9047 // A Thumb2 conditional branch outside of an IT block is a t2Bcc.
9048 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() != ARMCC::AL && !inITBlock()){
9049 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2Bcc);
9050 return true;
9051 }
9052 break;
9053 case ARM::t2Bcc:
9054 // If the conditional is AL or we're in an IT block, we really want t2B.
9055 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() == ARMCC::AL || inITBlock()) {
9056 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2B);
9057 return true;
9058 }
9059 break;
9060 case ARM::tBcc:
9061 // If the conditional is AL, we really want tB.
9062 if (Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() == ARMCC::AL) {
9063 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::tB);
9064 return true;
9065 }
9066 break;
9067 case ARM::tLDMIA: {
9068 // If the register list contains any high registers, or if the writeback
9069 // doesn't match what tLDMIA can do, we need to use the 32-bit encoding
9070 // instead if we're in Thumb2. Otherwise, this should have generated
9071 // an error in validateInstruction().
9072 unsigned Rn = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
9073 bool hasWritebackToken =
9074 (static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[3]).isToken() &&
9075 static_cast<ARMOperand &>(*Operands[3]).getToken() == "!");
9076 bool listContainsBase;
9077 if (checkLowRegisterList(Inst, 3, Rn, 0, listContainsBase) ||
9078 (!listContainsBase && !hasWritebackToken) ||
9079 (listContainsBase && hasWritebackToken)) {
9080 // 16-bit encoding isn't sufficient. Switch to the 32-bit version.
9081 assert(isThumbTwo());
9082 Inst.setOpcode(hasWritebackToken ? ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD : ARM::t2LDMIA);
9083 // If we're switching to the updating version, we need to insert
9084 // the writeback tied operand.
9085 if (hasWritebackToken)
9086 Inst.insert(Inst.begin(),
9087 MCOperand::createReg(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()));
9088 return true;
9089 }
9090 break;
9091 }
9092 case ARM::tSTMIA_UPD: {
9093 // If the register list contains any high registers, we need to use
9094 // the 32-bit encoding instead if we're in Thumb2. Otherwise, this
9095 // should have generated an error in validateInstruction().
9096 unsigned Rn = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
9097 bool listContainsBase;
9098 if (checkLowRegisterList(Inst, 4, Rn, 0, listContainsBase)) {
9099 // 16-bit encoding isn't sufficient. Switch to the 32-bit version.
9100 assert(isThumbTwo());
9101 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2STMIA_UPD);
9102 return true;
9103 }
9104 break;
9105 }
9106 case ARM::tPOP: {
9107 bool listContainsBase;
9108 // If the register list contains any high registers, we need to use
9109 // the 32-bit encoding instead if we're in Thumb2. Otherwise, this
9110 // should have generated an error in validateInstruction().
9111 if (!checkLowRegisterList(Inst, 2, 0, ARM::PC, listContainsBase))
9112 return false;
9113 assert(isThumbTwo());
9114 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2LDMIA_UPD);
9115 // Add the base register and writeback operands.
9116 Inst.insert(Inst.begin(), MCOperand::createReg(ARM::SP));
9117 Inst.insert(Inst.begin(), MCOperand::createReg(ARM::SP));
9118 return true;
9119 }
9120 case ARM::tPUSH: {
9121 bool listContainsBase;
9122 if (!checkLowRegisterList(Inst, 2, 0, ARM::LR, listContainsBase))
9123 return false;
9124 assert(isThumbTwo());
9125 Inst.setOpcode(ARM::t2STMDB_UPD);
9126 // Add the base register and writeback operands.
9127 Inst.insert(Inst.begin(), MCOperand::createReg(ARM::SP));
9128 Inst.insert(Inst.begin(), MCOperand::createReg(ARM::SP));
9129 return true;
9130 }
9131 case ARM::t2MOVi:
9132 // If we can use the 16-bit encoding and the user didn't explicitly
9133 // request the 32-bit variant, transform it here.
9134 if (isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
9135 (Inst.getOperand(1).isImm() &&
9136 (unsigned)Inst.getOperand(1).getImm() <= 255) &&
9137 Inst.getOperand(4).getReg() == (inITBlock() ? 0 : ARM::CPSR) &&
9138 !HasWideQualifier) {
9139 // The operands aren't in the same order for tMOVi8...
9140 MCInst TmpInst;
9141 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::tMOVi8);
9142 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9143 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9144 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9145 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
9146 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9147 Inst = TmpInst;
9148 return true;
9149 }
9150 break;
9151
9152 case ARM::t2MOVr:
9153 // If we can use the 16-bit encoding and the user didn't explicitly
9154 // request the 32-bit variant, transform it here.
9155 if (isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
9156 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
9157 Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() == ARMCC::AL &&
9158 Inst.getOperand(4).getReg() == ARM::CPSR &&
9159 !HasWideQualifier) {
9160 // The operands aren't the same for tMOV[S]r... (no cc_out)
9161 MCInst TmpInst;
9162 TmpInst.setOpcode(Inst.getOperand(4).getReg() ? ARM::tMOVSr : ARM::tMOVr);
9163 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9164 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9165 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
9166 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9167 Inst = TmpInst;
9168 return true;
9169 }
9170 break;
9171
9172 case ARM::t2SXTH:
9173 case ARM::t2SXTB:
9174 case ARM::t2UXTH:
9175 case ARM::t2UXTB:
9176 // If we can use the 16-bit encoding and the user didn't explicitly
9177 // request the 32-bit variant, transform it here.
9178 if (isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
9179 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
9180 Inst.getOperand(2).getImm() == 0 &&
9181 !HasWideQualifier) {
9182 unsigned NewOpc;
9183 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
9184 default: llvm_unreachable("Illegal opcode!");
9185 case ARM::t2SXTH: NewOpc = ARM::tSXTH; break;
9186 case ARM::t2SXTB: NewOpc = ARM::tSXTB; break;
9187 case ARM::t2UXTH: NewOpc = ARM::tUXTH; break;
9188 case ARM::t2UXTB: NewOpc = ARM::tUXTB; break;
9189 }
9190 // The operands aren't the same for thumb1 (no rotate operand).
9191 MCInst TmpInst;
9192 TmpInst.setOpcode(NewOpc);
9193 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9194 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9195 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9196 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9197 Inst = TmpInst;
9198 return true;
9199 }
9200 break;
9201
9202 case ARM::MOVsi: {
9203 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc SOpc = ARM_AM::getSORegShOp(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm());
9204 // rrx shifts and asr/lsr of #32 is encoded as 0
9205 if (SOpc == ARM_AM::rrx || SOpc == ARM_AM::asr || SOpc == ARM_AM::lsr)
9206 return false;
9207 if (ARM_AM::getSORegOffset(Inst.getOperand(2).getImm()) == 0) {
9208 // Shifting by zero is accepted as a vanilla 'MOVr'
9209 MCInst TmpInst;
9210 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::MOVr);
9211 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9212 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9213 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9214 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9215 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
9216 Inst = TmpInst;
9217 return true;
9218 }
9219 return false;
9220 }
9221 case ARM::ANDrsi:
9222 case ARM::ORRrsi:
9223 case ARM::EORrsi:
9224 case ARM::BICrsi:
9225 case ARM::SUBrsi:
9226 case ARM::ADDrsi: {
9227 unsigned newOpc;
9228 ARM_AM::ShiftOpc SOpc = ARM_AM::getSORegShOp(Inst.getOperand(3).getImm());
9229 if (SOpc == ARM_AM::rrx) return false;
9230 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
9231 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode!");
9232 case ARM::ANDrsi: newOpc = ARM::ANDrr; break;
9233 case ARM::ORRrsi: newOpc = ARM::ORRrr; break;
9234 case ARM::EORrsi: newOpc = ARM::EORrr; break;
9235 case ARM::BICrsi: newOpc = ARM::BICrr; break;
9236 case ARM::SUBrsi: newOpc = ARM::SUBrr; break;
9237 case ARM::ADDrsi: newOpc = ARM::ADDrr; break;
9238 }
9239 // If the shift is by zero, use the non-shifted instruction definition.
9240 // The exception is for right shifts, where 0 == 32
9241 if (ARM_AM::getSORegOffset(Inst.getOperand(3).getImm()) == 0 &&
9242 !(SOpc == ARM_AM::lsr || SOpc == ARM_AM::asr)) {
9243 MCInst TmpInst;
9244 TmpInst.setOpcode(newOpc);
9245 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9246 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9247 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
9248 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9249 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
9250 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(6));
9251 Inst = TmpInst;
9252 return true;
9253 }
9254 return false;
9255 }
9256 case ARM::ITasm:
9257 case ARM::t2IT: {
9258 // Set up the IT block state according to the IT instruction we just
9259 // matched.
9260 assert(!inITBlock() && "nested IT blocks?!");
9261 startExplicitITBlock(ARMCC::CondCodes(Inst.getOperand(0).getImm()),
9262 Inst.getOperand(1).getImm());
9263 break;
9264 }
9265 case ARM::t2LSLrr:
9266 case ARM::t2LSRrr:
9267 case ARM::t2ASRrr:
9268 case ARM::t2SBCrr:
9269 case ARM::t2RORrr:
9270 case ARM::t2BICrr:
9271 // Assemblers should use the narrow encodings of these instructions when permissible.
9272 if ((isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
9273 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(2).getReg())) &&
9274 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() &&
9275 Inst.getOperand(5).getReg() == (inITBlock() ? 0 : ARM::CPSR) &&
9276 !HasWideQualifier) {
9277 unsigned NewOpc;
9278 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
9279 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode");
9280 case ARM::t2LSLrr: NewOpc = ARM::tLSLrr; break;
9281 case ARM::t2LSRrr: NewOpc = ARM::tLSRrr; break;
9282 case ARM::t2ASRrr: NewOpc = ARM::tASRrr; break;
9283 case ARM::t2SBCrr: NewOpc = ARM::tSBC; break;
9284 case ARM::t2RORrr: NewOpc = ARM::tROR; break;
9285 case ARM::t2BICrr: NewOpc = ARM::tBIC; break;
9286 }
9287 MCInst TmpInst;
9288 TmpInst.setOpcode(NewOpc);
9289 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9290 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
9291 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9292 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
9293 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9294 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9295 Inst = TmpInst;
9296 return true;
9297 }
9298 return false;
9299
9300 case ARM::t2ANDrr:
9301 case ARM::t2EORrr:
9302 case ARM::t2ADCrr:
9303 case ARM::t2ORRrr:
9304 // Assemblers should use the narrow encodings of these instructions when permissible.
9305 // These instructions are special in that they are commutable, so shorter encodings
9306 // are available more often.
9307 if ((isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
9308 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(2).getReg())) &&
9309 (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() ||
9310 Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(2).getReg()) &&
9311 Inst.getOperand(5).getReg() == (inITBlock() ? 0 : ARM::CPSR) &&
9312 !HasWideQualifier) {
9313 unsigned NewOpc;
9314 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
9315 default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected opcode");
9316 case ARM::t2ADCrr: NewOpc = ARM::tADC; break;
9317 case ARM::t2ANDrr: NewOpc = ARM::tAND; break;
9318 case ARM::t2EORrr: NewOpc = ARM::tEOR; break;
9319 case ARM::t2ORRrr: NewOpc = ARM::tORR; break;
9320 }
9321 MCInst TmpInst;
9322 TmpInst.setOpcode(NewOpc);
9323 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
9324 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(5));
9325 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) {
9326 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9327 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
9328 } else {
9329 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(2));
9330 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(1));
9331 }
9332 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(3));
9333 TmpInst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(4));
9334 Inst = TmpInst;
9335 return true;
9336 }
9337 return false;
9338 }
9339 return false;
9340}
9341
9342unsigned ARMAsmParser::checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) {
9343 // 16-bit thumb arithmetic instructions either require or preclude the 'S'
9344 // suffix depending on whether they're in an IT block or not.
9345 unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
9346 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Opc);
9347 if (MCID.TSFlags & ARMII::ThumbArithFlagSetting) {
9348 assert(MCID.hasOptionalDef() &&
9349 "optionally flag setting instruction missing optional def operand");
9350 assert(MCID.NumOperands == Inst.getNumOperands() &&
9351 "operand count mismatch!");
9352 // Find the optional-def operand (cc_out).
9353 unsigned OpNo;
9354 for (OpNo = 0;
9355 !MCID.OpInfo[OpNo].isOptionalDef() && OpNo < MCID.NumOperands;
9356 ++OpNo)
9357 ;
9358 // If we're parsing Thumb1, reject it completely.
9359 if (isThumbOne() && Inst.getOperand(OpNo).getReg() != ARM::CPSR)
9360 return Match_RequiresFlagSetting;
9361 // If we're parsing Thumb2, which form is legal depends on whether we're
9362 // in an IT block.
9363 if (isThumbTwo() && Inst.getOperand(OpNo).getReg() != ARM::CPSR &&
9364 !inITBlock())
9365 return Match_RequiresITBlock;
9366 if (isThumbTwo() && Inst.getOperand(OpNo).getReg() == ARM::CPSR &&
9367 inITBlock())
9368 return Match_RequiresNotITBlock;
9369 // LSL with zero immediate is not allowed in an IT block
9370 if (Opc == ARM::tLSLri && Inst.getOperand(3).getImm() == 0 && inITBlock())
9371 return Match_RequiresNotITBlock;
9372 } else if (isThumbOne()) {
9373 // Some high-register supporting Thumb1 encodings only allow both registers
9374 // to be from r0-r7 when in Thumb2.
9375 if (Opc == ARM::tADDhirr && !hasV6MOps() &&
9376 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()) &&
9377 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(2).getReg()))
9378 return Match_RequiresThumb2;
9379 // Others only require ARMv6 or later.
9380 else if (Opc == ARM::tMOVr && !hasV6Ops() &&
9381 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(0).getReg()) &&
9382 isARMLowRegister(Inst.getOperand(1).getReg()))
9383 return Match_RequiresV6;
9384 }
9385
9386 // Before ARMv8 the rules for when SP is allowed in t2MOVr are more complex
9387 // than the loop below can handle, so it uses the GPRnopc register class and
9388 // we do SP handling here.
9389 if (Opc == ARM::t2MOVr && !hasV8Ops())
9390 {
9391 // SP as both source and destination is not allowed
9392 if (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == ARM::SP &&
9393 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == ARM::SP)
9394 return Match_RequiresV8;
9395 // When flags-setting SP as either source or destination is not allowed
9396 if (Inst.getOperand(4).getReg() == ARM::CPSR &&
9397 (Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == ARM::SP ||
9398 Inst.getOperand(1).getReg() == ARM::SP))
9399 return Match_RequiresV8;
9400 }
9401
9402 switch (Inst.getOpcode()) {
9403 case ARM::VMRS:
9404 case ARM::VMSR:
9405 case ARM::VMRS_FPCXTS:
9406 case ARM::VMRS_FPCXTNS:
9407 case ARM::VMSR_FPCXTS:
9408 case ARM::VMSR_FPCXTNS:
9409 case ARM::VMRS_FPSCR_NZCVQC:
9410 case ARM::VMSR_FPSCR_NZCVQC:
9411 case ARM::FMSTAT:
9412 case ARM::VMRS_VPR:
9413 case ARM::VMRS_P0:
9414 case ARM::VMSR_VPR:
9415 case ARM::VMSR_P0:
9416 // Use of SP for VMRS/VMSR is only allowed in ARM mode with the exception of
9417 // ARMv8-A.
9418 if (Inst.getOperand(0).isReg() && Inst.getOperand(0).getReg() == ARM::SP &&
9419 (isThumb() && !hasV8Ops()))
9420 return Match_InvalidOperand;
9421 break;
9422 default:
9423 break;
9424 }
9425
9426 for (unsigned I = 0; I < MCID.NumOperands; ++I)
9427 if (MCID.OpInfo[I].RegClass == ARM::rGPRRegClassID) {
9428 // rGPRRegClass excludes PC, and also excluded SP before ARMv8
9429 if ((Inst.getOperand(I).getReg() == ARM::SP) && !hasV8Ops())
9430 return Match_RequiresV8;
9431 else if (Inst.getOperand(I).getReg() == ARM::PC)
9432 return Match_InvalidOperand;
9433 }
9434
9435 return Match_Success;
9436}
9437
9438namespace llvm {
9439
9440template <> inline bool IsCPSRDead<MCInst>(const MCInst *Instr) {
9441 return true; // In an assembly source, no need to second-guess
9442}
9443
9444} // end namespace llvm
9445
9446// Returns true if Inst is unpredictable if it is in and IT block, but is not
9447// the last instruction in the block.
9448bool ARMAsmParser::isITBlockTerminator(MCInst &Inst) const {
9449 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
9450
9451 // All branch & call instructions terminate IT blocks with the exception of
9452 // SVC.
9453 if (MCID.isTerminator() || (MCID.isCall() && Inst.getOpcode() != ARM::tSVC) ||
9454 MCID.isReturn() || MCID.isBranch() || MCID.isIndirectBranch())
9455 return true;
9456
9457 // Any arithmetic instruction which writes to the PC also terminates the IT
9458 // block.
9459 if (MCID.hasDefOfPhysReg(Inst, ARM::PC, *MRI))
9460 return true;
9461
9462 return false;
9463}
9464
9465unsigned ARMAsmParser::MatchInstruction(OperandVector &Operands, MCInst &Inst,
9466 SmallVectorImpl<NearMissInfo> &NearMisses,
9467 bool MatchingInlineAsm,
9468 bool &EmitInITBlock,
9469 MCStreamer &Out) {
9470 // If we can't use an implicit IT block here, just match as normal.
9471 if (inExplicitITBlock() || !isThumbTwo() || !useImplicitITThumb())
9472 return MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, &NearMisses, MatchingInlineAsm);
9473
9474 // Try to match the instruction in an extension of the current IT block (if
9475 // there is one).
9476 if (inImplicitITBlock()) {
9477 extendImplicitITBlock(ITState.Cond);
9478 if (MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, nullptr, MatchingInlineAsm) ==
9479 Match_Success) {
9480 // The match succeded, but we still have to check that the instruction is
9481 // valid in this implicit IT block.
9482 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
9483 if (MCID.isPredicable()) {
9484 ARMCC::CondCodes InstCond =
9485 (ARMCC::CondCodes)Inst.getOperand(MCID.findFirstPredOperandIdx())
9486 .getImm();
9487 ARMCC::CondCodes ITCond = currentITCond();
9488 if (InstCond == ITCond) {
9489 EmitInITBlock = true;
9490 return Match_Success;
9491 } else if (InstCond == ARMCC::getOppositeCondition(ITCond)) {
9492 invertCurrentITCondition();
9493 EmitInITBlock = true;
9494 return Match_Success;
9495 }
9496 }
9497 }
9498 rewindImplicitITPosition();
9499 }
9500
9501 // Finish the current IT block, and try to match outside any IT block.
9502 flushPendingInstructions(Out);
9503 unsigned PlainMatchResult =
9504 MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, &NearMisses, MatchingInlineAsm);
9505 if (PlainMatchResult == Match_Success) {
9506 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
9507 if (MCID.isPredicable()) {
9508 ARMCC::CondCodes InstCond =
9509 (ARMCC::CondCodes)Inst.getOperand(MCID.findFirstPredOperandIdx())
9510 .getImm();
9511 // Some forms of the branch instruction have their own condition code
9512 // fields, so can be conditionally executed without an IT block.
9513 if (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::tBcc || Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::t2Bcc) {
9514 EmitInITBlock = false;
9515 return Match_Success;
9516 }
9517 if (InstCond == ARMCC::AL) {
9518 EmitInITBlock = false;
9519 return Match_Success;
9520 }
9521 } else {
9522 EmitInITBlock = false;
9523 return Match_Success;
9524 }
9525 }
9526
9527 // Try to match in a new IT block. The matcher doesn't check the actual
9528 // condition, so we create an IT block with a dummy condition, and fix it up
9529 // once we know the actual condition.
9530 startImplicitITBlock();
9531 if (MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, nullptr, MatchingInlineAsm) ==
9532 Match_Success) {
9533 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
9534 if (MCID.isPredicable()) {
9535 ITState.Cond =
9536 (ARMCC::CondCodes)Inst.getOperand(MCID.findFirstPredOperandIdx())
9537 .getImm();
9538 EmitInITBlock = true;
9539 return Match_Success;
9540 }
9541 }
9542 discardImplicitITBlock();
9543
9544 // If none of these succeed, return the error we got when trying to match
9545 // outside any IT blocks.
9546 EmitInITBlock = false;
9547 return PlainMatchResult;
9548}
9549
9550static std::string ARMMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS,
9551 unsigned VariantID = 0);
9552
9553static const char *getSubtargetFeatureName(uint64_t Val);
9554bool ARMAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode,
9555 OperandVector &Operands,
9556 MCStreamer &Out, uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
9557 bool MatchingInlineAsm) {
9558 MCInst Inst;
9559 unsigned MatchResult;
9560 bool PendConditionalInstruction = false;
9561
9562 SmallVector<NearMissInfo, 4> NearMisses;
9563 MatchResult = MatchInstruction(Operands, Inst, NearMisses, MatchingInlineAsm,
9564 PendConditionalInstruction, Out);
9565
9566 switch (MatchResult) {
9567 case Match_Success:
9568 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Parsed as: ";
9569 Inst.dump_pretty(dbgs(), MII.getName(Inst.getOpcode()));
9570 dbgs() << "\n");
9571
9572 // Context sensitive operand constraints aren't handled by the matcher,
9573 // so check them here.
9574 if (validateInstruction(Inst, Operands)) {
9575 // Still progress the IT block, otherwise one wrong condition causes
9576 // nasty cascading errors.
9577 forwardITPosition();
9578 return true;
9579 }
9580
9581 { // processInstruction() updates inITBlock state, we need to save it away
9582 bool wasInITBlock = inITBlock();
9583
9584 // Some instructions need post-processing to, for example, tweak which
9585 // encoding is selected. Loop on it while changes happen so the
9586 // individual transformations can chain off each other. E.g.,
9587 // tPOP(r8)->t2LDMIA_UPD(sp,r8)->t2STR_POST(sp,r8)
9588 while (processInstruction(Inst, Operands, Out))
9589 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Changed to: ";
9590 Inst.dump_pretty(dbgs(), MII.getName(Inst.getOpcode()));
9591 dbgs() << "\n");
9592
9593 // Only after the instruction is fully processed, we can validate it
9594 if (wasInITBlock && hasV8Ops() && isThumb() &&
9595 !isV8EligibleForIT(&Inst)) {
9596 Warning(IDLoc, "deprecated instruction in IT block");
9597 }
9598 }
9599
9600 // Only move forward at the very end so that everything in validate
9601 // and process gets a consistent answer about whether we're in an IT
9602 // block.
9603 forwardITPosition();
9604
9605 // ITasm is an ARM mode pseudo-instruction that just sets the ITblock and
9606 // doesn't actually encode.
9607 if (Inst.getOpcode() == ARM::ITasm)
9608 return false;
9609
9610 Inst.setLoc(IDLoc);
9611 if (PendConditionalInstruction) {
9612 PendingConditionalInsts.push_back(Inst);
9613 if (isITBlockFull() || isITBlockTerminator(Inst))
9614 flushPendingInstructions(Out);
9615 } else {
9616 Out.EmitInstruction(Inst, getSTI());
9617 }
9618 return false;
9619 case Match_NearMisses:
9620 ReportNearMisses(NearMisses, IDLoc, Operands);
9621 return true;
9622 case Match_MnemonicFail: {
9623 FeatureBitset FBS = ComputeAvailableFeatures(getSTI().getFeatureBits());
9624 std::string Suggestion = ARMMnemonicSpellCheck(
9625 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken(), FBS);
9626 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction" + Suggestion,
9627 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[0]).getLocRange());
9628 }
9629 }
9630
9631 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!");
9632}
9633
9634/// parseDirective parses the arm specific directives
9635bool ARMAsmParser::ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) {
9636 const MCObjectFileInfo::Environment Format =
9637 getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->getObjectFileType();
9638 bool IsMachO = Format == MCObjectFileInfo::IsMachO;
9639 bool IsCOFF = Format == MCObjectFileInfo::IsCOFF;
9640
9641 StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getIdentifier();
9642 if (IDVal == ".word")
9643 parseLiteralValues(4, DirectiveID.getLoc());
9644 else if (IDVal == ".short" || IDVal == ".hword")
9645 parseLiteralValues(2, DirectiveID.getLoc());
9646 else if (IDVal == ".thumb")
9647 parseDirectiveThumb(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9648 else if (IDVal == ".arm")
9649 parseDirectiveARM(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9650 else if (IDVal == ".thumb_func")
9651 parseDirectiveThumbFunc(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9652 else if (IDVal == ".code")
9653 parseDirectiveCode(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9654 else if (IDVal == ".syntax")
9655 parseDirectiveSyntax(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9656 else if (IDVal == ".unreq")
9657 parseDirectiveUnreq(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9658 else if (IDVal == ".fnend")
9659 parseDirectiveFnEnd(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9660 else if (IDVal == ".cantunwind")
9661 parseDirectiveCantUnwind(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9662 else if (IDVal == ".personality")
9663 parseDirectivePersonality(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9664 else if (IDVal == ".handlerdata")
9665 parseDirectiveHandlerData(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9666 else if (IDVal == ".setfp")
9667 parseDirectiveSetFP(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9668 else if (IDVal == ".pad")
9669 parseDirectivePad(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9670 else if (IDVal == ".save")
9671 parseDirectiveRegSave(DirectiveID.getLoc(), false);
9672 else if (IDVal == ".vsave")
9673 parseDirectiveRegSave(DirectiveID.getLoc(), true);
9674 else if (IDVal == ".ltorg" || IDVal == ".pool")
9675 parseDirectiveLtorg(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9676 else if (IDVal == ".even")
9677 parseDirectiveEven(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9678 else if (IDVal == ".personalityindex")
9679 parseDirectivePersonalityIndex(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9680 else if (IDVal == ".unwind_raw")
9681 parseDirectiveUnwindRaw(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9682 else if (IDVal == ".movsp")
9683 parseDirectiveMovSP(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9684 else if (IDVal == ".arch_extension")
9685 parseDirectiveArchExtension(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9686 else if (IDVal == ".align")
9687 return parseDirectiveAlign(DirectiveID.getLoc()); // Use Generic on failure.
9688 else if (IDVal == ".thumb_set")
9689 parseDirectiveThumbSet(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9690 else if (IDVal == ".inst")
9691 parseDirectiveInst(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9692 else if (IDVal == ".inst.n")
9693 parseDirectiveInst(DirectiveID.getLoc(), 'n');
9694 else if (IDVal == ".inst.w")
9695 parseDirectiveInst(DirectiveID.getLoc(), 'w');
9696 else if (!IsMachO && !IsCOFF) {
9697 if (IDVal == ".arch")
9698 parseDirectiveArch(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9699 else if (IDVal == ".cpu")
9700 parseDirectiveCPU(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9701 else if (IDVal == ".eabi_attribute")
9702 parseDirectiveEabiAttr(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9703 else if (IDVal == ".fpu")
9704 parseDirectiveFPU(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9705 else if (IDVal == ".fnstart")
9706 parseDirectiveFnStart(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9707 else if (IDVal == ".object_arch")
9708 parseDirectiveObjectArch(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9709 else if (IDVal == ".tlsdescseq")
9710 parseDirectiveTLSDescSeq(DirectiveID.getLoc());
9711 else
9712 return true;
9713 } else
9714 return true;
9715 return false;
9716}
9717
9718/// parseLiteralValues
9719/// ::= .hword expression [, expression]*
9720/// ::= .short expression [, expression]*
9721/// ::= .word expression [, expression]*
9722bool ARMAsmParser::parseLiteralValues(unsigned Size, SMLoc L) {
9723 auto parseOne = [&]() -> bool {
9724 const MCExpr *Value;
9725 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value))
9726 return true;
9727 getParser().getStreamer().EmitValue(Value, Size, L);
9728 return false;
9729 };
9730 return (parseMany(parseOne));
9731}
9732
9733/// parseDirectiveThumb
9734/// ::= .thumb
9735bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveThumb(SMLoc L) {
9736 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive") ||
9737 check(!hasThumb(), L, "target does not support Thumb mode"))
9738 return true;
9739
9740 if (!isThumb())
9741 SwitchMode();
9742
9743 getParser().getStreamer().EmitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_Code16);
9744 return false;
9745}
9746
9747/// parseDirectiveARM
9748/// ::= .arm
9749bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveARM(SMLoc L) {
9750 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive") ||
9751 check(!hasARM(), L, "target does not support ARM mode"))
9752 return true;
9753
9754 if (isThumb())
9755 SwitchMode();
9756 getParser().getStreamer().EmitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_Code32);
9757 return false;
9758}
9759
9760void ARMAsmParser::doBeforeLabelEmit(MCSymbol *Symbol) {
9761 // We need to flush the current implicit IT block on a label, because it is
9762 // not legal to branch into an IT block.
9763 flushPendingInstructions(getStreamer());
9764}
9765
9766void ARMAsmParser::onLabelParsed(MCSymbol *Symbol) {
9767 if (NextSymbolIsThumb) {
9768 getParser().getStreamer().EmitThumbFunc(Symbol);
9769 NextSymbolIsThumb = false;
9770 }
9771}
9772
9773/// parseDirectiveThumbFunc
9774/// ::= .thumbfunc symbol_name
9775bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveThumbFunc(SMLoc L) {
9776 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
9777 const auto Format = getContext().getObjectFileInfo()->getObjectFileType();
9778 bool IsMachO = Format == MCObjectFileInfo::IsMachO;
9779
9780 // Darwin asm has (optionally) function name after .thumb_func direction
9781 // ELF doesn't
9782
9783 if (IsMachO) {
9784 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier) ||
9785 Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::String)) {
9786 MCSymbol *Func = getParser().getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(
9787 Parser.getTok().getIdentifier());
9788 getParser().getStreamer().EmitThumbFunc(Func);
9789 Parser.Lex();
9790 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
9791 "unexpected token in '.thumb_func' directive"))
9792 return true;
9793 return false;
9794 }
9795 }
9796
9797 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
9798 "unexpected token in '.thumb_func' directive"))
9799 return true;
9800
9801 NextSymbolIsThumb = true;
9802 return false;
9803}
9804
9805/// parseDirectiveSyntax
9806/// ::= .syntax unified | divided
9807bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveSyntax(SMLoc L) {
9808 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
9809 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
9810 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
9811 Error(L, "unexpected token in .syntax directive");
9812 return false;
9813 }
9814
9815 StringRef Mode = Tok.getString();
9816 Parser.Lex();
9817 if (check(Mode == "divided" || Mode == "DIVIDED", L,
9818 "'.syntax divided' arm assembly not supported") ||
9819 check(Mode != "unified" && Mode != "UNIFIED", L,
9820 "unrecognized syntax mode in .syntax directive") ||
9821 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive"))
9822 return true;
9823
9824 // TODO tell the MC streamer the mode
9825 // getParser().getStreamer().Emit???();
9826 return false;
9827}
9828
9829/// parseDirectiveCode
9830/// ::= .code 16 | 32
9831bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveCode(SMLoc L) {
9832 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
9833 const AsmToken &Tok = Parser.getTok();
9834 if (Tok.isNot(AsmToken::Integer))
9835 return Error(L, "unexpected token in .code directive");
9836 int64_t Val = Parser.getTok().getIntVal();
9837 if (Val != 16 && Val != 32) {
9838 Error(L, "invalid operand to .code directive");
9839 return false;
9840 }
9841 Parser.Lex();
9842
9843 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive"))
9844 return true;
9845
9846 if (Val == 16) {
9847 if (!hasThumb())
9848 return Error(L, "target does not support Thumb mode");
9849
9850 if (!isThumb())
9851 SwitchMode();
9852 getParser().getStreamer().EmitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_Code16);
9853 } else {
9854 if (!hasARM())
9855 return Error(L, "target does not support ARM mode");
9856
9857 if (isThumb())
9858 SwitchMode();
9859 getParser().getStreamer().EmitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_Code32);
9860 }
9861
9862 return false;
9863}
9864
9865/// parseDirectiveReq
9866/// ::= name .req registername
9867bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveReq(StringRef Name, SMLoc L) {
9868 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
9869 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the '.req' token.
9870 unsigned Reg;
9871 SMLoc SRegLoc, ERegLoc;
9872 if (check(ParseRegister(Reg, SRegLoc, ERegLoc), SRegLoc,
9873 "register name expected") ||
9874 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
9875 "unexpected input in .req directive."))
9876 return true;
9877
9878 if (RegisterReqs.insert(std::make_pair(Name, Reg)).first->second != Reg)
9879 return Error(SRegLoc,
9880 "redefinition of '" + Name + "' does not match original.");
9881
9882 return false;
9883}
9884
9885/// parseDirectiveUneq
9886/// ::= .unreq registername
9887bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveUnreq(SMLoc L) {
9888 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
9889 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
9890 return Error(L, "unexpected input in .unreq directive.");
9891 RegisterReqs.erase(Parser.getTok().getIdentifier().lower());
9892 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the identifier.
9893 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
9894 "unexpected input in '.unreq' directive"))
9895 return true;
9896 return false;
9897}
9898
9899// After changing arch/CPU, try to put the ARM/Thumb mode back to what it was
9900// before, if supported by the new target, or emit mapping symbols for the mode
9901// switch.
9902void ARMAsmParser::FixModeAfterArchChange(bool WasThumb, SMLoc Loc) {
9903 if (WasThumb != isThumb()) {
9904 if (WasThumb && hasThumb()) {
9905 // Stay in Thumb mode
9906 SwitchMode();
9907 } else if (!WasThumb && hasARM()) {
9908 // Stay in ARM mode
9909 SwitchMode();
9910 } else {
9911 // Mode switch forced, because the new arch doesn't support the old mode.
9912 getParser().getStreamer().EmitAssemblerFlag(isThumb() ? MCAF_Code16
9913 : MCAF_Code32);
9914 // Warn about the implcit mode switch. GAS does not switch modes here,
9915 // but instead stays in the old mode, reporting an error on any following
9916 // instructions as the mode does not exist on the target.
9917 Warning(Loc, Twine("new target does not support ") +
9918 (WasThumb ? "thumb" : "arm") + " mode, switching to " +
9919 (!WasThumb ? "thumb" : "arm") + " mode");
9920 }
9921 }
9922}
9923
9924/// parseDirectiveArch
9925/// ::= .arch token
9926bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveArch(SMLoc L) {
9927 StringRef Arch = getParser().parseStringToEndOfStatement().trim();
9928 ARM::ArchKind ID = ARM::parseArch(Arch);
9929
9930 if (ID == ARM::ArchKind::INVALID)
9931 return Error(L, "Unknown arch name");
9932
9933 bool WasThumb = isThumb();
9934 Triple T;
9935 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
9936 STI.setDefaultFeatures("", ("+" + ARM::getArchName(ID)).str());
9937 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits()));
9938 FixModeAfterArchChange(WasThumb, L);
9939
9940 getTargetStreamer().emitArch(ID);
9941 return false;
9942}
9943
9944/// parseDirectiveEabiAttr
9945/// ::= .eabi_attribute int, int [, "str"]
9946/// ::= .eabi_attribute Tag_name, int [, "str"]
9947bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveEabiAttr(SMLoc L) {
9948 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
9949 int64_t Tag;
9950 SMLoc TagLoc;
9951 TagLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
9952 if (Parser.getTok().is(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
9953 StringRef Name = Parser.getTok().getIdentifier();
9954 Tag = ARMBuildAttrs::AttrTypeFromString(Name);
9955 if (Tag == -1) {
9956 Error(TagLoc, "attribute name not recognised: " + Name);
9957 return false;
9958 }
9959 Parser.Lex();
9960 } else {
9961 const MCExpr *AttrExpr;
9962
9963 TagLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
9964 if (Parser.parseExpression(AttrExpr))
9965 return true;
9966
9967 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(AttrExpr);
9968 if (check(!CE, TagLoc, "expected numeric constant"))
9969 return true;
9970
9971 Tag = CE->getValue();
9972 }
9973
9974 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "comma expected"))
9975 return true;
9976
9977 StringRef StringValue = "";
9978 bool IsStringValue = false;
9979
9980 int64_t IntegerValue = 0;
9981 bool IsIntegerValue = false;
9982
9983 if (Tag == ARMBuildAttrs::CPU_raw_name || Tag == ARMBuildAttrs::CPU_name)
9984 IsStringValue = true;
9985 else if (Tag == ARMBuildAttrs::compatibility) {
9986 IsStringValue = true;
9987 IsIntegerValue = true;
9988 } else if (Tag < 32 || Tag % 2 == 0)
9989 IsIntegerValue = true;
9990 else if (Tag % 2 == 1)
9991 IsStringValue = true;
9992 else
9993 llvm_unreachable("invalid tag type");
9994
9995 if (IsIntegerValue) {
9996 const MCExpr *ValueExpr;
9997 SMLoc ValueExprLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
9998 if (Parser.parseExpression(ValueExpr))
9999 return true;
10000
10001 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(ValueExpr);
10002 if (!CE)
10003 return Error(ValueExprLoc, "expected numeric constant");
10004 IntegerValue = CE->getValue();
10005 }
10006
10007 if (Tag == ARMBuildAttrs::compatibility) {
10008 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "comma expected"))
10009 return true;
10010 }
10011
10012 if (IsStringValue) {
10013 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::String))
10014 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "bad string constant");
10015
10016 StringValue = Parser.getTok().getStringContents();
10017 Parser.Lex();
10018 }
10019
10020 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10021 "unexpected token in '.eabi_attribute' directive"))
10022 return true;
10023
10024 if (IsIntegerValue && IsStringValue) {
10025 assert(Tag == ARMBuildAttrs::compatibility);
10026 getTargetStreamer().emitIntTextAttribute(Tag, IntegerValue, StringValue);
10027 } else if (IsIntegerValue)
10028 getTargetStreamer().emitAttribute(Tag, IntegerValue);
10029 else if (IsStringValue)
10030 getTargetStreamer().emitTextAttribute(Tag, StringValue);
10031 return false;
10032}
10033
10034/// parseDirectiveCPU
10035/// ::= .cpu str
10036bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveCPU(SMLoc L) {
10037 StringRef CPU = getParser().parseStringToEndOfStatement().trim();
10038 getTargetStreamer().emitTextAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::CPU_name, CPU);
10039
10040 // FIXME: This is using table-gen data, but should be moved to
10041 // ARMTargetParser once that is table-gen'd.
10042 if (!getSTI().isCPUStringValid(CPU))
10043 return Error(L, "Unknown CPU name");
10044
10045 bool WasThumb = isThumb();
10046 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
10047 STI.setDefaultFeatures(CPU, "");
10048 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits()));
10049 FixModeAfterArchChange(WasThumb, L);
10050
10051 return false;
10052}
10053
10054/// parseDirectiveFPU
10055/// ::= .fpu str
10056bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveFPU(SMLoc L) {
10057 SMLoc FPUNameLoc = getTok().getLoc();
10058 StringRef FPU = getParser().parseStringToEndOfStatement().trim();
10059
10060 unsigned ID = ARM::parseFPU(FPU);
10061 std::vector<StringRef> Features;
10062 if (!ARM::getFPUFeatures(ID, Features))
10063 return Error(FPUNameLoc, "Unknown FPU name");
10064
10065 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
10066 for (auto Feature : Features)
10067 STI.ApplyFeatureFlag(Feature);
10068 setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits()));
10069
10070 getTargetStreamer().emitFPU(ID);
10071 return false;
10072}

10074/// parseDirectiveFnStart
10075/// ::= .fnstart
10076bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveFnStart(SMLoc L) {
10077 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10078 "unexpected token in '.fnstart' directive"))
10079 return true;
10080
10081 if (UC.hasFnStart()) {
10082 Error(L, ".fnstart starts before the end of previous one");
10083 UC.emitFnStartLocNotes();
10084 return true;
10085 }
10086
10087 // Reset the unwind directives parser state
10088 UC.reset();
10089
10090 getTargetStreamer().emitFnStart();
10091
10092 UC.recordFnStart(L);
10093 return false;
10094}
10095
10096/// parseDirectiveFnEnd
10097/// ::= .fnend
10098bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveFnEnd(SMLoc L) {
10099 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10100 "unexpected token in '.fnend' directive"))
10101 return true;
10102 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10103 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10104 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .fnend directive");
10105
10106 // Reset the unwind directives parser state
10107 getTargetStreamer().emitFnEnd();
10108
10109 UC.reset();
10110 return false;
10111}
