10113/// parseDirectiveCantUnwind
10114/// ::= .cantunwind
10115bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveCantUnwind(SMLoc L) {
10116 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10117 "unexpected token in '.cantunwind' directive"))
10118 return true;
10119
10120 UC.recordCantUnwind(L);
10121 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10122 if (check(!UC.hasFnStart(), L, ".fnstart must precede .cantunwind directive"))
10123 return true;
10124
10125 if (UC.hasHandlerData()) {
10126 Error(L, ".cantunwind can't be used with .handlerdata directive");
10127 UC.emitHandlerDataLocNotes();
10128 return true;
10129 }
10130 if (UC.hasPersonality()) {
10131 Error(L, ".cantunwind can't be used with .personality directive");
10132 UC.emitPersonalityLocNotes();
10133 return true;
10134 }
10135
10136 getTargetStreamer().emitCantUnwind();
10137 return false;
10138}
10139
10140/// parseDirectivePersonality
10141/// ::= .personality name
10142bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectivePersonality(SMLoc L) {
10143 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10144 bool HasExistingPersonality = UC.hasPersonality();
10145
10146 // Parse the name of the personality routine
10147 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
10148 return Error(L, "unexpected input in .personality directive.");
10149 StringRef Name(Parser.getTok().getIdentifier());
10150 Parser.Lex();
10151
10152 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10153 "unexpected token in '.personality' directive"))
10154 return true;
10155
10156 UC.recordPersonality(L);
10157
10158 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10159 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10160 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .personality directive");
10161 if (UC.cantUnwind()) {
10162 Error(L, ".personality can't be used with .cantunwind directive");
10163 UC.emitCantUnwindLocNotes();
10164 return true;
10165 }
10166 if (UC.hasHandlerData()) {
10167 Error(L, ".personality must precede .handlerdata directive");
10168 UC.emitHandlerDataLocNotes();
10169 return true;
10170 }
10171 if (HasExistingPersonality) {
10172 Error(L, "multiple personality directives");
10173 UC.emitPersonalityLocNotes();
10174 return true;
10175 }
10176
10177 MCSymbol *PR = getParser().getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
10178 getTargetStreamer().emitPersonality(PR);
10179 return false;
10180}
10181
10182/// parseDirectiveHandlerData
10183/// ::= .handlerdata
10184bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveHandlerData(SMLoc L) {
10185 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10186 "unexpected token in '.handlerdata' directive"))
10187 return true;
10188
10189 UC.recordHandlerData(L);
10190 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10191 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10192 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .personality directive");
10193 if (UC.cantUnwind()) {
10194 Error(L, ".handlerdata can't be used with .cantunwind directive");
10195 UC.emitCantUnwindLocNotes();
10196 return true;
10197 }
10198
10199 getTargetStreamer().emitHandlerData();
10200 return false;
10201}
10202
10203/// parseDirectiveSetFP
10204/// ::= .setfp fpreg, spreg [, offset]
10205bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveSetFP(SMLoc L) {
10206 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10207 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10208 if (check(!UC.hasFnStart(), L, ".fnstart must precede .setfp directive") ||
10209 check(UC.hasHandlerData(), L,
10210 ".setfp must precede .handlerdata directive"))
10211 return true;
10212
10213 // Parse fpreg
10214 SMLoc FPRegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10215 int FPReg = tryParseRegister();
10216
10217 if (check(FPReg == -1, FPRegLoc, "frame pointer register expected") ||
10218 Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "comma expected"))
10219 return true;
10220
10221 // Parse spreg
10222 SMLoc SPRegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10223 int SPReg = tryParseRegister();
10224 if (check(SPReg == -1, SPRegLoc, "stack pointer register expected") ||
10225 check(SPReg != ARM::SP && SPReg != UC.getFPReg(), SPRegLoc,
10226 "register should be either $sp or the latest fp register"))
10227 return true;
10228
10229 // Update the frame pointer register
10230 UC.saveFPReg(FPReg);
10231
10232 // Parse offset
10233 int64_t Offset = 0;
10234 if (Parser.parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
10235 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
10236 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
10237 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
10238 Parser.Lex(); // skip hash token.
10239
10240 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr;
10241 SMLoc ExLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10242 SMLoc EndLoc;
10243 if (getParser().parseExpression(OffsetExpr, EndLoc))
10244 return Error(ExLoc, "malformed setfp offset");
10245 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(OffsetExpr);
10246 if (check(!CE, ExLoc, "setfp offset must be an immediate"))
10247 return true;
10248 Offset = CE->getValue();
10249 }
10250
10251 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
10252 return true;
10253
10254 getTargetStreamer().emitSetFP(static_cast<unsigned>(FPReg),
10255 static_cast<unsigned>(SPReg), Offset);
10256 return false;
10257}
10258
10259/// parseDirective
10260/// ::= .pad offset
10261bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectivePad(SMLoc L) {
10262 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10263 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10264 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10265 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .pad directive");
10266 if (UC.hasHandlerData())
10267 return Error(L, ".pad must precede .handlerdata directive");
10268
10269 // Parse the offset
10270 if (Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Hash) &&
10271 Parser.getTok().isNot(AsmToken::Dollar))
10272 return Error(Parser.getTok().getLoc(), "'#' expected");
10273 Parser.Lex(); // skip hash token.
10274
10275 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr;
10276 SMLoc ExLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10277 SMLoc EndLoc;
10278 if (getParser().parseExpression(OffsetExpr, EndLoc))
10279 return Error(ExLoc, "malformed pad offset");
10280 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(OffsetExpr);
10281 if (!CE)
10282 return Error(ExLoc, "pad offset must be an immediate");
10283
10284 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10285 "unexpected token in '.pad' directive"))
10286 return true;
10287
10288 getTargetStreamer().emitPad(CE->getValue());
10289 return false;
10290}
10291
10292/// parseDirectiveRegSave
10293/// ::= .save { registers }
10294/// ::= .vsave { registers }
10295bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveRegSave(SMLoc L, bool IsVector) {
10296 // Check the ordering of unwind directives
10297 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10298 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .save or .vsave directives");
10299 if (UC.hasHandlerData())
10300 return Error(L, ".save or .vsave must precede .handlerdata directive");
10301
10302 // RAII object to make sure parsed operands are deleted.
10303 SmallVector<std::unique_ptr<MCParsedAsmOperand>, 1> Operands;
10304
10305 // Parse the register list
10306 if (parseRegisterList(Operands) ||
10307 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive"))
10308 return true;
10309 ARMOperand &Op = (ARMOperand &)*Operands[0];
10310 if (!IsVector && !Op.isRegList())
10311 return Error(L, ".save expects GPR registers");
10312 if (IsVector && !Op.isDPRRegList())
10313 return Error(L, ".vsave expects DPR registers");
10314
10315 getTargetStreamer().emitRegSave(Op.getRegList(), IsVector);
10316 return false;
10317}
10318
10319/// parseDirectiveInst
10320/// ::= .inst opcode [, ...]
10321/// ::= .inst.n opcode [, ...]
10322/// ::= .inst.w opcode [, ...]
10323bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveInst(SMLoc Loc, char Suffix) {
10324 int Width = 4;
10325
10326 if (isThumb()) {
10327 switch (Suffix) {
10328 case 'n':
10329 Width = 2;
10330 break;
10331 case 'w':
10332 break;
10333 default:
10334 Width = 0;
10335 break;
10336 }
10337 } else {
10338 if (Suffix)
10339 return Error(Loc, "width suffixes are invalid in ARM mode");
10340 }
10341
10342 auto parseOne = [&]() -> bool {
10343 const MCExpr *Expr;
10344 if (getParser().parseExpression(Expr))
10345 return true;
10346 const MCConstantExpr *Value = dyn_cast_or_null<MCConstantExpr>(Expr);
10347 if (!Value) {
10348 return Error(Loc, "expected constant expression");
10349 }
10350
10351 char CurSuffix = Suffix;
10352 switch (Width) {
10353 case 2:
10354 if (Value->getValue() > 0xffff)
10355 return Error(Loc, "inst.n operand is too big, use inst.w instead");
10356 break;
10357 case 4:
10358 if (Value->getValue() > 0xffffffff)
10359 return Error(Loc, StringRef(Suffix ? "inst.w" : "inst") +
10360 " operand is too big");
10361 break;
10362 case 0:
10363 // Thumb mode, no width indicated. Guess from the opcode, if possible.
10364 if (Value->getValue() < 0xe800)
10365 CurSuffix = 'n';
10366 else if (Value->getValue() >= 0xe8000000)
10367 CurSuffix = 'w';
10368 else
10369 return Error(Loc, "cannot determine Thumb instruction size, "
10370 "use inst.n/inst.w instead");
10371 break;
10372 default:
10373 llvm_unreachable("only supported widths are 2 and 4");
10374 }
10375
10376 getTargetStreamer().emitInst(Value->getValue(), CurSuffix);
10377 return false;
10378 };
10379
10380 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
10381 return Error(Loc, "expected expression following directive");
10382 if (parseMany(parseOne))
10383 return true;
10384 return false;
10385}
10386
10387/// parseDirectiveLtorg
10388/// ::= .ltorg | .pool
10389bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveLtorg(SMLoc L) {
10390 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive"))
10391 return true;
10392 getTargetStreamer().emitCurrentConstantPool();
10393 return false;
10394}
10395
10396bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveEven(SMLoc L) {
10397 const MCSection *Section = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
10398
10399 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement, "unexpected token in directive"))
10400 return true;
10401
10402 if (!Section) {
10403 getStreamer().InitSections(false);
10404 Section = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
10405 }
10406
10407 assert(Section && "must have section to emit alignment");
10408 if (Section->UseCodeAlign())
10409 getStreamer().EmitCodeAlignment(2);
10410 else
10411 getStreamer().EmitValueToAlignment(2);
10412
10413 return false;
10414}
10415
10416/// parseDirectivePersonalityIndex
10417/// ::= .personalityindex index
10418bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectivePersonalityIndex(SMLoc L) {
10419 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10420 bool HasExistingPersonality = UC.hasPersonality();
10421
10422 const MCExpr *IndexExpression;
10423 SMLoc IndexLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10424 if (Parser.parseExpression(IndexExpression) ||
10425 parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10426 "unexpected token in '.personalityindex' directive")) {
10427 return true;
10428 }
10429
10430 UC.recordPersonalityIndex(L);
10431
10432 if (!UC.hasFnStart()) {
10433 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .personalityindex directive");
10434 }
10435 if (UC.cantUnwind()) {
10436 Error(L, ".personalityindex cannot be used with .cantunwind");
10437 UC.emitCantUnwindLocNotes();
10438 return true;
10439 }
10440 if (UC.hasHandlerData()) {
10441 Error(L, ".personalityindex must precede .handlerdata directive");
10442 UC.emitHandlerDataLocNotes();
10443 return true;
10444 }
10445 if (HasExistingPersonality) {
10446 Error(L, "multiple personality directives");
10447 UC.emitPersonalityLocNotes();
10448 return true;
10449 }
10450
10451 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(IndexExpression);
10452 if (!CE)
10453 return Error(IndexLoc, "index must be a constant number");
10454 if (CE->getValue() < 0 || CE->getValue() >= ARM::EHABI::NUM_PERSONALITY_INDEX)
10455 return Error(IndexLoc,
10456 "personality routine index should be in range [0-3]");
10457
10458 getTargetStreamer().emitPersonalityIndex(CE->getValue());
10459 return false;
10460}
10461
10462/// parseDirectiveUnwindRaw
10463/// ::= .unwind_raw offset, opcode [, opcode...]
10464bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveUnwindRaw(SMLoc L) {
10465 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10466 int64_t StackOffset;
10467 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr;
10468 SMLoc OffsetLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
10469
10470 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10471 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .unwind_raw directives");
10472 if (getParser().parseExpression(OffsetExpr))
10473 return Error(OffsetLoc, "expected expression");
10474
10475 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(OffsetExpr);
10476 if (!CE)
10477 return Error(OffsetLoc, "offset must be a constant");
10478
10479 StackOffset = CE->getValue();
10480
10481 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma"))
10482 return true;
10483
10484 SmallVector<uint8_t, 16> Opcodes;
10485
10486 auto parseOne = [&]() -> bool {
10487 const MCExpr *OE;
10488 SMLoc OpcodeLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
10489 if (check(getLexer().is(AsmToken::EndOfStatement) ||
10490 Parser.parseExpression(OE),
10491 OpcodeLoc, "expected opcode expression"))
10492 return true;
10493 const MCConstantExpr *OC = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(OE);
10494 if (!OC)
10495 return Error(OpcodeLoc, "opcode value must be a constant");
10496 const int64_t Opcode = OC->getValue();
10497 if (Opcode & ~0xff)
10498 return Error(OpcodeLoc, "invalid opcode");
10499 Opcodes.push_back(uint8_t(Opcode));
10500 return false;
10501 };
10502
10503 // Must have at least 1 element
10504 SMLoc OpcodeLoc = getLexer().getLoc();
10505 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
10506 return Error(OpcodeLoc, "expected opcode expression");
10507 if (parseMany(parseOne))
10508 return true;
10509
10510 getTargetStreamer().emitUnwindRaw(StackOffset, Opcodes);
10511 return false;
10512}
10513
10514/// parseDirectiveTLSDescSeq
10515/// ::= .tlsdescseq tls-variable
10516bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveTLSDescSeq(SMLoc L) {
10517 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10518
10519 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
10520 return TokError("expected variable after '.tlsdescseq' directive");
10521
10522 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE =
10523 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Parser.getTok().getIdentifier(),
10524 MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_ARM_TLSDESCSEQ, getContext());
10525 Lex();
10526
10527 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10528 "unexpected token in '.tlsdescseq' directive"))
10529 return true;
10530
10531 getTargetStreamer().AnnotateTLSDescriptorSequence(SRE);
10532 return false;
10533}
10534
10535/// parseDirectiveMovSP
10536/// ::= .movsp reg [, #offset]
10537bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveMovSP(SMLoc L) {
10538 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10539 if (!UC.hasFnStart())
10540 return Error(L, ".fnstart must precede .movsp directives");
10541 if (UC.getFPReg() != ARM::SP)
10542 return Error(L, "unexpected .movsp directive");
10543
10544 SMLoc SPRegLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10545 int SPReg = tryParseRegister();
10546 if (SPReg == -1)
10547 return Error(SPRegLoc, "register expected");
10548 if (SPReg == ARM::SP || SPReg == ARM::PC)
10549 return Error(SPRegLoc, "sp and pc are not permitted in .movsp directive");
10550
10551 int64_t Offset = 0;
10552 if (Parser.parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
10553 if (Parser.parseToken(AsmToken::Hash, "expected #constant"))
10554 return true;
10555
10556 const MCExpr *OffsetExpr;
10557 SMLoc OffsetLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10558
10559 if (Parser.parseExpression(OffsetExpr))
10560 return Error(OffsetLoc, "malformed offset expression");
10561
10562 const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(OffsetExpr);
10563 if (!CE)
10564 return Error(OffsetLoc, "offset must be an immediate constant");
10565
10566 Offset = CE->getValue();
10567 }
10568
10569 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10570 "unexpected token in '.movsp' directive"))
10571 return true;
10572
10573 getTargetStreamer().emitMovSP(SPReg, Offset);
10574 UC.saveFPReg(SPReg);
10575
10576 return false;
10577}
10578
10579/// parseDirectiveObjectArch
10580/// ::= .object_arch name
10581bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveObjectArch(SMLoc L) {
10582 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10583 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
10584 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "unexpected token");
10585
10586 StringRef Arch = Parser.getTok().getString();
10587 SMLoc ArchLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10588 Lex();
10589
10590 ARM::ArchKind ID = ARM::parseArch(Arch);
10591
10592 if (ID == ARM::ArchKind::INVALID)
10593 return Error(ArchLoc, "unknown architecture '" + Arch + "'");
10594 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
10595 return true;
10596
10597 getTargetStreamer().emitObjectArch(ID);
10598 return false;
10599}
10600
10601/// parseDirectiveAlign
10602/// ::= .align
10603bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveAlign(SMLoc L) {
10604 // NOTE: if this is not the end of the statement, fall back to the target
10605 // agnostic handling for this directive which will correctly handle this.
10606 if (parseOptionalToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
10607 // '.align' is target specifically handled to mean 2**2 byte alignment.
10608 const MCSection *Section = getStreamer().getCurrentSectionOnly();
10609 assert(Section && "must have section to emit alignment");
10610 if (Section->UseCodeAlign())
10611 getStreamer().EmitCodeAlignment(4, 0);
10612 else
10613 getStreamer().EmitValueToAlignment(4, 0, 1, 0);
10614 return false;
10615 }
10616 return true;
10617}
10618
10619/// parseDirectiveThumbSet
10620/// ::= .thumb_set name, value
10621bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveThumbSet(SMLoc L) {
10622 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10623
10624 StringRef Name;
10625 if (check(Parser.parseIdentifier(Name),
10626 "expected identifier after '.thumb_set'") ||
10627 parseToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected comma after name '" + Name + "'"))
10628 return true;
10629
10630 MCSymbol *Sym;
10631 const MCExpr *Value;
10632 if (MCParserUtils::parseAssignmentExpression(Name, /* allow_redef */ true,
10633 Parser, Sym, Value))
10634 return true;
10635
10636 getTargetStreamer().emitThumbSet(Sym, Value);
10637 return false;
10638}

10642 RegisterMCAsmParser<ARMAsmParser> X(getTheARMLETarget());
10643 RegisterMCAsmParser<ARMAsmParser> Y(getTheARMBETarget());
10644 RegisterMCAsmParser<ARMAsmParser> A(getTheThumbLETarget());
10645 RegisterMCAsmParser<ARMAsmParser> B(getTheThumbBETarget());
10646}

10648#define GET_REGISTER_MATCHER

10654// Some diagnostics need to vary with subtarget features, so they are handled
10655// here. For example, the DPR class has either 16 or 32 registers, depending
10656// on the FPU available.
10657const char *
10658ARMAsmParser::getCustomOperandDiag(ARMMatchResultTy MatchError) {
10659 switch (MatchError) {
10660 // rGPR contains sp starting with ARMv8.
10661 case Match_rGPR:
10662 return hasV8Ops() ? "operand must be a register in range [r0, r14]"
10663 : "operand must be a register in range [r0, r12] or r14";
10664 // DPR contains 16 registers for some FPUs, and 32 for others.
10665 case Match_DPR:
10666 return hasD32() ? "operand must be a register in range [d0, d31]"
10667 : "operand must be a register in range [d0, d15]";
10668 case Match_DPR_RegList:
10669 return hasD32() ? "operand must be a list of registers in range [d0, d31]"
10670 : "operand must be a list of registers in range [d0, d15]";
10671
10672 // For all other diags, use the static string from tablegen.
10673 default:
10674 return getMatchKindDiag(MatchError);
10675 }
10676}
10677
10678// Process the list of near-misses, throwing away ones we don't want to report
10679// to the user, and converting the rest to a source location and string that
10680// should be reported.
10681void
10682ARMAsmParser::FilterNearMisses(SmallVectorImpl<NearMissInfo> &NearMissesIn,
10683 SmallVectorImpl<NearMissMessage> &NearMissesOut,
10684 SMLoc IDLoc, OperandVector &Operands) {
10685 // TODO: If operand didn't match, sub in a dummy one and run target
10686 // predicate, so that we can avoid reporting near-misses that are invalid?
10687 // TODO: Many operand types dont have SuperClasses set, so we report
10688 // redundant ones.
10689 // TODO: Some operands are superclasses of registers (e.g.
10690 // MCK_RegShiftedImm), we don't have any way to represent that currently.
10691 // TODO: This is not all ARM-specific, can some of it be factored out?
10692
10693 // Record some information about near-misses that we have already seen, so
10694 // that we can avoid reporting redundant ones. For example, if there are
10695 // variants of an instruction that take 8- and 16-bit immediates, we want
10696 // to only report the widest one.
10697 std::multimap<unsigned, unsigned> OperandMissesSeen;
10698 SmallSet<FeatureBitset, 4> FeatureMissesSeen;
10699 bool ReportedTooFewOperands = false;
10700
10701 // Process the near-misses in reverse order, so that we see more general ones
10702 // first, and so can avoid emitting more specific ones.
10703 for (NearMissInfo &I : reverse(NearMissesIn)) {
10704 switch (I.getKind()) {
10705 case NearMissInfo::NearMissOperand: {
10706 SMLoc OperandLoc =
10707 ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[I.getOperandIndex()]).getStartLoc();
10708 const char *OperandDiag =
10709 getCustomOperandDiag((ARMMatchResultTy)I.getOperandError());
10710
10711 // If we have already emitted a message for a superclass, don't also report
10712 // the sub-class. We consider all operand classes that we don't have a
10713 // specialised diagnostic for to be equal for the propose of this check,
10714 // so that we don't report the generic error multiple times on the same
10715 // operand.
10716 unsigned DupCheckMatchClass = OperandDiag ? I.getOperandClass() : ~0U;
10717 auto PrevReports = OperandMissesSeen.equal_range(I.getOperandIndex());
10718 if (std::any_of(PrevReports.first, PrevReports.second,
10719 [DupCheckMatchClass](
10720 const std::pair<unsigned, unsigned> Pair) {
10721 if (DupCheckMatchClass == ~0U || Pair.second == ~0U)
10722 return Pair.second == DupCheckMatchClass;
10723 else
10724 return isSubclass((MatchClassKind)DupCheckMatchClass,
10725 (MatchClassKind)Pair.second);
10726 }))
10727 break;
10728 OperandMissesSeen.insert(
10729 std::make_pair(I.getOperandIndex(), DupCheckMatchClass));
10730
10731 NearMissMessage Message;
10732 Message.Loc = OperandLoc;
10733 if (OperandDiag) {
10734 Message.Message = OperandDiag;
10735 } else if (I.getOperandClass() == InvalidMatchClass) {
10736 Message.Message = "too many operands for instruction";
10737 } else {
10738 Message.Message = "invalid operand for instruction";
10739 LLVM_DEBUG(
10740 dbgs() << "Missing diagnostic string for operand class "
10741 << getMatchClassName((MatchClassKind)I.getOperandClass())
10742 << I.getOperandClass() << ", error " << I.getOperandError()
10743 << ", opcode " << MII.getName(I.getOpcode()) << "\n");
10744 }
10745 NearMissesOut.emplace_back(Message);
10746 break;
10747 }
10748 case NearMissInfo::NearMissFeature: {
10749 const FeatureBitset &MissingFeatures = I.getFeatures();
10750 // Don't report the same set of features twice.
10751 if (FeatureMissesSeen.count(MissingFeatures))
10752 break;
10753 FeatureMissesSeen.insert(MissingFeatures);
10754
10755 // Special case: don't report a feature set which includes arm-mode for
10756 // targets that don't have ARM mode.
10757 if (MissingFeatures.test(Feature_IsARMBit) && !hasARM())
10758 break;
10759 // Don't report any near-misses that both require switching instruction
10760 // set, and adding other subtarget features.
10761 if (isThumb() && MissingFeatures.test(Feature_IsARMBit) &&
10762 MissingFeatures.count() > 1)
10763 break;
10764 if (!isThumb() && MissingFeatures.test(Feature_IsThumbBit) &&
10765 MissingFeatures.count() > 1)
10766 break;
10767 if (!isThumb() && MissingFeatures.test(Feature_IsThumb2Bit) &&
10768 (MissingFeatures & ~FeatureBitset({Feature_IsThumb2Bit,
10769 Feature_IsThumbBit})).any())
10770 break;
10771 if (isMClass() && MissingFeatures.test(Feature_HasNEONBit))
10772 break;
10773
10774 NearMissMessage Message;
10775 Message.Loc = IDLoc;
10776 raw_svector_ostream OS(Message.Message);
10777
10778 OS << "instruction requires:";
10779 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MissingFeatures.size(); i != e; ++i)
10780 if (MissingFeatures.test(i))
10781 OS << ' ' << getSubtargetFeatureName(i);
10782
10783 NearMissesOut.emplace_back(Message);
10784
10785 break;
10786 }
10787 case NearMissInfo::NearMissPredicate: {
10788 NearMissMessage Message;
10789 Message.Loc = IDLoc;
10790 switch (I.getPredicateError()) {
10791 case Match_RequiresNotITBlock:
10792 Message.Message = "flag setting instruction only valid outside IT block";
10793 break;
10794 case Match_RequiresITBlock:
10795 Message.Message = "instruction only valid inside IT block";
10796 break;
10797 case Match_RequiresV6:
10798 Message.Message = "instruction variant requires ARMv6 or later";
10799 break;
10800 case Match_RequiresThumb2:
10801 Message.Message = "instruction variant requires Thumb2";
10802 break;
10803 case Match_RequiresV8:
10804 Message.Message = "instruction variant requires ARMv8 or later";
10805 break;
10806 case Match_RequiresFlagSetting:
10807 Message.Message = "no flag-preserving variant of this instruction available";
10808 break;
10809 case Match_InvalidOperand:
10810 Message.Message = "invalid operand for instruction";
10811 break;
10812 default:
10813 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled target predicate error");
10814 break;
10815 }
10816 NearMissesOut.emplace_back(Message);
10817 break;
10818 }
10819 case NearMissInfo::NearMissTooFewOperands: {
10820 if (!ReportedTooFewOperands) {
10821 SMLoc EndLoc = ((ARMOperand &)*Operands.back()).getEndLoc();
10822 NearMissesOut.emplace_back(NearMissMessage{
10823 EndLoc, StringRef("too few operands for instruction")});
10824 ReportedTooFewOperands = true;
10825 }
10826 break;
10827 }
10828 case NearMissInfo::NoNearMiss:
10829 // This should never leave the matcher.
10830 llvm_unreachable("not a near-miss");
10831 break;
10832 }
10833 }
10834}
10835
10836void ARMAsmParser::ReportNearMisses(SmallVectorImpl<NearMissInfo> &NearMisses,
10837 SMLoc IDLoc, OperandVector &Operands) {
10838 SmallVector<NearMissMessage, 4> Messages;
10839 FilterNearMisses(NearMisses, Messages, IDLoc, Operands);
10840
10841 if (Messages.size() == 0) {
10842 // No near-misses were found, so the best we can do is "invalid
10843 // instruction".
10844 Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction");
10845 } else if (Messages.size() == 1) {
10846 // One near miss was found, report it as the sole error.
10847 Error(Messages[0].Loc, Messages[0].Message);
10848 } else {
10849 // More than one near miss, so report a generic "invalid instruction"
10850 // error, followed by notes for each of the near-misses.
10851 Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction, any one of the following would fix this:");
10852 for (auto &M : Messages) {
10853 Note(M.Loc, M.Message);
10854 }
10855 }
10856}
10857
10858/// parseDirectiveArchExtension
10859/// ::= .arch_extension [no]feature
10860bool ARMAsmParser::parseDirectiveArchExtension(SMLoc L) {
10861 // FIXME: This structure should be moved inside ARMTargetParser
10862 // when we start to table-generate them, and we can use the ARM
10863 // flags below, that were generated by table-gen.
10864 static const struct {
10865 const unsigned Kind;
10866 const FeatureBitset ArchCheck;
10867 const FeatureBitset Features;
10868 } Extensions[] = {
10869 { ARM::AEK_CRC, {Feature_HasV8Bit}, {ARM::FeatureCRC} },
10870 { ARM::AEK_CRYPTO, {Feature_HasV8Bit},
10871 {ARM::FeatureCrypto, ARM::FeatureNEON, ARM::FeatureFPARMv8} },
10872 { ARM::AEK_FP, {Feature_HasV8Bit},
10873 {ARM::FeatureVFP2_D16_SP, ARM::FeatureFPARMv8} },
10874 { (ARM::AEK_HWDIVTHUMB | ARM::AEK_HWDIVARM),
10875 {Feature_HasV7Bit, Feature_IsNotMClassBit},
10876 {ARM::FeatureHWDivThumb, ARM::FeatureHWDivARM} },
10877 { ARM::AEK_MP, {Feature_HasV7Bit, Feature_IsNotMClassBit},
10878 {ARM::FeatureMP} },
10879 { ARM::AEK_SIMD, {Feature_HasV8Bit},
10880 {ARM::FeatureNEON, ARM::FeatureVFP2_D16_SP, ARM::FeatureFPARMv8} },
10881 { ARM::AEK_SEC, {Feature_HasV6KBit}, {ARM::FeatureTrustZone} },
10882 // FIXME: Only available in A-class, isel not predicated
10883 { ARM::AEK_VIRT, {Feature_HasV7Bit}, {ARM::FeatureVirtualization} },
10884 { ARM::AEK_FP16, {Feature_HasV8_2aBit},
10885 {ARM::FeatureFPARMv8, ARM::FeatureFullFP16} },
10886 { ARM::AEK_RAS, {Feature_HasV8Bit}, {ARM::FeatureRAS} },
10887 { ARM::AEK_LOB, {Feature_HasV8_1MMainlineBit}, {ARM::FeatureLOB} },
10888 // FIXME: Unsupported extensions.
10889 { ARM::AEK_OS, {}, {} },
10890 { ARM::AEK_IWMMXT, {}, {} },
10891 { ARM::AEK_IWMMXT2, {}, {} },
10892 { ARM::AEK_MAVERICK, {}, {} },
10893 { ARM::AEK_XSCALE, {}, {} },
10894 };
10895
10896 MCAsmParser &Parser = getParser();
10897
10898 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::Identifier))
10899 return Error(getLexer().getLoc(), "expected architecture extension name");
10900
10901 StringRef Name = Parser.getTok().getString();
10902 SMLoc ExtLoc = Parser.getTok().getLoc();
10903 Lex();
10904
10905 if (parseToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement,
10906 "unexpected token in '.arch_extension' directive"))
10907 return true;
10908
10909 bool EnableFeature = true;
10910 if (Name.startswith_lower("no")) {
10911 EnableFeature = false;
10912 Name = Name.substr(2);
10913 }
10914 unsigned FeatureKind = ARM::parseArchExt(Name);
10915 if (FeatureKind == ARM::AEK_INVALID)
10916 return Error(ExtLoc, "unknown architectural extension: " + Name);
10917
10918 for (const auto &Extension : Extensions) {
10919 if (Extension.Kind != FeatureKind)
10920 continue;
10921
10922 if (Extension.Features.none())
10923 return Error(ExtLoc, "unsupported architectural extension: " + Name);
10924
10925 if ((getAvailableFeatures() & Extension.ArchCheck) != Extension.ArchCheck)
10926 return Error(ExtLoc, "architectural extension '" + Name +
10927 "' is not "
10928 "allowed for the current base architecture");
10929
10930 MCSubtargetInfo &STI = copySTI();
10931 if (EnableFeature) {
10932 STI.SetFeatureBitsTransitively(Extension.Features);
10933 } else {
10934 STI.ClearFeatureBitsTransitively(Extension.Features);
10935 }
10936 FeatureBitset Features = ComputeAvailableFeatures(STI.getFeatureBits());
10937 setAvailableFeatures(Features);
10938 return false;
10939 }
10940
10941 return Error(ExtLoc, "unknown architectural extension: " + Name);
10942}
10943
10944// Define this matcher function after the auto-generated include so we
10945// have the match class enum definitions.
10946unsigned ARMAsmParser::validateTargetOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &AsmOp,
10947 unsigned Kind) {
10948 ARMOperand &Op = static_cast<ARMOperand &>(AsmOp);
10949 // If the kind is a token for a literal immediate, check if our asm
10950 // operand matches. This is for InstAliases which have a fixed-value
10951 // immediate in the syntax.
10952 switch (Kind) {
10953 default: break;
10954 case MCK__35_0:
10955 if (Op.isImm())
10956 if (const MCConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<MCConstantExpr>(Op.getImm()))
10957 if (CE->getValue() == 0)
10958 return Match_Success;
10959 break;
10960 case MCK_ModImm:
10961 if (Op.isImm()) {
10962 const MCExpr *SOExpr = Op.getImm();
10963 int64_t Value;
10964 if (!SOExpr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Value))
10965 return Match_Success;
10966 assert((Value >= std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() &&
10967 Value <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) &&
10968 "expression value must be representable in 32 bits");
10969 }
10970 break;
10971 case MCK_rGPR:
10972 if (hasV8Ops() && Op.isReg() && Op.getReg() == ARM::SP)
10973 return Match_Success;
10974 return Match_rGPR;
10975 case MCK_GPRPair:
10976 if (Op.isReg() &&
10977 MRI->getRegClass(ARM::GPRRegClassID).contains(Op.getReg()))
10978 return Match_Success;
10979 break;
10980 }
10981 return Match_InvalidOperand;
10982}
